<HTML> <HEAD><TITLE>C.I. Mutual Funds News</TITLE></HEAD> <BODY BGCOLOR="#EBE8DF"><CENTER><TABLE CELLSPACING=2 CELLPADDING=0 BORDER=2><TR><TD><A HREF="home2.html"><IMG BORDER=0 ALT="C.I. Mutual Funds" SRC="pagebanner_white.gif"></A></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER><P><CENTER><IMG WIDTH=403 HEIGHT=82 BORDER=0 ALT="How To Buy C.I. Mutual Funds" SRC="headings/head_howtobuy.gif"></A></CENTER><HR NOSHADE><P>The first step is to contact a financial adviser. Because a successful investment strategy must be tailored to meet your needs, C.I. Funds are available only through brokers, investment dealers, financial planners and other investment professionals. Their understanding of investments and ability to communicate with you is vital to providing the best possible service.<P>Ask your friends and colleagues if they can recommend someone. The Canadian Association of Financial Planners oversees all registered financial planners. They publish <I>A Consumer Guide to Financial Planning</I>, available by calling 416-593-6592, and may be able to refer you to a local chapter for advice. Or, feel free to contact C.I. at 1 (800) 268-9374. We will recommend advisers in your area, but the final decision is up to you.<P><B>Purchase Methods</B><BR>C.I. Funds may be purchased by either the deferred sales charge method or the initial commission method. With a deferred sales charge, there is no commission at the time of purchase. However, if you redeem within seven years of purchase, charges will apply which gradually decrease the longer your investment is held in the fund.<P>With the initial commission method, a commission will be deducted by your financial adviser at the time of purchase. This commission is negotiable between you and your adviser and may range from 0% to 5%.<P><B>Plans and Products</B><BR>There are three types of investment plans - systematic redemption to provide income, pre-authorized chequing for regular purchases, and interfund exchange for transferring from one fund to another. Your investment may be held in an <A HREF="#open">open account</A>, a <A HREF="#rrsp">registered retirement savings plan</A> (RRSP), a <A HREF="#rrif">registered retirement income fund</A> (RRIF), a <A HREF="#lira">locked-in retirement account</A> (LIRA) or a <A HREF="#lif">life income fund</A> (LIF).<P><B>Pre-authorized Cheque Plans</B><BR><UL><LI>Takes advantage of dollar-cost averaging.<LI>Regular purchases of Fund units.<LI>No initial purchase necessary.<LI>Minimum automatic investment of $25 per month or per quarter.<LI>Can be stopped anytime at no charge.</UL><B>Systematic Redemption Plan</B><BR><UL><LI>If you have units valued at $5,000 or more in any Fund<LI>Regular redemptions (withdrawals) provide income<LI>No minimum<LI>Redemptions in excess of distributions and net capital appreciation of a Fund will result in a return of capital</UL><B>Interfund proceeds Exchange Plan</B><BR><UL><LI>You can redeem units of one Fund and direct to purchase another<LI>Sales charge is applied to purchase portion of transaction<LI>Charge is negotiable<LI>Monthly or quarterly</UL><P><HR><P><B><A NAME="open">Open</A> Account (Cash Account)</B><BR><UL><LI>Non-registered<LI>Can be joint with spouse or family member<LI>Accounts can be held in trust for a child<LI>No setup or termination fees</UL><B><A NAME="rrsp">Registered</A> Retirement Savings Plan (RRSP)</B><UL><LI>Minimum investment $500</UL><B><A NAME="rrif">Registered</A> Retirement Income Fund (RRIF)</B><BR><UL><LI>For rollover of RRSP at retirement </UL><B><A NAME="lira">Locked-in</A> Retirement Account (LIRA)</B><BR><UL><LI>Available in Alberta, British Columbia, Manitoba, Saskatchewan, New Brunswick and Quebec</UL><B><A NAME="lif">Life</A> Income Fund (LIF)</B><BR><UL><LI>For rollover of LIRA<LI>Available in Ontario, Alberta, British Columbia, Manitoba, and Saskatchewan</UL><HR><center><A HREF="home2.html"><IMG WIDTH=115 HEIGHT=49 BORDER=0 ALT="C.I. Home Page" SRC="menu/about_ci.gif"></A><A HREF="ditip.html"><IMG WIDTH=115 HEIGHT=49 BORDER=0 ALT="Daily Investment Tip" SRC="menu/daily_tip.gif"></A><A HREF="feedback.html"><IMG WIDTH=115 HEIGHT=49 BORDER=0 ALT="Feedback to C.I." SRC="menu/feedback.gif"></A><A HREF="prices.html"><IMG WIDTH=115 HEIGHT=49 BORDER=0 ALT="C.I. Fund Prices" SRC="menu/daily_prices.gif"></A></center><PRE></PRE><A HREF="disclaimer.html">Disclaimer</A><p>All material on this site is copyright &copy; C.I. Mutual Funds Inc., 1995, 1996<P>Questions?  send mail to <A HREF="mailto:webmaster@cifunds.com">webmaster@cifunds.com</A>.</BODY> </HTML> 
