<HTML> <HEAD><TITLE>C.I. Mutual Funds: International - BEA Associates</TITLE></HEAD> <BODY BGCOLOR="#EBE8DF"><CENTER><TABLE CELLSPACING=2 CELLPADDING=0 BORDER=2><TR><TD><A HREF="home2.html"><IMG BORDER=0 ALT="C.I. Mutual Funds" SRC="pagebanner_white.gif"></A></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER><P><PRE></PRE><H1 ALIGN=CENTER>BEA Associates</H1><FONT SIZE=4><B>&nbsp;Bill Sterling</B><BR><IMG WIDTH=108 HEIGHT=112 align=left HSPACE=5 BORDER=0 ALT="William Sterling Photo" SRC="images/sterling.gif">Bill Sterling leads the global strategy team.  A highly respected international economist, he tracks movements of capital around the world, zeroing in on the extreme situations which are often indicators of impending changes in trends.  His research is invaluable in determining asset allocation strategies for the international bond and equity teams.<BR clear=all><P><B>&nbsp;Bill Priest</B><BR><IMG WIDTH=108 HEIGHT=94 align=left HSPACE=5 BORDER=0 ALT="William Priest Photo" SRC="images/priest.gif">Bill Priest, CEO of the firm, is also BEA's American equities specialist.  He applies a global criterion to U.S. stock selection, focusing on those companies which are restructuring - often returning to core businesses - and expanding into new international markets..<BR clear=all><P><B>&nbsp;Emilio Bassini</B><BR><IMG WIDTH=108 HEIGHT=102 align=left vspace=5 HSPACE=5 BORDER=0 ALT="Emilio Bassini Photo" SRC="images/bassini.gif">As leader of the international equities team and BEA's emerging markets strategist,  Emilio Bassini focuses on undervalued situations which demonstrate strong growth potential despite market misperception. To the portfolios under his direction, he brings years of experience in the structuring and management of businesses in developing countries and an enthusiasm for the potential of the world's emerging markets.<BR clear=all><P><B>&nbsp;Gregg Diliberto</B><BR><IMG WIDTH=108 HEIGHT=138 align=left HSPACE=5 BORDER=0 ALT="Gregg Diliberto Photo" SRC="images/diliberto.gif">A mathematician by training, Gregg Diliberto directs the team which determines portfolio selection for C.I.'s international fixed income funds.  He favours broad diversification to include quality corporate and municipal bonds as well as government issues from around the world, constantly monitoring their movements and currency changes with a proprietary information technology system designed to his specifications.<BR clear=all><P><B>&nbsp;Stephen Swift</B><BR><IMG align=left HSPACE=5 BORDER=0 ALT="Stephen Swift Photo" SRC="images/swift.gif">With over 20 years of hands-on experience in the Far East, Stephen Swift is intimately acquainted with the markets and economies of the Pacific Rim nations.  His credentials include responsibility for the giant CS Tiger Fund, one of the largest mutual funds specializing in Southeast Asian equities, and 15 years managing a regional fund for Wardley Investment Services, a former subsidiary of the Hong Kong and Shanghai Bank.<BR clear=all><P><B>&nbsp;Richard Watt</B><BR><IMG align=left HSPACE=5 BORDER=0 ALT="Richard Watt Photo" SRC="images/watt.gif">Richard Watt is a Latin American specialist with particular experience in the region's smaller companies.  Prior to joining BEA, he was manager of the Latin American New Growth Fund N.A. for Gartmore Investment Limited in London, England and also headed their research and emerging markets investment team.<BR clear=all><P></FONT><BR clear=all><PRE></PRE><HR NOSHADE><FONT SIZE=5>Market Commentaries and Fund Statistics</FONT><P><center><table border=0><TR valign=top><TD><B><A HREF="bea_global.html">C.I. Global Fund</A></B><BR><B><A HREF="bea_global.html">C.I. Global Equity RSP Fund</A> &nbsp;&nbsp;</B><P><A HREF="bea_bond.html"><B>C.I. World Bond Fund</A></B><BR><A HREF="bea_bond.html"><B>C.I. Global Bond RSP Fund</A></B><P><A HREF="bea_emerging.html"><B>C.I. Emerging Markets Fund</B></A><P><A HREF="bea_latin.html"><B>C.I. Lat