<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>C.I. Mutual Funds Daily $ Tip</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#EBE8DF"><CENTER><A HREF="/text_only.html"><FONT SIZE=3>Text Only Options </FONT></B></CENTER><BR><CENTER><A HREF="/mainimage.map"><IMG SRC="topmenu.gif" WIDTH=658 HEIGHT=161 BORDER=off usemap="#mainmap" ismap></A><map name="mainmap"><area coords="100,14,203,39"href="/about_ci.html"><area coords="101,41,203,66"href="/prices_ci.html"><area coords="100,68,203,92"href="/managers_ci.html"><area coords="100,95,203,120"href="/performance_ci.html"><area coords="316,14,426,39"href="/about_hansberger.html"><area coords="316,41,427,66"href="/prices_hansberger.html"><area coords="316,67,427,93"href="/managers_hansberger.html"><area coords="316,95,427,120"href="/performance_hansberger.html"><area coords="539,14,643,39"href="/about_sector.html"><area coords="539,41,642,65"href="/prices_sector.html"><area coords="539,68,642,93"href="/managers_sector.html"><area coords="539,94,643,120"href="/performance_sector.html"><area coords="4,137,94,160"href="/home.html"><area coords="97,137,187,160"href="/perspective.html"><area coords="192,137,280,161"href="/cinews.html"><area coords="285,137,373,161"href="/feedback.html"><area coords="378,136,468,160"href="/calculator.html"><area coords="471,137,561,163"href="/libruary.html"><area coords="565,137,654,160"href="/links.html"><area coords="22,33,98,114"href="/about_ci.html"><area coords="240,32,316,115"href="/about_hansberger.html"><area coords="468,26,538,115"href="/about_sector.html"></map></CENTER><BR><BR><TD><CENTER><FONT SIZE=7>C.I. Daily $ Tip</FONT><br>By Everett Banning, Host of Moneyworks</CENTER></td></tr></table><hr noshade><p><IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg"><h3>Searching for the free in 'duty-free'.</H3><p>For some of us, winter or summer vacation plans include a trip through the airport.  Since Canadians love a bargain, they naturally flock to duty-free shops.  But all too often, they're disappointed by the prices.  Tobacco and booze are the most popular items sold, followed by European jewellery and fragrances and Asian electronics.  But, on many items all you really save are the sales taxes.  <p><p>The trick to shopping duty free depends on where you are and where you're going.  For example:  A Japanese tourist can get a great deal on European perfume at a Canadian duty free.  Or a European might score savings on a Japanese camera.  But such deals are only good compared to the prices in their home country. <p><p>So when you travel abroad, compare the prices to those in Canada.  Just because it's duty-free doesn't mean it's a bargain.  Shopping smart is part of how MoneyWorks!<p><p><p><A HREF="/old_ditiplist.html"><B>Previous Tips</B></A><HR><PRE></PRE><FONT SIZE=2>This communication is published by C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. Any commentaries contained in this communication are provided as a general source of information and should not be considered personal investment advice.  Every effort has been made to ensure that the material contained in this communication is accurate at the time of publication.  However, C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. cannot guarantee its accuracy or completeness and accepts no responsibility for any loss arising from any use of or reliance on the information contained herein.<P><A HREF="disclaimer.html">Complete disclaimer text</A><p></FONT>All material on this site is copyright &copy; C.I. Mutual Funds, 1995, 1996<P>Questions?  send mail to <A HREF="MAILTO:webmaster@cifunds.com">webmaster@cifunds.com</A>.</BODY> </HTML> 
