t.  The scariest development in recent years was the collapse of the Mexican peso.  The impact ricocheted through the global markets.  A lot of investments took a big hit.  <p><p>But look what's happened.  Well managed funds that are diversified in several global markets have more than recovered.  And even the Mexican market has surprised analysts and recorded some impressive gains in recent months.  Those who sold when the market turned down, lost money.  Many of those who stayed in for rough ride, have seen their investments bounce back.  It happens with even the best blue chip investments in North America.  <p><p>Invest to meet your long term goals, and trust good fund managers to get you through the storm<p><p><p><A HREF="/old_ditiplist.html"><B>Previous Tips</B></A><HR><PRE></PRE><FONT SIZE=2>This communication is published by C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. Any commentaries contained in this communication are provided as a general source of information and should not be considered personal investment advice.  Every effort has been made to ensure that the material contained in this communication is accurate at the time of publication.  However, C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. cannot guarantee its accuracy or completeness and accepts no responsibility for any loss arising from any use of or reliance on the information contained herein.<P><A HREF="disclaimer.html">Complete disclaimer text</A><p></FONT>All material on this site is copyright &copy; C.I. Mutual Funds, 1995, 1996<P>Questions?  send mail to <A HREF="MAILTO:webmaster@cifunds.com">webmaster@cifunds.com</A>.</BODY> </HTML> 
