<hr noshade><p>
<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>Good value from a financial planner</H3>
A lot is said about financial planners and investment advisors helping you manage your future.  But you must get your money's worth.  Professional advisors are paid in two ways.  They might earn a commission from financial products that they buy for your account.  Or, you might pay them an hourly fee.  Or, you might pay a blend of commission and fees.  Planners are paid for the time they spend on your account, and for the time they invest in keeping up with the financial markets, tax laws, accounting rules, and the whole realm of investment products.  A financial planner should save you time, by providing a service you have neither the time nor the knowledge to do yourself.  They can keep you on track, so you don't spend too much and invest too little.  They help build your future, and offer a dispassionate, informed, outside opinion. <p>
<p>
