iates, believes that international markets can give you a good gain from from diversification:<p><p>"If one invests in 8 or 10 or 15 different emerging markets, the down moves are often more than offset by the up moves in other markets"- BILL STERLING.<p><p>Canada has made the top ten list of world stock markets only once in the past ten years, and the U.S. has made the list just four times.  So, history suggests that emerging markets can benefit your portfolio:<p><p>"Over time, one can, by putting a fraction of say 10 or 20 percent of a portfolio in emerging markets, have a reduced risk level." - BILL STERLING. <p><p><p><A HREF="/old_ditiplist.html"><B>Previous Tips</B></A><HR><PRE></PRE><FONT SIZE=2>This communication is published by C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. Any commentaries contained in this communication are provided as a general source of information and should not be considered personal investment advice.  Every effort has been made to ensure that the material contained in this communication is accurate at the time of publication.  However, C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. cannot guarantee its accuracy or completeness and accepts no responsibility for any loss arising from any use of or reliance on the information contained herein.<P><A HREF="disclaimer.html">Complete disclaimer text</A><p></FONT>All material on this site is copyright &copy; C.I. Mutual Funds, 1995, 1996<P>Questions?  send mail to <A HREF="MAILTO:webmaster@cifunds.com">webmaster@cifunds.com</A>.</BODY> </HTML> 
