d software programmes that will allow you to make your own will, or you can consult your lawyer. The cost is low compared to the peace of mind it will bring you. Make sure a copy of your will remains with your lawyer and that your family knows where all your important documents are stored. Review your will at least every five years to account for changes in your life. Consider granting power of attorney to your spouse or a trusted friend in the event you become unable to handle your finances.<p><p>Don't put off drawing up a will. You can't take it with you, and only a will can ensure your assets go where you want them to in this life.<p><p><A HREF="/old_ditiplist.html"><B>Previous Tips</B></A><HR><PRE></PRE><FONT SIZE=2>This communication is published by C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. Any commentaries contained in this communication are provided as a general source of information and should not be considered personal investment advice.  Every effort has been made to ensure that the material contained in this communication is accurate at the time of publication.  However, C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. cannot guarantee its accuracy or completeness and accepts no responsibility for any loss arising from any use of or reliance on the information contained herein.<P><A HREF="disclaimer.html">Complete disclaimer text</A><p></FONT>All material on this site is copyright &copy; C.I. Mutual Funds, 1995, 1996<P>Questions?  send mail to <A HREF="MAILTO:webmaster@cifunds.com">webmaster@cifunds.com</A>.</BODY> </HTML> 
