ver the next few years, and how old you are now.<p><p>If you start saving 4% or 5% of your annual income at age 25, you can enjoy your retirement on about 70% of your average annual pay. If you wait until age 35, you'll have to save between 6% and 8%. If you procrastinate until age 45, you'll have to sock away up to 14% per year to retire comfortably.<p><p>However, these numbers also depend on the return your investments earn. One or two percentage points may not seem like much, but it can mean a fortune as the years pass by. Ask your investment adviser about good, long-term investments that will bring you a slightly higher rate of return. When you retire, you'll be glad you did.<p><A HREF="/old_ditiplist.html"><B>Previous Tips</B></A><HR><PRE></PRE><FONT SIZE=2>This communication is published by C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. Any commentaries contained in this communication are provided as a general source of information and should not be considered personal investment advice.  Every effort has been made to ensure that the material contained in this communication is accurate at the time of publication.  However, C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. cannot guarantee its accuracy or completeness and accepts no responsibility for any loss arising from any use of or reliance on the information contained herein.<P><A HREF="disclaimer.html">Complete disclaimer text</A><p></FONT>All material on this site is copyright &copy; C.I. Mutual Funds, 1995, 1996<P>Questions?  send mail to <A HREF="MAILTO:webmaster@cifunds.com">webmaster@cifunds.com</A>.</BODY> </HTML> 
