<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>The doomsters will always be wrong.</H3>
Now, here's a picture of doom:  There's a war on in the Middle East, and 20 nations have sent their armies to fight a madman.  Crude oil has shot up over forty dollars a barrel.  The economy has been shrinking for months, stuck in a dismal recession.  Big banks across the country are writing off hundreds of millions in bad real estate loans.  The stock market is in the claws of an ugly bear, down 20 percent in the past six months.  Blue chip companies are cutting dividends.  Some of their shares are selling for less than ten dollars each.  Bad stuff.  What to do?  Why not buy into the stock market?  Those who bought stocks during these gloomy days of 1990 could have been there for a record smashing six year bull, that <p>
pushed the Dow Jones average up 150 percent.  When the day is dark, it's probably the cloud overhead.  It'll blow away. <p>
<p>
