<hr noshade><p>
<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>This is not for the wealthy, just for the wise.</H3>
Our comments are mostly aimed at helping the average person take care of their money a little better - because most of us will never be really wealthy.  But most of us can be comfortable and secure, by following a few basic rules of money management.  It all starts with attitude.   Now, we all get that "I feel so broke" feeling from time-to-time - but if you stop a moment,  you'll probably find that you're not doing too badly!   65 percent of adult Canadians own a home, 80 percent own a car, virtually everybody has a colour TV.  So, in spite of any regretable habits, you have substantial assets already.  The secret to doing a little better, is found in several small adjustments in life.  Make plans, set some goals.  Try to spend just 5 percent less, and maybe earn 5 percent more.  Then, put the money into an investment plan regularly.  And as the years go by, you'll discover how MoneyWorks! <p>
<p>
