<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>The big prize from the interest rate sweepstakes</H3>
The world of money has offered up more winnings to people across the country than any tax cuts, wage raises or lottery winnings.  All this new found money is coming from cuts in interest rates.  For every one percent cut in interest rates, consumers get to keep another one billion dollars.   Over the past year, interest rates have dropped by about three percent, so the winnings total about three billion dollar a year.  On a personal level, if you've been carrying a hundred thousand dollar mortgage, the recent cuts are worth about three thousand dollars a year.   On a ten thousand dollar loan, about three hundred dollars a year.  This also means that new houses and other goods are available to more people.  They can borrow more money on the same income.  As these interest rate savings trickle through the economy, the construction and retail sectors will benefit, and that's something to cheer about! <p>
<p>
<p>
