<hr noshade><p>
<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>High-tech is no fad!</H3>
No segment of the markets has been hotter in recent years, than high technology.  It has been crazy.  Companies with millions of dollars in sales have seen their stock market valuations soar to the billions of dollars.  But just because investors go nuts, doesn't mean the investments are bad.  After all, we are in the cyber age.  Even your electric shaver and your coffee maker has computer chips in them.  More fundamentally, the entire way in which we receive our entertainment and information, the ways we work and shop, are all part of the revolution.  Most of it is centered around the Internet, which will soon be part of our TV screen - and about as easy to use as choosing a TV show to watch.  New multi-purpose CD's will replace video and audio tape and  computer disks and lead to a new surge in home electronics.  In spite of the bumps on the high-tech investment highway, the direction we're going is clear, and good technology companies will pay off for all of us. <p>
<p>
<p>
