<hr noshade><p>
<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>Taking a close look at mortgage life insurance</H3>
Mortgage life insurance pays off your mortgage in the event you die.  Such insurance will cost up to $50 a month per 100 thousand dollars of mortgage principal.  But what if you don't die for 15 years, and the principal on the mortgage is down to $25,000. You will have paid $50 per month, but would only generate a relatively small payout to your heirs.  Not to mention the opportunity lost for  making higher return investments. You would likely be better off in buying a 100 thousand dollar term life policy.  That way, your heirs will get 100 thousand dollars, and not just whatever happens to be left on the mortgage balance.    As well, with a term life policy, you will likely get more coverage per dollar.  So, make sure you read the fine print on mortgage life insurance.  Ask lots of questions, and compare the numbers to alternative insurance products. Being mortgage wise can improve how MoneyWorks! <p>
<p>
