<hr noshade><p>
<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg"><h3>Save more money at the bank.</H3>
It may only add up to a few dollars a month, but you can reduce the costs of banking, if you want to.  When they return cheques, they charge for it.  But do you need them, if your statement confirms your record of withdrawals and deposits?  You can make carbons or photocopies before you mail out the cheques, if you really want copies.  Be sure you don't keep too much cash in a chequing account that doesn't earn interest.  Get it into a savings account.  And don't have several accounts with little bits of money everywhere.  Consolidate, because you can often get higher rates for larger deposits.  Use your own bank's automated teller machines, the charges are less than using one at another bank.  Ask for an overdraft on your account, to avoid costly NSF charges.  Be sure to use student or seniors discounts if you qualify.  And those new debit cards can be cheaper and more convenient than cheques. <p>
<p>
