<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>C.I. Mutual Funds Daily $ Tip</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#EBE8DF"><CENTER><A HREF="/text_only.html"><FONT SIZE=3>Text Only Options </FONT></B></CENTER><BR><CENTER><A HREF="/mainimage.map"><IMG SRC="topmenu.gif" WIDTH=658 HEIGHT=161 BORDER=off usemap="#mainmap" ismap></A><map name="mainmap"><area coords="100,14,203,39"href="/about_ci.html"><area coords="101,41,203,66"href="/prices_ci.html"><area coords="100,68,203,92"href="/managers_ci.html"><area coords="100,95,203,120"href="/performance_ci.html"><area coords="316,14,426,39"href="/about_hansberger.html"><area coords="316,41,427,66"href="/prices_hansberger.html"><area coords="316,67,427,93"href="/managers_hansberger.html"><area coords="316,95,427,120"href="/performance_hansberger.html"><area coords="539,14,643,39"href="/about_sector.html"><area coords="539,41,642,65"href="/prices_sector.html"><area coords="539,68,642,93"href="/managers_sector.html"><area coords="539,94,643,120"href="/performance_sector.html"><area coords="4,137,94,160"href="/home.html"><area coords="97,137,187,160"href="/perspective.html"><area coords="192,137,280,161"href="/cinews.html"><area coords="285,137,373,161"href="/feedback.html"><area coords="378,136,468,160"href="/calculator.html"><area coords="471,137,561,163"href="/libruary.html"><area coords="565,137,654,160"href="/links.html"><area coords="22,33,98,114"href="/about_ci.html"><area coords="240,32,316,115"href="/about_hansberger.html"><area coords="468,26,538,115"href="/about_sector.html"></map></CENTER><BR><BR><TD><CENTER><FONT SIZE=7>C.I. Daily $ Tip</FONT><br>By Everett Banning, Host of Moneyworks</CENTER></td></tr></table><hr noshade><p><IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg"><h3>Have enough money for retirement?</H3>How much money do you need for retirement?  Most financial planners figure that people need about three-quarters of their current income to live comfortably through their retirement.  It can be less if you trade down to cheaper home, or if you get rid of a car, or drive a smaller car.  But there are some things you can do to accelerate your savings rate, so you'll have more income in later years.  <p>One, instead of rushing to pay off your house mortgage fast, keep making smaller payments and invest the extra cash.  There are many investment funds with solid, double-digit track records, that can grow your nest egg much faster than any mortgage paydown will save you.<p>Two, take full advantage of spousal RSPs, so your retirement income, and taxes, will be split, and likely be lower.<p>And third, when you invest, diversify, using different kinds of investments to maximize growth and reduce risk.<p><p><p><A HREF="/old_ditiplist.html"><B>Previous Tips</B></A><HR><PRE></PRE><FONT SIZE=2>This communication is published by C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. Any commentaries contained in this communication are provided as a general source of information and should not be considered personal investment advice.  Every effort has been made to ensure that the material contained in this communication is accurate at the time of publication.  However, C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. cannot guarantee its accuracy or completeness and accepts no responsibility for any loss arising from any use of or reliance on the information contained herein.<P><A HREF="disclaimer.html">Complete disclaimer text</A><p></FONT>All material on this site is copyright &copy; C.I. Mutual Funds, 1995, 1996<P>Questions?  send mail to <A HREF="MAILTO:webmaster@cifunds.com">webmaster@cifunds.com</A>.</BODY> </HTML> 
