<hr noshade><p>
<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>Initial public offerings!</H3>
The intial public offering - or IPO - is the term used when a company first goes to the stock market.  And this has been a rip-roaring year for IPOs.  While they are - on average - riskier than established stocks, new listings are worth investigating.    A lot of mutual fund managers include carefully selected IPOs because of their growth potential.  You have to do your homework.  How long has the company has been in business? What kind of results have they delivered?  Do the people running the company have their own money at risk?  What is their track record?  Do their products or services have a unique competitive position?  And does the industry have a solid future?  If you can pick one or two rising stars for a small part of your portfolio, they can add a little more zing to your performance. <p>
<p>
<p>
