<hr noshade><p>
<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>Inside tips on how to make money.</H3>
We'd all like to get in on the next hot investment trend, to make some quick and easy money.  But for every person who has won this lottery, there are many losers.  An inside tip on the stock market is almost always worthless, if only because nobody can predict the future.  The insider tips that are really worth something come from long time, successful investors like Warren Buffett, Peter Lynch and John Templeton.  As successful investors, they put a lot of work into researching companies.  It's like shopping wisely.   They make sure they know these companies first.  They buy well-run businesses with a promising future, but only when the price is good.  That's because buying stocks should be a process of investing.  You shouldn't be gambling.  If you have chosen your investments well, they're worth hanging onto through good and bad times. <p>
<p>
<p>
