<hr noshade><p>
<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>How to live through an autopsy.</H3>
Every year tens of thousands of Canadians are audited by Revenue Canada. Receiving an audit notice may at first feel like an invitation to your own autopsy. But don't panic.  Most audits simply stem from random selection. Instead, focus your attention on preparing for the audit. You can represent yourself, or hire someone to represent you, which may not be a bad investment. Regardless of your approach, be prepared. Give your self time to sort and organize all of your receipts and other documentation. Make it easy for the Revenue Canada auditor to review your materials.  Make sure you don't ignore an assessment notice. Revenue Canada can get tough.  And do what you can to speed the audit. If you owe more in taxes, the sooner you pay it, the lower the penalties .  Audits are not pleasant, but they help maintain integrity in the tax system and are a part of how MoneyWorks! <p>
<p>
