<hr noshade><p>
<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>Learning to listen to your financial planner.</H3>
All too often, investors will simply ignore the recommendations of the  professionals they hire to  advise them on money and keep them on track with their financial goals.  Say you hear of some penny-stock promotion. The story sounds good  so, you decide to take the risk. But then you take it to your broker. They tell you the investment is too risky. If your broker is top notch, they may simply refuse to make the trade for you. But, before you get too angry, think about this:   The broker will be following of the "know-your-client" rule. They should be acting to prevent you from making mistakes.  So when your broker explains to you why a particular investment is bad, you should take a serious listen. After all, that what you're paying them for?!!  Avoiding the bad investments will boost the impact of your good ones. <p>
<p>
<p>
