<hr noshade><p>
<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>It's best to own than to loan!</H3>
So many financial observers have said that those who own rather than loan, make more money.  Those who put their money in productive assets, in good, growing businesses, gain more in the long run, than those who lend their money to businesses or governments by investing in bonds.  A recent study by a group of professors at York University found that people who try to build their future by putting everything in  Treasury Bills, risk outliving their money.  But those who include a good portion of carefully chosen equity investments will get better returns and can live more securely.  The York study reports that bonds returned 2.8 percent a year from 1950 to 1993, and that the Toronto Stock Exchange returned an average 7.7 percent.  Since many of us will live well into our 80s and 90s, this is valuable information. <p>
<p>
<p>
