<hr noshade><p>
<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>Know the fund you want before you place an order.</H3>
There was a survey done recently by the firm Marketing Solutions of Toronto.  They surveyed people who have invested in mutual funds.  It found that about forty percent of them don't know the exact name of the fund they own.  This is an important piece of information, because the name of the fund can reflect the strategies and goals of the fund manager.  A seemingly small slip-up in the name of the fund might get you a global investment which does not qualify for your RSP.  It might get you a small companies fund investment which may be more volatile than you are willing to tolerate.  It could get you into a long term bond fund when you wanted short term bonds that fluctuate less.  Even with the very best professional advice, it is worth doing some research on the kinds of funds and the strategies used by fund managers, so when you place your buy order, you get exactly what you intended. <p>
<p>
<p>
