<hr noshade><p>
<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>The ups and downs of making money.</H3>
You can use the ups and downs of the market to make even more money.  You may have heard financial experts say they like it when the market turns down, because those are the bargain days.  Stocks are on sale.  They're cheap.  The difficult part is knowing when to be buying and when to be selling.  Most people get that part wrong.  Market timing is difficult even for seasoned professionals.  The secret is to be in the market all the time.  You can do this by making regular monthly investment contributions, so you get dollar cost averaging on your side.  If you invest the same amount, lets say, 500 dollars a month, every month, you're buying throughout the market cycle.  You buy more shares when prices are down.  When the stock market cycle goes  back up, your average share price is lower.  And the value of your total investment is higher than if you'd tried to time the market and got it wrong. <p>
<p>
<p>
<A HREF="/old_ditiplist.html"><B>Previous Tips</B></A>
