<hr noshade><p>
<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>Don't let big numbers dazzle you.</H3>
The growth in the popularity of investment funds has been meteoric.  But choosing the right funds requires some thought.  The financial section of the paper is full of numbers and charts showing who is first and who is last.  Funds that suddenly turn in big numbers get a lot of attention.  But that doesn't mean they are a good place to put your money.  A recent survey which identified eight funds in the U.S. market, that reported over 40 percent growth in the past year, found that number to be highly misleading.  Because those eight eyepopping funds had been so mediocre the previous four years, that none even matched the average performance of the stock market index.  Long term, steady performance from a fund manager is usually the smart way to go, even when some dazzling numbers try to pull you in another direction. <p>
<p>
<p>
