 If you are in the top tax bracket, investments outside your RRSP may be subject to tax and commissions.<p><p>That stock which goes from thirty to forty dollars looks like a winner, but nearly half of your ten dollar profit goes to taxes with another dollar or so to brokerage fees. The biggest trap of any short-term strategy is trying to predict both the stock's peak and bottom - few experts try to be that precise. The best strategy is to invest for the long term with solid investments that continue to gain in value over time. In the short term, those instant winners may turn into losers.<p><p>Ask your investment adviser about winning mutual funds with good long-term records.<p><p><A HREF="/old_ditiplist.html"><B>Previous Tips</B></A><HR><PRE></PRE><FONT SIZE=2>This communication is published by C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. Any commentaries contained in this communication are provided as a general source of information and should not be considered personal investment advice.  Every effort has been made to ensure that the material contained in this communication is accurate at the time of publication.  However, C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. cannot guarantee its accuracy or completeness and accepts no responsibility for any loss arising from any use of or reliance on the information contained herein.<P><A HREF="disclaimer.html">Complete disclaimer text</A><p></FONT>All material on this site is copyright &copy; C.I. Mutual Funds, 1995, 1996<P>Questions?  send mail to <A HREF="MAILTO:webmaster@cifunds.com">webmaster@cifunds.com</A>.</BODY> </HTML> 
