p><p>A recent survey shows that about half of all Canadians plan to put money into an RRSP this year, with the average contribution being about $4,000.  Most Canadians hold about a year's worth of total income in their RRSPs -- an average of $30,000.  Only one person in twelve has over $100,000 in RRSP investments.  The survey also showed that most people intend to invest in mutual funds, stocks and bonds for their RRSP in 1995-96.  That's a change from other years, when people favoured investments like GICs.  <p><p>With interest rates low, smart investors are seeking the potential of higher returns, and that potential adds up over the long term. $4000 invested every year for 20 years at an annual return of 6% will equal $147,160. The same $4,000 invested every year for 20 years at a 10% annual return will total $229,080. Over the long term, small increases in annual returns make big differences in the value of your investment.<p><p><A HREF="/old_ditiplist.html"><B>Previous Tips</B></A><HR><PRE></PRE><FONT SIZE=2>This communication is published by C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. Any commentaries contained in this communication are provided as a general source of information and should not be considered personal investment advice.  Every effort has been made to ensure that the material contained in this communication is accurate at the time of publication.  However, C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. cannot guarantee its accuracy or completeness and accepts no responsibility for any loss arising from any use of or reliance on the information contained herein.<P><A HREF="disclaimer.html">Complete disclaimer text</A><p></FONT>All material on this site is copyright &copy; C.I. Mutual Funds, 1995, 1996<P>Questions?  send mail to <A HREF="MAILTO:webmaster@cifunds.com">webmaster@cifunds.com</A>.</BODY> </HTML> 
