<hr noshade><p>
<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>How to make money riding the waves of the economy</H3>
How to make money on the ups and downs of the economy?  Many professional money managers adjust investments to correspond with the businesses most likely to benefit - or suffer - as the economy moves from one part of the cycle to another.<p>
Experts say our economy tends to move in fairly predictable ways. <p>
The sectors of our economy seldom move together.  They follow one another.  Banks might do well, because interest rates are down, and people are borrowing more.  They borrow to buy cars, so car companies and parts suppliers do well.  That means steel, nickel, and copper companies do well.<p>
And then mining companies.<p>
People also borrow to buy new houses, so developers do well.<p>
They order more building materials, so forest companies win.This results in jobs and higher wages, so people spend it in stores.  So consumer companies get stronger.  Investing this way is called the sector rotation approach to benefit from the cycles of the economy. <p>
<p>
<p>
<A HREF="/old_ditiplist.html"><B>Previous Tips</B></A>
<HR>

