<hr noshade><p>
<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>The monsters that stomp around the markets.</H3>
The amazing Steven Speilberg's giant dinosaurs in Jurassic Park, have been exceeded by the fantasies of some investors, who have created some monsters of their own.  We cite the example of a Connecticut company called Iomega.  They evolved from being makers of an arcane product called a Bernoulli Box, into the celebrated manufacturers of a wonderful little computer storage system called the Zip Drive.  Personally, I think it is a great product.  It lets you store 50 discs worth of computer data on one simple Zip disc.  The Zip sells for about 200 dollars.  But even if every computer user in the world bought one, the company would not likely be worth the recent bidding price of Iomega's stock.  Investors put a 7 billion dollar market value on this company, that makes little Zip drives.  The happy lesson here, is that such madness never lasts. <p>
<p>
<p>
