ntries as part of their portfolios.  Many of the Latin American and Pacific Rim nations have chosen pro-growth strategies.  Even after some bad bumps like the Mexican peso crisis, it is encouraging that these countries are sticking with their plans for growth.  So, specific types of companies stand to benefit.  When a nation is building new infrastructure-roads, sewers, telephones, public buildings-then businesses that provide telecommunications, cement, banking services and transportation represent promising investment opportunities.  When a nation chooses to modernise its economy and liberalise its financial markets, then it becomes attractive to foreign investors.  More than ever, our economic future is linked to the fortunes of the Global Village, and emerging market mutual funds are one way to participate</H3><p><p><A HREF="/old_ditiplist.html"><B>Previous Tips</B></A><HR><PRE></PRE><FONT SIZE=2>This communication is published by C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. Any commentaries contained in this communication are provided as a general source of information and should not be considered personal investment advice.  Every effort has been made to ensure that the material contained in this communication is accurate at the time of publication.  However, C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. cannot guarantee its accuracy or completeness and accepts no responsibility for any loss arising from any use of or reliance on the information contained herein.<P><A HREF="disclaimer.html">Complete disclaimer text</A><p></FONT>All material on this site is copyright &copy; C.I. Mutual Funds, 1995, 1996<P>Questions?  send mail to <A HREF="MAILTO:webmaster@cifunds.com">webmaster@cifunds.com</A>.</BODY> </HTML> 
