<hr noshade><p>
<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>Why you should shun extended warranties.</H3>
Canadians, believe it or not, are the most insured people on the planet. In fact, we just can't seem to get enough of it. Yet not all of the insurance we buy is useful. In particular, you rarely receive a good deal when buying a so-called extended warranty. Say you've just picked up a new VCR, computer, TV or dishwasher. Invariably, the store clerk who just convinced you that you had to have the product, turns around and tries to get you to fork out another five to 10 per cent of the purchase price to buy an extended warranty.  Don't just do it!  First, you should always demand a reasonable warranty with a new appliance. And second, most studies show that extended warranties are rarely of good value. It's not the manufacturer who pays. It's you, through the premium. So watch out for those extended warranties!  It may be your best guarantee of financial prudence, because that's how MoneyWorks! <p>
<p>
