ance, returning rented videos too late only costs a couple of dollars each time, but it could add up to $100 in a year. Bottled water from the supermarket is expensive, a filter system could save a lot of money.  Talk about where you drive, and consider the 10-block rule -- if you are going fewer than ten blocks, walk or ride a bicycle. It will improve your health, your environment, and your pocketbook.  A discount plan for long distance phone calls, cutting back on the daily newspapers, and doing your own yard work can mean more dollars in your pocket.  <p><p>Carry a spiral notepad and write down all the cash you spend for a month. It might surprise you how much money dribbles away. It's not what you earn. It's what you keep that counts, and the more you keep the more you can invest for tomorrow.<p><p><A HREF="/old_ditiplist.html"><B>Previous Tips</B></A><HR><PRE></PRE><FONT SIZE=2>This communication is published by C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. Any commentaries contained in this communication are provided as a general source of information and should not be considered personal investment advice.  Every effort has been made to ensure that the material contained in this communication is accurate at the time of publication.  However, C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. cannot guarantee its accuracy or completeness and accepts no responsibility for any loss arising from any use of or reliance on the information contained herein.<P><A HREF="disclaimer.html">Complete disclaimer text</A><p></FONT>All material on this site is copyright &copy; C.I. Mutual Funds, 1995, 1996<P>Questions?  send mail to <A HREF="MAILTO:webmaster@cifunds.com">webmaster@cifunds.com</A>.</BODY> </HTML> 
