ample, buying a house has been a goal for most people.  Many experts think that house prices will never again go through the kind of boom we experienced in the 1970s and 80s.  Owing your home has advantages, but it may be risky to consider it the major investment in life.  So, consider renting to cut your living costs.  Now, what about a car?  It can eat up 15 or 20 percent of an average income.  Think if you can do without a car, or with just one car in your family.  Invest your savings.  Or consider using your money to start a business - instead of holding a job.  <P></P>The era of big government and big business is over and lost jobs are unlikely to come back.  It seems our economy is returning to an era of self-reliance and entrepreneurialism, so your own business may give you a better future. <p><p><p><A HREF="/old_ditiplist.html"><B>Previous Tips</B></A><HR><PRE></PRE><FONT SIZE=2>This communication is published by C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. Any commentaries contained in this communication are provided as a general source of information and should not be considered personal investment advice.  Every effort has been made to ensure that the material contained in this communication is accurate at the time of publication.  However, C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. cannot guarantee its accuracy or completeness and accepts no responsibility for any loss arising from any use of or reliance on the information contained herein.<P><A HREF="disclaimer.html">Complete disclaimer text</A><p></FONT>All material on this site is copyright &copy; C.I. Mutual Funds, 1995, 1996<P>Questions?  send mail to <A HREF="MAILTO:webmaster@cifunds.com">webmaster@cifunds.com</A>.</BODY> </HTML> 
