<hr noshade><p>
<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>How to catch up with your cash.</H3>
Most of us get down to some serious money making much later than we'd like.  But we can make up for lost time.  To get some cash into an investment account, and get the money working for you, there are a number of things to consider.  Maybe the time has come to trade down your house.  You can reduce your daily living expenses and free up some equity to put in stocks or investment funds.  A number of experts believe equity investments will outperform real estate in the years ahead.  Include equities as one part of your mix of investments.  While they are more volatile than other investments, over ten, fifteen or twenty years, equities generally deliver higher returns.  Consider ways to increase your income.  Perhaps a small business is something you might be good at.  Look at ways to increase your savings.  And be sure you claim all your deductions when you file your tax return. <p>
<p>
