 credit card debt. Your investments will rarely match what you'll have to pay out on high interest rate charges.  What do you gain when you earn 10 per cent on your savings, and your debt is costing you more than 20 per cent? <p><p>Two, never put everything you have in just one place.  You might feel safe and secure with all your money in a savings account, but you may get more growth by putting even a small part of your money into a mutual fund. Three, don't buy an investment unless you understand what it is, how it works, and what the risks are.<p> <p>Four, don't deal with cold callers who try to promote investments to you.  Check them out carefully because there are some shady operators out there.  Five, don't ignore taxes.  Make an allowance for taxes when they are due, so you won't get any surprises down the road.  <p><p>Six, don't try to follow the rush because you'll likely be too late.  Consult a financial adviser about a good investment plan and stick to it with annual updates, regardless of what the headlines say.<p><p><A HREF="/old_ditiplist.html"><B>Previous Tips</B></A><HR><PRE></PRE><FONT SIZE=2>This communication is published by C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. Any commentaries contained in this communication are provided as a general source of information and should not be considered personal investment advice.  Every effort has been made to ensure that the material contained in this communication is accurate at the time of publication.  However, C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. cannot guarantee its accuracy or completeness and accepts no responsibility for any loss arising from any use of or reliance on the information contained herein.<P><A HREF="disclaimer.html">Complete disclaimer text</A><p></FONT>All material on this site is copyright &copy; C.I. Mutual Funds, 1995, 1996<P>Questions?  send mail to <A HREF="MAILTO:webmaster@cifunds.com">webmaster@cifunds.com</A>.</BODY> </HTML> 
