ut to buy a car, remember these tips. Determine in advance how much you want to spend.  Focus on the various models which interest you and fall within your price range.  Ignore specific list prices because virtually all car dealerships will negotiate on price. <P>Once you have found the car you like, don't hesitate to go from dealer to dealer because they will undercut each other on the same car models.  A new-car sale for them is like a loss-leader because it generates future business for their service department.  Don't hesitate to ask the dealer what their breakeven price is, and be willing to walk unless you have won the concessions you want. <P>That's why they call them "dealers" and good bargaining brings good deals.<P><A HREF="/old_ditiplist.html"><B>Previous Tips</B></A><HR><PRE></PRE><FONT SIZE=2>This communication is published by C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. Any commentaries contained in this communication are provided as a general source of information and should not be considered personal investment advice.  Every effort has been made to ensure that the material contained in this communication is accurate at the time of publication.  However, C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. cannot guarantee its accuracy or completeness and accepts no responsibility for any loss arising from any use of or reliance on the information contained herein.<P><A HREF="disclaimer.html">Complete disclaimer text</A><p></FONT>All material on this site is copyright &copy; C.I. Mutual Funds, 1995, 1996<P>Questions?  send mail to <A HREF="MAILTO:webmaster@cifunds.com">webmaster@cifunds.com</A>.</BODY> </HTML> 
