<hr noshade><p>
<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>Why investment funds are so popular</H3>
The growth in the amount of money that people have in investment funds is staggering.  The assets of Canadian equity funds is up over 40 percent in the past year, while the assets in foreign equity funds is up over 30 percent.  In total, we've got about 175 billion dollars invested in Canada.  This all makes sense, though.  Those who want their assets to grow over the long term haven't been getting much return from interest earning investments.  And that is unlikely to change.  So, we look to equities.  Also, the boomers have their home and a lot of their child rearing expenses behind them, and want to save for retirement.  Boomers are voting for equities.  But boomers are also short of time, so they want others to take some of the work load.  They opt for the professional management available when they buy investment funds, rather than having to follow the vagaries of the stock market themselves.  So, the big numbers we're seeing are neither peculiar nor worrisome. <p>
<p>
<p>
