<hr noshade><p>
<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>Why I like the drugs!</H3>
I like the drugs.  The drug companies are involved in many exciting ideas, that might deliver good earnings and are worth considering for a small corner of an investment portfolio.  These are the prime movers in the field of biotechnology.  At the core of a lot of excitement, is bio-engineering:  Working with life's building blocks to find solutions for many illnesses.  For example, vaccines can be growm in artificial cell banks, instead of using animal tissue - which is purer, cheaper, and profitable.  Scientists are now mapping the entire human genetic code, to lead them to better of ways of diagnosing, treating, or avoiding illnesses.  Instead of giving people an injection, we know of a vaccine for flu that can be inhaled.  As the aging baby boom creates more demand for health care, the development of new products makes drug companies even more compelling. <p>
<p>
