r might expose you to more risk than you realise.  <p><p>The biggest item on the insurance list is liability insurance.  It can cost eight or nine dollars a day, which adds up to a lot during a one or two week holiday or business trip.  But it can cost you everything you own, and more, if you're in an accident and get sued--particularly in some foreign jurisdictions.  If I'm unsure, I pay for liability insurance.  <p><p>Generally, credit card insurance packages do not cover liability, because of the cost.  They cover car damage and health costs.  It's best to check with the company that insures your own car to see if your liability coverage extends to cars that you rent, particularly out of the country.   <p><p>Also, know who's first in line.  The car rental agency may expect you to pay for an accident, making it your responsibility to collect from your credit card or insurance company.  You may not be able to change that, but its good to know how it works.<p><p><A HREF="/old_ditiplist.html"><B>Previous Tips</B></A><HR><PRE></PRE><FONT SIZE=2>This communication is published by C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. Any commentaries contained in this communication are provided as a general source of information and should not be considered personal investment advice.  Every effort has been made to ensure that the material contained in this communication is accurate at the time of publication.  However, C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. cannot guarantee its accuracy or completeness and accepts no responsibility for any loss arising from any use of or reliance on the information contained herein.<P><A HREF="disclaimer.html">Complete disclaimer text</A><p></FONT>All material on this site is copyright &copy; C.I. Mutual Funds, 1995, 1996<P>Questions?  send mail to <A HREF="MAILTO:webmaster@cifunds.com">webmaster@cifunds.com</A>.</BODY> </HTML> 
