<hr noshade><p>
<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>Four smart ways to use your mortgage</H3>
For most of us, a mortgage is the largest financial undertaking of our lives. So here are four quick tips to help you win on the mortgage front. <p>
One, remember that a mortgage is the cheapest loan you can get. So when it comes time to renew, add to your mortgage to pay for planned expenditures such as renovations.  <p>
Two, maintain your mortgage payments even if you renew at a lower rate.  You'll be accustomed to the higher payment, and, by maintaining it, you'll pay down the principal faster.  <p>
Three, consider going to bimonthly payments to help speed up the pay off.  <p>
And four, consider shortening the amortization of your mortgage. A 20 year term will bump up your payment.  But over the life of your mortgage, you'll save a fortune on interest, and you will be mortgage free five years sooner than with a conventional 25 year term. So use  your mortgage to your advantage. <p>
<p>
