<hr noshade><p>
<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>What causes you to spend too much?</H3>
Where does all the money go?  It seems that everytime you get some out of the bank, it just flies away.  They should print money on sticky paper.  When you have cash or a credit card available, right there, in your pocket, it's just too easy to spend - especially when you're standing in a store or shopping mall, too easily influenced by impulse.  Why not consider shopping trips without much money on you?  See what you'd like.  Go home and think about it, and whether it makes sense.  The proliferation of easy credit by credit card, persuasive advertising campaigns, and attractive bargain promotions are all good aspects of the consumer economy.   But you're in charge.  By giving even some purchases a sober second thought, you gain control of the cash flow, you run up less debt, you keep more money in the bank, and you're on your way to discovering the extra money you'll need to build your future. <p>
<p>
<p>
