<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>C.I. Mutual Funds Daily $ Tip</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#EBE8DF"><CENTER><A HREF="/text_only.html"><FONT SIZE=3>Text Only Options </FONT></B></CENTER><BR><CENTER><A HREF="/mainimage.map"><IMG SRC="topmenu.gif" WIDTH=658 HEIGHT=161 BORDER=off usemap="#mainmap" ismap></A><map name="mainmap"><area coords="100,14,203,39"href="/about_ci.html"><area coords="101,41,203,66"href="/prices_ci.html"><area coords="100,68,203,92"href="/managers_ci.html"><area coords="100,95,203,120"href="/performance_ci.html"><area coords="316,14,426,39"href="/about_hansberger.html"><area coords="316,41,427,66"href="/prices_hansberger.html"><area coords="316,67,427,93"href="/managers_hansberger.html"><area coords="316,95,427,120"href="/performance_hansberger.html"><area coords="539,14,643,39"href="/about_sector.html"><area coords="539,41,642,65"href="/prices_sector.html"><area coords="539,68,642,93"href="/managers_sector.html"><area coords="539,94,643,120"href="/performance_sector.html"><area coords="4,137,94,160"href="/home.html"><area coords="97,137,187,160"href="/perspective.html"><area coords="192,137,280,161"href="/cinews.html"><area coords="285,137,373,161"href="/feedback.html"><area coords="378,136,468,160"href="/calculator.html"><area coords="471,137,561,163"href="/libruary.html"><area coords="565,137,654,160"href="/links.html"><area coords="22,33,98,114"href="/about_ci.html"><area coords="240,32,316,115"href="/about_hansberger.html"><area coords="468,26,538,115"href="/about_sector.html"></map></CENTER><BR><BR><TD><CENTER><FONT SIZE=7>C.I. Daily $ Tip</FONT><br>By Everett Banning, Host of Moneyworks</CENTER></td></tr></table><hr noshade><p><IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg"><h3>How to get over a fight about money.</H3>Lots of people fight about money.  It's one of the big reasons that marriages break down.  Some experts say that couples would rather talk about sex than money.  Well, let's talk about money today.  Often, you'll find that a penny pincher has married a wild spender.  That an indecisive worrier has married a reckless buyer.  That someone who's secretive and private about money is with a flashy show-off.  These polar opposites can get together on money, with a positive heart-to-heart discussion.  Each of you should work to understand the positive aspects of the other's financial behaviour.  Talk about what's good about the other person - and how you can compromise to adopt behaviour that works for your mutual benefit.  Play down the negatives, but don't avoid them either.  Draw up separate lists of your goals in life, compare them, and use them to develop joint goals that can you work towards together.  This kind of discussion and planning can work, if you're committed to your relationship, another aspect of how MoneyWorks! <p><p><p><A HREF="/old_ditiplist.html"><B>Previous Tips</B></A><HR><PRE></PRE><FONT SIZE=2>This communication is published by C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. Any commentaries contained in this communication are provided as a general source of information and should not be considered personal investment advice.  Every effort has been made to ensure that the material contained in this communication is accurate at the time of publication.  However, C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. cannot guarantee its accuracy or completeness and accepts no responsibility for any loss arising from any use of or reliance on the information contained herein.<P><A HREF="disclaimer.html">Complete disclaimer text</A><p></FONT>All material on this site is copyright &copy; C.I. Mutual Funds, 1995, 1996<P>Questions?  send mail to <A HREF="MAILTO:webmaster@cifunds.com">webmaster@cifunds.com</A>.</BODY> </HTML> 
