<hr noshade><p>
<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>Not crazy about three percent!</H3>
You've now been told that savings bonds will pay you just three, four or five percent.  This is not getting your money to work for you - although it provides a secure holding pattern.  You need something that will compound your cash faster to fill the treasure chest.  Is there a magic answer?  Nope.  Yet, some thoughtful changes might move the growth rate up a few notches.  Keep a portion of your money in safe 5 or 6 percent investments.  Then, use some of your money for investments which might fluctuate up and down, but provide long term average growth of 12 percent or more.  You'll likely find that your average return has pushed up to the 10 percent range that you need to build a future.  In today's investment environment, consider some risk and volatility, if you want better performance for you money.<p>
<p>
<p>
