<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>Which way the stock market?</H3>
We have witnessed one of the great bull markets in stocks. It's gone up ceaselessly for more than five years.  And as the months have passed, and the Dow and TSE averages surged, the fear of heights is plainly evident.  As sure as the markets go up, they also go down, part of the normal cycle of things.  Good investment managers are prepared for this.  They invest in companies that are good, no matter what the stock market does.  A well run company retains much of its value and earnings power, through thick and thin.  While the daily news reports on the Dow or TSE , or on what the dollar or inflation, are doing - investment managers regard this information with passing interest.  They want to know about the talent of company personnel, the competitiveness of their products, the growth potential of the company.  That's where there is real money to be made. <p>
<p>
<p>
