nt pensions are at risk--and even the best company pension will likely only cover up to 70% of pre-retirement income.  That's a gap even a small RSP can bridge.  For example, your eligible contribution could be only $600 a year.  But, $600 a year at 8% over 30 years will accumulate to $68,000.<P>If you contribute your RSP dollars to a Spousal Plan, you get additional benefits.  One, you save taxes now.  Two, by splitting income with your spouse, you can both draw lower retirement incomes to reduce your overall tax exposure.<P>Small annual RSP investments now can make a big difference in the years to come.<P><A HREF="/old_ditiplist.html"><B>Previous Tips</B></A><HR><PRE></PRE><FONT SIZE=2>This communication is published by C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. Any commentaries contained in this communication are provided as a general source of information and should not be considered personal investment advice.  Every effort has been made to ensure that the material contained in this communication is accurate at the time of publication.  However, C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. cannot guarantee its accuracy or completeness and accepts no responsibility for any loss arising from any use of or reliance on the information contained herein.<P><A HREF="disclaimer.html">Complete disclaimer text</A><p></FONT>All material on this site is copyright &copy; C.I. Mutual Funds, 1995, 1996<P>Questions?  send mail to <A HREF="MAILTO:webmaster@cifunds.com">webmaster@cifunds.com</A>.</BODY> </HTML> 
