<hr noshade><p>
<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>Tips on how to curb your spending emotions</H3>
Our emotions often lead us into the trap of over-spending. But it's important to everyone's financial health to not spend what you don't have.  So here are five tips for taking control:<p>
One, remember that the happiness that money buys is terribly shallow.  <p>
Two, don't drown your kids in expensive, but superflous, faddy clothing.  Look for a compromise between what's in and what's affordable.<p>
Three, avoid spending just to feel good.  It's not uncommon to head to the mall for a "pick-me-up" purchase when we feel down. Instead, try a good book or a walk in the park.<p>
Four, stay clear of the  "keeping-up-with-the-Joneses" trap.  Let the Joneses deal with the debt payments!<p>
And five, get over the fashion avant garde thing.   Styles change quickly and keeping up is costly.<p>
So remember to watch your emotions when spending, because they can influence how MoneyWorks! <p>
<p>
