 averaging is a technique you use to make regular, monthly contributions to a savings or investment plan.  You can put away as little as 25 dollars a month, and this money goes into buying units in an investment fund.   By doing it regularly, you buy more units when the price is low, and fewer units when the price is high.   Therefore, your average cost is lower than it might have been if you'd tried to time the market.   <P>You also benefit from compound growth if your earlier monthly investments begin to generate returns and are reinvested.   You free yourself from worries about what the market might do next, because you're in for the long haul.  <P>If you make investing a habit you can reap enormous rewards.  Dollar-cost-averaging, a smart strategy for savvy investors.<P><A HREF="/old_ditiplist.html"><B>Previous Tips</B></A><HR><PRE></PRE><FONT SIZE=2>This communication is published by C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. Any commentaries contained in this communication are provided as a general source of information and should not be considered personal investment advice.  Every effort has been made to ensure that the material contained in this communication is accurate at the time of publication.  However, C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. cannot guarantee its accuracy or completeness and accepts no responsibility for any loss arising from any use of or reliance on the information contained herein.<P><A HREF="disclaimer.html">Complete disclaimer text</A><p></FONT>All material on this site is copyright &copy; C.I. Mutual Funds, 1995, 1996<P>Questions?  send mail to <A HREF="MAILTO:webmaster@cifunds.com">webmaster@cifunds.com</A>.</BODY> </HTML> 
