our personality.  Simply put, some people are their own worst enemy when it comes to investing.  They make three common mistakes.  They buy investments, driven by greed.  They want a quick buck.  They sell too quickly, driven by fear.  And they invest in things that they know little about.  These investors, guided by emotion rather than knowledge, tend to lose their money, forgetting how hard it is to earn it in the first place.  Be honest with yourself when assessing your investment track record.  And, if you're tempted to go for a gamble, it doesn't mean you shouldn't invest.  But you might improve your odds by choosing a professional to help select your investments. <p><p><p><A HREF="/old_ditiplist.html"><B>Previous Tips</B></A><HR><PRE></PRE><FONT SIZE=2>This communication is published by C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. Any commentaries contained in this communication are provided as a general source of information and should not be considered personal investment advice.  Every effort has been made to ensure that the material contained in this communication is accurate at the time of publication.  However, C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. cannot guarantee its accuracy or completeness and accepts no responsibility for any loss arising from any use of or reliance on the information contained herein.<P><A HREF="disclaimer.html">Complete disclaimer text</A><p></FONT>All material on this site is copyright &copy; C.I. Mutual Funds, 1995, 1996<P>Questions?  send mail to <A HREF="MAILTO:webmaster@cifunds.com">webmaster@cifunds.com</A>.</BODY> </HTML> 
