<hr noshade><p>
<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>Nobody ever has enough money.</H3>
The number one reason that people aren't wealthy is because they don't have enough money.  What we mean is - people don't accumulate wealth because they believe they don't have enough money to save and invest.  Some of our previous reports have shown how small amounts of money, invested regularly over 25 or 30 years, can grow into hundreds of thousands of dollars.  So, when we looked at the habits of one young person out on his own, we discovered that one or two less rented videos a week, a beer at home instead of at the bar, using the apartment stove instead of a restaurant, and not worrying about the pricey fashion label on the back of the jeans, paying off the VISA every month to avoid interest penalties, can generate the kind of cash that can grow into considerable wealth over the years.  It's important to remember that having fun in life does not always mean spending money. <p>
<p>
