<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>Mutual funds have changed things!</H3>
The latest figures on Mutual Fund investing show that people continue to put money into funds like never before.  Total fund assets are close to 190 billion dollars.  More than a quarter of this, 50 billion, is invested in Canadian equity funds.  About half that amount, 26 billion, is invested in Money Market funds - which suggests that most people are looking for growth and long term performance rather than short term security.  Canadians are becoming more diversified too, with over 40 billion invested in other markets, like New York,  Asia and the Emerging nations.   All that mutual fund cash has become such a powerful force, that many experts believe the markets are actually more stable because of it.  And they don't think it is nervous money that will be pulled out in a panic during short term fluctations.  It's how MoneyWorks. <p>
<p>
