<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>C.I. Mutual Funds Daily $ Tip</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#EBE8DF"><CENTER><A HREF="/text_only.html"><FONT SIZE=3>Text Only Options </FONT></B></CENTER><BR><CENTER><A HREF="/mainimage.map"><IMG SRC="topmenu.gif" WIDTH=658 HEIGHT=161 BORDER=off usemap="#mainmap" ismap></A><map name="mainmap"><area coords="100,14,203,39"href="/about_ci.html"><area coords="101,41,203,66"href="/prices_ci.html"><area coords="100,68,203,92"href="/managers_ci.html"><area coords="100,95,203,120"href="/performance_ci.html"><area coords="316,14,426,39"href="/about_hansberger.html"><area coords="316,41,427,66"href="/prices_hansberger.html"><area coords="316,67,427,93"href="/managers_hansberger.html"><area coords="316,95,427,120"href="/performance_hansberger.html"><area coords="539,14,643,39"href="/about_sector.html"><area coords="539,41,642,65"href="/prices_sector.html"><area coords="539,68,642,93"href="/managers_sector.html"><area coords="539,94,643,120"href="/performance_sector.html"><area coords="4,137,94,160"href="/home.html"><area coords="97,137,187,160"href="/perspective.html"><area coords="192,137,280,161"href="/cinews.html"><area coords="285,137,373,161"href="/feedback.html"><area coords="378,136,468,160"href="/calculator.html"><area coords="471,137,561,163"href="/libruary.html"><area coords="565,137,654,160"href="/links.html"><area coords="22,33,98,114"href="/about_ci.html"><area coords="240,32,316,115"href="/about_hansberger.html"><area coords="468,26,538,115"href="/about_sector.html"></map></CENTER><BR><BR><TD><CENTER><FONT SIZE=7>C.I. Daily $ Tip</FONT><br>By Everett Banning, Host of Moneyworks</CENTER></td></tr></table><hr noshade><p><IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg"><h3>Save tax by giving money to your kids.</H3>You might be able to lower your annual tax bill by giving some money to your spouse or kids.  The idea is to split income as much as you can.  One thought is to gift money to children over the age of 18 - assuming they're in a lower tax bracket than you.  The children invest the money.  <P></P>The funds they earn from the investments are taxed in their hands, they get to use up all their personal tax credits, deductions, and RSP room, exposing your family to a lower overall tax hit.  With younger children, consider putting any child benefit payments from the government into an account in the child's name.  That way, the income earned by the money is not attributed to you.  You can also remove taxable income from your future tax returns by transferring property or funds to your spouse or children, so that any capital gains or income will be attributed to them.  Seek advice from a qualified financial expert to be sure this is done properly. <p><p><p><A HREF="/old_ditiplist.html"><B>Previous Tips</B></A><HR><PRE></PRE><FONT SIZE=2>This communication is published by C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. Any commentaries contained in this communication are provided as a general source of information and should not be considered personal investment advice.  Every effort has been made to ensure that the material contained in this communication is accurate at the time of publication.  However, C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. cannot guarantee its accuracy or completeness and accepts no responsibility for any loss arising from any use of or reliance on the information contained herein.<P><A HREF="disclaimer.html">Complete disclaimer text</A><p></FONT>All material on this site is copyright &copy; C.I. Mutual Funds, 1995, 1996<P>Questions?  send mail to <A HREF="MAILTO:webmaster@cifunds.com">webmaster@cifunds.com</A>.</BODY> </HTML> 
