$150 billion in assets. So how do you pick the right one for you? <P>First, you should consult a financial adviser to help craft a strategy which takes into consideration your age, income, goals and tax picture.  <P>Second, learn about the different kinds of funds.  There are money market funds, fixed income funds, equity, balanced, and speciality funds.  When you select your mix of investments, also consider international as well as domestic funds to get the growth and income you want.  <P>Third, find out about the track record of the people who manage the fund, and make sure the track record is for the current manager. Although past performance is no guarantee of future returns, you can still buy quality.  <P>A solid plan, product knowledge, and good management - three factors that affect your choice of investment funds.<P><A HREF="/old_ditiplist.html"><B>Previous Tips</B></A><HR><PRE></PRE><FONT SIZE=2>This communication is published by C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. Any commentaries contained in this communication are provided as a general source of information and should not be considered personal investment advice.  Every effort has been made to ensure that the material contained in this communication is accurate at the time of publication.  However, C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. cannot guarantee its accuracy or completeness and accepts no responsibility for any loss arising from any use of or reliance on the information contained herein.<P><A HREF="disclaimer.html">Complete disclaimer text</A><p></FONT>All material on this site is copyright &copy; C.I. Mutual Funds, 1995, 1996<P>Questions?  send mail to <A HREF="MAILTO:webmaster@cifunds.com">webmaster@cifunds.com</A>.</BODY> </HTML> 
