<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>What eager beavers can do to learn lots about investing.</H3>
Most of us don't have enough time to learn about investing or personal finance issues. That's too bad, because knowledge can do much to improve your living standards. If you can squeeze in the time, you may consider  courses with the Canadian Securities Institute. It offers the Canadian Securities Course, which stock brokers and various investment industry people must take. But in shorter courses, tailored for the public, you can learn how to analyze investment opportunities or understand how the economy works.  The courses will teach you everything from how to understand what the money supply is and why it matters, to how to analyse the annual report of a publically traded company.  Becoming  a better informed investor will help you ask your financial advisor better questions and  give you keener insight into  how MoneyWorks! <p>
<p>
