<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>The good and the bad on the dollar!</H3>
Canada's been living with a 71 or 72 cent dollar for the past few years.  Recently, it's been up around 74. Some experts predict it'll go higher.  You can see the pride shining from the looney.  A high value dollar makes people feel better, as if the world has given it a higher mark on a global economy test.  There are some good aspects this.  It makes it cheaper to import things - like cars and stereos.  It makes  holidays more affordable.  You get more Maragaritas on the beach.  Now, for the downside.  A higher dollar makes it more expensive for others to buy Canadian goods, and that effects jobs and corporate profits.  It makes a Canadian vacation more expensive.  And  a higher dollar can effect the balance of payments, and push up interest rates.  So, ego aside, a rising dollar is not always worth celebrating. <p>
<p>
<p>
