titutions.  <p><p>First, a self-directed RRSP allows you to put a variety of investments from different sources all in one RRSP account.  You can diversify by including a mixture of individual bonds, stocks, and investment funds. Second, you can also include foreign investments.  Remember, Canada is only 3 percent of the world market, and you can devote 20 percent of your RRSP to foreign investments. Third, a self-directed plan which includes all your RRSP investments may be cheaper, because you pay only one administration fee.<p><p>Remember though, you will need to spend the time and research required to keep careful track of your investments' performance, and you will have to pay brokerage fees when you buy or sell. Talk to your investment adviser to see if a self-directed RRSP is right for you.<p><p><A HREF="/old_ditiplist.html"><B>Previous Tips</B></A><HR><PRE></PRE><FONT SIZE=2>This communication is published by C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. Any commentaries contained in this communication are provided as a general source of information and should not be considered personal investment advice.  Every effort has been made to ensure that the material contained in this communication is accurate at the time of publication.  However, C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. cannot guarantee its accuracy or completeness and accepts no responsibility for any loss arising from any use of or reliance on the information contained herein.<P><A HREF="disclaimer.html">Complete disclaimer text</A><p></FONT>All material on this site is copyright &copy; C.I. Mutual Funds, 1995, 1996<P>Questions?  send mail to <A HREF="MAILTO:webmaster@cifunds.com">webmaster@cifunds.com</A>.</BODY> </HTML> 
