ple, if your kids have grown and left home, if the mortgage is paid off, and if you have a comfortable nestegg, then you should really ask if you need insurance at all!  But if you're raising a family and carrying a mortgage, you probably do need some life insurance.  <P></P>To calculate how much, determine how much family income is needed to maintain your current lifestyle for a year.  Multiply that by 10. If you currently spend 40 thousand a year, 400 thousand in insurance earning 10 per cent interest would maintain the household.  Buying more insurance than you need curtails the amount you can put into savings.  So make sure you're covered but not over covered.  Being sensible with insurance helps ensure that MoneyWorks!  I'm Everett Banning<p><p><A HREF="/old_ditiplist.html"><B>Previous Tips</B></A><HR><PRE></PRE><FONT SIZE=2>This communication is published by C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. Any commentaries contained in this communication are provided as a general source of information and should not be considered personal investment advice.  Every effort has been made to ensure that the material contained in this communication is accurate at the time of publication.  However, C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. cannot guarantee its accuracy or completeness and accepts no responsibility for any loss arising from any use of or reliance on the information contained herein.<P><A HREF="disclaimer.html">Complete disclaimer text</A><p></FONT>All material on this site is copyright &copy; C.I. Mutual Funds, 1995, 1996<P>Questions?  send mail to <A HREF="MAILTO:webmaster@cifunds.com">webmaster@cifunds.com</A>.</BODY> </HTML> 
