more than a third of Canadians still have not taken steps to lower their long distance costs.<P>You don't necessarily have to switch telephone companies to get better rates, just follow these steps:  <P>Identify your calling patterns.  <P>Call your phone company and ask for their best possible rate based on your patterns.  <P>Insist on very specific answers.  <P>Then, armed with that information, start calling competitive phone services and ask them for their best rates based on your patterns.  <P>Check that there are no hidden costs.  <P>Find out their service capabilities.  <P>Make sure they don't charge for incomplete calls.<P>You can cut your calling expenses, and add the amount saved to your monthly mutual fund investment.<P><A HREF="/old_ditiplist.html"><B>Previous Tips</B></A><HR><PRE></PRE><FONT SIZE=2>This communication is published by C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. Any commentaries contained in this communication are provided as a general source of information and should not be considered personal investment advice.  Every effort has been made to ensure that the material contained in this communication is accurate at the time of publication.  However, C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. cannot guarantee its accuracy or completeness and accepts no responsibility for any loss arising from any use of or reliance on the information contained herein.<P><A HREF="disclaimer.html">Complete disclaimer text</A><p></FONT>All material on this site is copyright &copy; C.I. Mutual Funds, 1995, 1996<P>Questions?  send mail to <A HREF="MAILTO:webmaster@cifunds.com">webmaster@cifunds.com</A>.</BODY> </HTML> 
