<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>C.I. Mutual Funds Daily $ Tip</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#EBE8DF"><CENTER><A HREF="/text_only.html"><FONT SIZE=3>Text Only Options </FONT></B></CENTER><BR><CENTER><A HREF="/mainimage.map"><IMG SRC="topmenu.gif" WIDTH=658 HEIGHT=161 BORDER=off usemap="#mainmap" ismap></A><map name="mainmap"><area coords="100,14,203,39"href="/about_ci.html"><area coords="101,41,203,66"href="/prices_ci.html"><area coords="100,68,203,92"href="/managers_ci.html"><area coords="100,95,203,120"href="/performance_ci.html"><area coords="316,14,426,39"href="/about_hansberger.html"><area coords="316,41,427,66"href="/prices_hansberger.html"><area coords="316,67,427,93"href="/managers_hansberger.html"><area coords="316,95,427,120"href="/performance_hansberger.html"><area coords="539,14,643,39"href="/about_sector.html"><area coords="539,41,642,65"href="/prices_sector.html"><area coords="539,68,642,93"href="/managers_sector.html"><area coords="539,94,643,120"href="/performance_sector.html"><area coords="4,137,94,160"href="/home.html"><area coords="97,137,187,160"href="/perspective.html"><area coords="192,137,280,161"href="/cinews.html"><area coords="285,137,373,161"href="/feedback.html"><area coords="378,136,468,160"href="/calculator.html"><area coords="471,137,561,163"href="/libruary.html"><area coords="565,137,654,160"href="/links.html"><area coords="22,33,98,114"href="/about_ci.html"><area coords="240,32,316,115"href="/about_hansberger.html"><area coords="468,26,538,115"href="/about_sector.html"></map></CENTER><BR><BR><TD><CENTER><FONT SIZE=7>C.I. Daily $ Tip</FONT><br>By Everett Banning, Host of Moneyworks</CENTER></td></tr></table><hr noshade><p><IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg"><h3>The cost of getting your money back.</H3><p>We've talked about all kinds of ways to put money into an RSP - but not much about getting the money out.  An RSP is simply a way of delaying tax - hopefully until a time of your life when your tax rate will be lower.  But lots of people need to dip into their RSP savings before they retire.  When you make a withdrawal, the institution holding your RSP will withhold some of the money for taxes, and forward it to Revenue Canada.  <p><p>This hit isn't as bad as you might imagine.  If you take out less than five thousand dollars, the withholding tax is just ten percent.  Up to fifteen thousand dollars, the amount withheld is twenty percent.  And over fifteen thousand, the rate is 30 percent.  At the end of the year, you must report the withdrawals as income.  And that could mean a higher tax hit then - which could lead to another sizeable payment to Ottawa.  <p><p>So, plan your RSP withdrawals carefully.  It's how MoneyWorks. <p><p><p><A HREF="/old_ditiplist.html"><B>Previous Tips</B></A><HR><PRE></PRE><FONT SIZE=2>This communication is published by C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. Any commentaries contained in this communication are provided as a general source of information and should not be considered personal investment advice.  Every effort has been made to ensure that the material contained in this communication is accurate at the time of publication.  However, C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. cannot guarantee its accuracy or completeness and accepts no responsibility for any loss arising from any use of or reliance on the information contained herein.<P><A HREF="disclaimer.html">Complete disclaimer text</A><p></FONT>All material on this site is copyright &copy; C.I. Mutual Funds, 1995, 1996<P>Questions?  send mail to <A HREF="MAILTO:webmaster@cifunds.com">webmaster@cifunds.com</A>.</BODY> </HTML> 
