rates fall, so investors receive their normal interest plus a capital gain if they sell shares of the fund. Also, when interest rates fall, most companies become more profitable because their floating loan costs decrease. Banks win because they lower the interest they give depositors while their fixed-rate outstanding loans don't change; their costs go down while their income stays the same. Equity mutual funds may rise because of these increased profits and because investors are turning to equities from bonds, pushing up their price on increased demand.<p><p>Natural resource companies may like rising interest rates because the price of their products, such as oil, minerals, or timber, may rise as well, unless they are locked into long-term price contracts with their customers.<p><p>Interest rates should attract your interest, because they can dramatically affect the return on your investments.<p><p><A HREF="/old_ditiplist.html"><B>Previous Tips</B></A><HR><PRE></PRE><FONT SIZE=2>This communication is published by C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. Any commentaries contained in this communication are provided as a general source of information and should not be considered personal investment advice.  Every effort has been made to ensure that the material contained in this communication is accurate at the time of publication.  However, C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. cannot guarantee its accuracy or completeness and accepts no responsibility for any loss arising from any use of or reliance on the information contained herein.<P><A HREF="disclaimer.html">Complete disclaimer text</A><p></FONT>All material on this site is copyright &copy; C.I. Mutual Funds, 1995, 1996<P>Questions?  send mail to <A HREF="MAILTO:webmaster@cifunds.com">webmaster@cifunds.com</A>.</BODY> </HTML> 
