<hr noshade><p>
<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>They think young, but they're getting older.</H3>
The young-thinking, but getting older boomers are more powerful and wealthier than ever.  With the some post Second World War babies now over the age of fifty, the banking and financial service businesses are well aware of this group's financial clout.  People over fifty make up one-quarter of the population.  They control three-quarter's of the nation's private wealth.  That leaves just a quarter of the nation's wealth to everybody else.  Many of them own their homes, mortgage-free.  Their kids are grown and educated.  Boomers at the peak of their careers and earning power.  And they stand to inherit hundreds of billions worth of assets from their parents.  There is good news for all generations in this phenomenon, because this will have to be invested.  It will be used to fuel new enterprises, which creates opportunities and economic growth.  As in the past 50 years, the boomers will again, spread their wealth. <p>
<p>
