ng term, a lease will cost you more.  <p><p>Consider the differences between a lease and a loan.  With an auto loan, as you make payments, the loan gets smaller.  That means more of each succeeding loan payment goes to principal and not just interest.  <p><p>With a lease, you're actually on the hook longer for more of that principal.  That's because a lease essentially gives you access to more credit for a longer term with lower payments.  So your lease payments cover the costs of carrying the principal but don't do much to reduce it.  As well, the tax benefit of leasing is often not as lucrative as promoted.  <p><p>So, if you're thinking, "new car", make sure to look before you lease ... because that's how MoneyWorks!<p><p><p><A HREF="/old_ditiplist.html"><B>Previous Tips</B></A><HR><PRE></PRE><FONT SIZE=2>This communication is published by C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. Any commentaries contained in this communication are provided as a general source of information and should not be considered personal investment advice.  Every effort has been made to ensure that the material contained in this communication is accurate at the time of publication.  However, C.I. Mutual Funds Inc. cannot guarantee its accuracy or completeness and accepts no responsibility for any loss arising from any use of or reliance on the information contained herein.<P><A HREF="disclaimer.html">Complete disclaimer text</A><p></FONT>All material on this site is copyright &copy; C.I. Mutual Funds, 1995, 1996<P>Questions?  send mail to <A HREF="MAILTO:webmaster@cifunds.com">webmaster@cifunds.com</A>.</BODY> </HTML> 
