<hr noshade><p>
<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>Watch the Internet scams.</H3>
Get rich quick stock scams that are as old as fool's gold have gone onto the Internet to catch the unwary.  And regulators in both Canada and the United States are concerned.  By its very nature, the Internet has an aura of high-tech sophistication about it.  It is used by so many in-the-know people, that the Internet seems to be just the place to pick up insider tips and hot money-making information.  But viewed simply, the Internet is no more than an electronic street corner - a place where people meet and exchange information.  And like a street corner, there are all kinds of odd and disreputable characters hanging around.  Authorities have already nabbed some of them, who were peddling two-bit stocks and rip-off investments.  The Internet is a terrific place to learn about personal finance and to do your banking and investing.  But as in other aspects of your life, make your Internet connections with well-known, reputable companies, and don't rush in where even fools should fear to tread, on the Internet. <p>
<p>
