<TD><CENTER><FONT SIZE=7>C.I. Daily $ Tip</FONT><br>By Everett Banning, Host of Moneyworks</CENTER></td>
</tr>
</table>
<hr noshade><p>
<IMG Hspace=10 border=0 alt="Everett Banning" ALIGN=right SRC="/banning.jpeg">
<h3>Your investments will fall.</H3>
Although there were days when investors were giddy with the three of the rising stock market, recent bumps on the road have now made it clear to everybody that the markets will also fall.  Anybody in search of something with better growth potential than a GIC is accepting market volatility as a fact of investment life.  A GIC's slight growth curve is smooth, but not very high.  The stock market's growth curve is jagged, but the long term trend is more impressive.  Those who are keen to have their assets grow handsomely must first set a time horizon.  If you're in for five, ten or more years, there's time to ride through the tough times in the stock market, and benefit from much better times.  Select your stocks and investment funds carefully, so you know the managers behind them will act in your interest through different  business and market conditions. And don't put all your money in just one or two investments. <p>
<p>
<p>
<A HREF="/old_ditiplist.html"><B>Previous Tips</B></A>
