</DOCHDR>
<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>StorageCenter&#174</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<IMG SRC="/gifs/logo_and_tagline.gif">
<IMG SRC="/gifs/Line.gif" WIDTH=100%>
<BR>
<CENTER>
<IMG SRC="/gifs/StorageCenterLogo.gif"></CENTER> 
<CENTER><H1>Complete Storage Management for Distributed Computed</H1>
<H4><EM>Now Supporting UNIX and Windows NT</EM></H4><BR>
<H3><A HREF="#1">Product Overview</A><BR>
<A HREF="#2">StorageCenter Beats the Competition</A><BR>
<A HREF="#3">Storage Management - The Key to Protecting Your Data</A><BR>
<A HREF="#4">Administration Module</A><BR>
<A HREF="#5">Backup and Restore Module</A><BR>
<A HREF="#6">Media Management Module</A><BR>
<A HREF="#7">Archiving Module</A><BR>
<A HREF="#8">StorageCenter Tools</A><BR>
<A HREF="#8.5">RSA Data Encryption in StorageCenter</A><BR>
<A HREF="#9">StorageCenter is Scaled to Meet Your Needs</A><BR>
<A HREF="/SCscreens/sc_screens.html">View the StorageCenter&#174; GUI and
Sample Screens</A><BR>
<A HREF="sc_jukeboxes.html">View a Listing of Supported Jukeboxes</A><BR>
<A HREF="/demo/sc.html">View the StorageCenter&#174; Demo</A></H3>
</CENTER>
<HR WIDTH="500" SIZE="6" ALIGN="CENTER">


<A NAME="1"></A><H2>Product Overview</H2><BR>
<H4>Powerful, Flexible, and Reliable</H4>
<P>
StorageCenter is designed to protect your most valuable asset - your data.  It offers power, flexibility, and reliability not found in other software.  StorageCenter is powerful because it is a complete and in-depth solution.  It's flexible because its architecture fits any network configuration and it scales to meet your needs.  It's reliable because it eliminates any single point of failure.</P>
<H4>Complete Solution</H4>
<P>
StorageCenter is a comprehensive storage management solution.  It offers four applications to assist you in managing your data:  Administration, Media Management, Backup and Restore, and Archiving.  Competitive solutions offering only backup and retrieval cannot be considered true storage management since they do only part of the job.</P>
<H4>Flexible Architecture</H4>
<P>
StorageCenter uses a Master Database architecture.  This architecture allows any file on any drive on any licensed CPU to be backed up or restored to/from any device attached to any licensed CPU.  StorageCenter can balance backup jobs between multiple CPUs, devices, and networks.  StorageCenter uses peer-to-peer networking to achieve this flexibility; hence there is no requirement to have a dedicated "backup server." StorageCenter is offered in Enterprise, Workgroup, and Personal versions, scaled to meet your needs.</P>
<H4>No Single Point of Failure</H4>
<P>
The Master Database can be mirrored on multiple CPUs to ensure robust operation.  If the primary host fails, an alternate CPU automatically takes over database functions.  In addition, StorageCenter minimizes the impact of a backup server failure by allowing multiple backup servers in a single StorageCenter domain.  If a backup server or device fails, the administrator can activate work orders to reroute jobs around the failed component.</P>
<HR>


<A NAME="2"></A><H2>StorageCenter beats the competition</H2><BR>
<H4>Competitors: Rigid Architecture</H4>
<P>
Some competitors have a rigid and confusing architecture.  They require you to design your network to take advantage of their product.  They require dedicated backup servers and devices thereby creating a performance bottleneck and single point of failure.  They require you to use proprietary tape formats which limit your long term flexibility and compatibility.</P>
<H4>StorageCenter: Fits Your Network</H4>
<P>
StorageCenter's unique peer-to-peer architecture is designed to fit any existing network.  You select which devices and CPUs will receive your backups.  StorageCenter leverages your existing resources and adapts to your future plans.  It won't inhibit your network's architectural flexibility, now or in the future.  StorageCenter also uses standard tape formats to assure long term compatibility and interoperability.</P>
<H4>Competitors: Rigid Pricing</H4>
<P>
The pricing of some competitors is more rigid than their architecture.  For example, to avoid exorbitant license fees for extra "backup servers," you must put all your tape devices on the same CPU.  They also hit you with extra charges if you mix different operating systems on the same network.  Why should their pricing drive your architecture?</P>
<H4>StorageCenter: Sensible Pricing</H4>
<P>
With StorageCenter's modular design, you only pay for the capability you need regardless of the architecture you choose.  Whether you're protecting a large enterprise, a small workgroup, or a single CPU, StorageCenter offers a solution scaled to your needs.  We offer you a cost effective solution regardless of your network architecture, number of CPUs, type of tape devices, or operating 
systems.</P>
<HR>


<A NAME="3"></A><H2>Storage Management - the key to protecting your data</H2>
<BR>
<H4>Data - An Irreplaceable Asset</H4>
<P>
Most experts point out that data is the most difficult, expensive, and time consuming asset to replace, whether lost to user error, a malicious act, or a natural disaster.  While insurance may adequately cover the cost of replacing facilities and equipment, data can be irreplaceable at any price.  Professional storage management is the key to protecting your organization from a data loss catastrophe.</P>
<H4>Professional Storage Management</H4>
<P>
Professional storage management requires putting the procedures in place to minimize the risk of data loss.  While most organizations have some method for backing up data, advanced storage management tools can help you become more methodical, timely, and efficient.  Professional storage management also allows you to address critical fiduciary, regulatory, and audit requirements that are seldom addressed by ad hoc backup solutions.  These needs include off-site tape vaulting, tape library management, and archiving for long term or permanent storage.</P>
<H4>Increased Productivity and Automation</H4>
<P>
Effective storage management tools can actually increase productivity by reducing both the time and skill level necessary to complete rudimentary tasks like daily and weekly backups, restoring lost files, cycling tapes, and creating data archives.  By automating repetitive tasks, storage management frees your staff to be more proactive.</P>
<H4>Improved Service Levels</H4>
<P>
It is a fact of life that data gets lost through user error.  The need to restore lost data will always exist.  It's also a fact of life that certain data will need to be stored for long periods.  Storage management tools allow you to provide these services to your data users without subjecting them to the uncertainties and delays of manual storage management techniques.</P>
<H4>Professional Tape Library Management</H4>
<P>
Most data backup regimens involve the cycling of tape volumes on a daily, weekly, or monthly basis to both on-site and off-site locations.  Add to this the need to keep some data in non-cycling archives and you have quite a pile of media on your hands.  Can you trust your tape library to manual labeling and tracking techniques?  Can you guarantee that your staff will never overwrite an archive tape?  How will you locate an archive tape several months or years from now?  The best answer to all these questions is a storage management tool that addresses the need for professional media management for your tape library.  Such a tool creates tape labels, verifies all tapes before writing to them, tracks their location, and manages the cycling process.</P>
<H4>Capacity Management</H4>
<P>
Storage management tools can give the administrator a means to systematically remove and archive inactive data from valuable disk storage while still keeping it accessible for quick and convenient restore.</P>
<HR>


<A NAME="4"></A><H2>Administration Module</H2> 
<BR>
<P>
The Administration Module provides a convenient way to define and name the hosts (CPUs), storage devices, media, and physical locations in your storage management domain.  Like all StorageCenter modules, Administration provides an easy Graphical User Interface.</P><BR>
<P>
Key Features:</P>
<UL>
<LI>assigns host and device "street names"
<LI>defines devices and media types
<LI>declares physical sites and storage locations
<LI>creates volume cycles* and volume pools
<LI>supports ANSI labels and bar codes
<LI>controls user lists and access privileges
</UL>
<HR>


<A NAME="5"></A><H2>Backup and Restore Module</H2> 
<BR>
<P>
The Backup and Restore Module allows you to initiate full, incremental, or selective backups and to restore data using a Graphical User Interface.  It offers convenient selection of file systems, backup devices, and job schedules.  The Backup and Restore Module is powerful enough for the administrator yet simple enough for the data user, making StorageCenter the right choice for organizations of all sizes that use UNIX or Windows NT.</P>
<P>
Key Features:</P>
<UL>
<LI>performs full, incremental, or selective backups
<LI>backs up all files, directories, and attributes
<LI>supports tape, optical, stacker, library, jukebox
<LI>stores backup catalogs on-disk for speedy search
<LI>maintains a detailed audit trail
<LI>reports job errors via e-mail or pager
<LI>stores data in standard tar or cpio format
<LI>compresses data for transmission across WANs
<LI>encrypts data for security using RSA algorithms
<LI>runs simultaneous parallel backup jobs*
<LI>appends multiple backup jobs to a single volume
<LI>spans large sessions across multiple volumes
<LI>cascades one saveset across multiple devices**
<LI>makes saveset copies for off-site storage*
<LI>backs up databases with SQL-BackTrack***
<LI>Stores pre-defined disaster recovery work orders
<LI>allows easy location and restore of selected files
</UL><BR>
<P>
*   Enterprise version only (see back cover)<BR>
**  Enterprise and Workgroup versions only<BR>
*** Requires optional DataTools SQL-BackTrack for Oracle or Sybase</P>
<HR>



<A NAME="6"></A><H2>Media Management Module</H2><BR>
<P>
The Media Management Module allows users to track and control the allocation, usage, location, expiration, and cycling of all media volumes and savesets.  It assists the administrator by increasing productivity and professionalism in an era of downsizing and tight budgets.</P>

<P>
Key Features:<P>
<UL>
<LI>tracks expiration date of each saveset on a volume
<LI>tracks volume scratch data
<LI>prevents against accidental overwrites
<LI>generates reports on media status
<LI>defines access control list for each saveset
<LI>tracks volume cycling to multiple locations
<LI>creates work orders to move volumes*
</UL>
<BR>
<P>
* Enterprise version only</P>
<HR>


<A NAME="7"></A><H2>Archiving Module</H2><BR>
<P>
The Archiving Module ends your disk space nightmares by providing rational and controlled methods for migrating files from limited disk space to virtually limitless off-line media.  The Grooming feature allows the administrator to remove files using criteria such as "not accessed in 90 days" or "having a 'tmp' extension."  The Make Space feature is also driven by user specified criteria but removes just enough files to meet the specified free-space goal.  StorageCenter can remove files in two ways.  "Deletion" permanently removes unneeded files, while the "Shelve" option moves files to tape and leaves a marker on the disk pointing to the archive location.  Archiving gives the administrator a means to systematically remove inactive data from valuable disk storage while still keeping it accessible for quick and convenient retrieval.</P>
<P>
Key Features:</P>
<UL>
<LI>cleans up file systems with the Grooming feature
<LI>frees valuable storage with the Make Space feature
<LI>constructs detailed file migration strategies
<LI>supports wild cards and other selection criteria
<LI>allows both Deletion and Shelving of data
<LI>provides on-disk file markers for shelved data
<LI>uses file markers for automatic retrieval
<LI>models strategies using Analyze Only mode
<LI>alerts file owners of pending migration via e-mail
<LI>notifies file owners of completed migration
<LI>assures future compatibility via standard media formats (tar and cpio)
</UL>
<HR>


<A NAME="8"></A><H2>StorageCenter Tools</H2><BR>
<P>
In addition to the modules described above, StorageCenter puts four additional tools at your fingertips:</P>
<UL>
<LI>Volume Initializer...  quickly initializes a new volume or range of volumes
<LI>Job Calendar...   presents all scheduled jobs by date
<LI>Backup File Browser...   quickly locates files or directories that have been backed up
<LI>Log File Viewer...   views audit trails of completed jobs
</UL>
<HR>


<A NAME="8.5"></A><H2>RSA Data Encryption Support</H2><BR>
<P>
StorageCenter includes encryption algorithms from RSA Data Security, Inc.,
the world leader in data encryption, and the inventor of the world-class
Public Key Cryptosystem.  This means that StorageCenter can make your backup
tapes anywhere in your network, and make them safely.  Cross-network
data transmission takes place using RSA's Digital Signature technology,
and savesets are created using RSA's 128-bit private key cryptosystem.
No one but the holder of the key can read the savesets.</P>
<P>
Perhaps you heard of a recent 'crack' in RSA's encryption.  The
incident involved a student who took advantage of 200 desktop systems,
and 2 mainframes, for a period of one week.  He eventually 'cracked' an
8-character string of data that had been encrypted.  The data he
cracked, though, had been encrypted with a 40-bit encryption algorithm.</P>
<P>
StorageCenter uses a 128-bit system, which is billions of times more
difficult to decrypt (without the key!). For more information on 
<A HREF="/SafetyPosit/SP_test/primer.html #6">encryption</A>, 
go to our Storage Management Key Definitions and Concepts page where you 
can also learn about <A HREF="/SafetyPosit/SP_test/primer.html #6.1">
node authentication</A>. These definitions and concepts are included in 
our section on SafetyPosit, our Internet backup service which also makes 
use of StorageCenter.</P>
<P>
Software Partners/32, Inc. is a business partner of RSA, and is thereby
an authorized OEM for their secure product.  We are the only ones with
the RSA encryption system as part of a standard backup/restore package.</P>

<HR>


<A NAME="9"></A><H2>StorageCenter is Scaled to Meet Your Needs</H2><BR>
<P>
StorageCenter is offered in three versions scaled for your configuration and needs: Enterprise, Workgroup, and Personal.  Value-added options are also available for robotic device control.  Open database backup for Oracle and Sybase is supported via SQL-BackTrack.*  With StorageCenter, you can get exactely what you need now and can easily expand as your network grows and changes.</P>
<BR>

