<TITLE>About Software Partners/32, INC.</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<IMG SRC="/gifs/logo_and_tagline.gif">
<IMG SRC="/gifs/Line.gif" WIDTH=100%>
<CENTER>
<H1>About Software Partners/32, Inc.</H1></CENTER>

<P>Since 1983, SOFTWARE PARTNERS/32, Inc. has supplied Backup/Restore, 
media management, and hierarchical storage management software tools to 
business, schools, military sites and industrial operations of all shapes,
sizes and description. The SP/32 product suite enables system management
to protect an organization's information resources, regardless of the
data's location, and to run systems at optimum efficiency.  SP/32 was
the first vendor in the industry to offer mainframe-style software tools
to manage, protect and secure data in the Digital VAX/VMS environment.
The Company has now extended support to the UNIX, OpenVMS, Windows NT and 
Digital Alpha environments.

<P>As its name implies, the Company views itself as a partner rather than a
software vendor.  Twenty-four hour product support and a liberal
demonstration/evaluation program are further testament to this point.  SP/32
offers a full range of consulting services for its software products, including
on-site installation assistance and product testing.
<BR><BR>
<CENTER>
<A HREF="#1">Markets Served</A><BR>
<A HREF="#2">Products</A><BR>
<A HREF="#3">Channels</A><BR>
<A HREF="#4">Contact Info</A><BR>
<A HREF="about_sp32_mgmt.html">Management</A><BR>
<A HREF="why_the_32.html">Why The '32'?</A><BR>
<A HREF="directions_to_sp32.html">Directions to SP/32</A></CENTER><BR>
<CENTER><HR SIZE=4></CENTER>
<A NAME="1"></A><H2>Markets Served</H2>
<P>SP/32 services clients in many industries and segments.  Fortune 500 clients
include Mobil, General Electric, Philip Morris, Texaco, British Petroleum,
DuPont, Boeing, R.J. Reynolds, Philips, Citibank and Dow Chemical.  Other
clients include universities, banking and financial institutions and large
government installations.

<P>SP/32 clients tend to be diversified organizations with multiple sites or
campus environments using distributed computing resources. Although these
organizations do not generally consider data classified, they do recognize a
need to segment and protect data through a centrally administered facility and
this service is provided effectively with SP/32 tools.  Clients tend to use a
heterogeneous computing environment with UNIX, Windows NT and OpenVMS systems.
<BR><BR>
<CENTER><HR SIZE=4></CENTER>
<A NAME="2"></A><H2>Products:</H2>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF="StorageCenter.html">StorageCenter&#174</A> extends data management capabilities to popular UNIX and Windows NT platforms.  Featuring a graphical user interface, <B>StorageCenter</B> provides reliable and flexible backup, restore, media management, and archiving.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="tapesys.html">TAPESYS&#174</A> is a comprehensive backup, restore, media management and archiving system for OpenVMS platforms.  It provides a complete range of services and functions, and eliminates potential problems caused by a single point of failure.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="thrunet.html">THRUnet&#174</A> extends the reach of <B>TAPESYS</B> to UNIX platforms.  With a UNIX-like interface, <B>THRUnet</B> allows SunOS, Solaris, IBM AIX, HP-UX, ULTRIX, SCO, Intergraph, and SGI IRIX clients to backup to OpenVMS hosts.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="thruway.html">THRUway&#174</A> provides access to remote disk drives, tape drives, and printers by making them appear as local devices.  <B>THRUway</B> extends the reach of <B>TAPESYS</B> and other OpenVMS applications.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="hierarchy.html">HIERARCHY&#174 </A> adds hierarchical storage management capability (HSM) to OpenVMS based systems.  With a wide range ot administrator options, <B>HIERARCHY</B> is compatible with <B>TAPESYS</B> or any backup and restore system.</LI>

<LI><A HREF="tt_recon.html">TT/RECON&#174 </A> provides VMS administrators with the ability to remotely control any terminal attached to a VMS-based system.  Ideal for education, demonstrations, and user help desks; <B>TT/RECON</B> provides virtual supervisory support.</LI>
</UL>
<CENTER><HR SIZE=4></CENTER>
<A NAME="3"></A><H2>Channels</H2>
<P>SP/32 utilizes several sales channels:
<UL><LI>Domestic distribution is pursued by SP/32's in-house sales and
marketing teams.  The Company also maintains Spire Technologies as a domestic
distributor. 
</LI>
<LI>A network of <A HREF="intl_distrib.html">international distributors</A> 
sell SP/32 products and services around the world.</LI>
<LI>SP/32 maintains formal relationships with storage systems OEMs and
third-party hardware distributors. 
</LI></UL>
