<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Software Partner's TAPESYS&#174</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<IMG SRC="/gifs/logo_and_tagline.gif">
<IMG SRC="/gifs/Line.gif" WIDTH=100%>

<CENTER><P><IMG SRC="/gifs/tapesys.gif" WIDTH=450 HEIGHT=150></P><BR><BR>
<H3><A HREF="#1">Product Overview</A><BR>
<A HREF="#2">Backup and Restore</A><BR>
<A HREF="#3">Media Management</A><BR>
<A HREF="#4">File Archiving</A><BR>
<A HREF="#5">Complete Data Security</A><BR>
<A HREF="#6">Flexible and Robust Architecture</A><BR>
<A HREF="#7">Management Reports</A><BR>
<A HREF="#8">Warranty & Support Information</A><BR>
<A HREF="#9">Features</A><BR></H3>
</CENTER>
<HR>
<A NAME="1"></A><H2>Product Overview</H2>
<P>TAPESYS is an automated data protection tool that manages a corporation's most valuable resource - its data.  Operating in an OpenVMS environment, TAPESYS provides a menu-driven suite of functions including: backup, restore, media management, and archiving.  TAPESYS enables the manager to establish a corporate-wide professional regimen for automated data backup. TAPESYS also provides advanced archiving tools for disk space management as well as media management tools for maintaining tape libraries.</P>
<P>TAPESYS operates in virtually all VMS and OpenVMS environments.  It is compatible with all magnetic and optical backup media including stackers, robotic devices, and jukeboxes.  TAPESYS companion products extend its capabilities with hierarchical storage management (HSM), remote data management, and UNIX support.</P>
<HR>
<A NAME="2"><H2>Backup and Restore</H2>
<P>TAPESYS provides a full set of features for automating the backup and restore of corporate-wide data.  TAPESYS has a flexible menu-driven interface to help the systems manager create backup schedules and strategies that are consistent with corporate goals.  The TAPESYS peer-to-peer architecture eliminates single point of failure problems inherent with a dedicated backup server.  TAPESYS manages backup resources and supports off-site or vault storage.  For example, TAPESYS can make exact duplicate off-site/vault tapes in parallel with regular backups via its Concurrent Magtape Processor (CMP) feature.  TAPESYS also aids the manager in tracking and controlling off-site/vault tapes. TAPESYS writes tapes using the standard, unmodified VMS BACKUP utility to ensure compatibility between systems.</P>
<HR>
<A NAME="3"><H2>Media Management</H2>
<P>TAPESYS provides all the tools needed to manage your tape or cartridge library.  The tape pool tracks the contents, status, and reuse date of each tape and ensures methodical tape rotation.  TAPESYS uses ANSI tape labeling conventions.  Tape labels are verified before backup to ensure that valuable data is not inadvertently overwritten due to operator error.  If inconsistencies are discovered, they are reported back to the operator console. TAPESYS jobs can call for specific tapes or scratch tapes to be supplied for backup jobs, to efficiently accommodate gravity stackers and robotic jukeboxes.</P>
<HR>
<A NAME="4"><H2>File Archiving</H2>
<P>TAPESYS also provides full archiving facilities in addition to media management.  TAPESYS will automatically archive files from disk to tape based upon the retention and expiration dates provided.  This utility gives the manager a rational and controlled means to ensure that there is always enough disk space.  Older, less used files can be archived to tape to free up limited disk space.  This is achieved without the risk of losing valuable data.</P>
<HR>
<A NAME="5"><H2>Complete Data Security</H2>
<P>Security is one of the most important parts of any storage management system. TAPESYS provides multiple security features.  Unauthorized use of allocated tapes is prohibited. Users can independently restore files from tapes allocated to them or files which they own on system backup tapes.  Based on the OpenVMS file protection scheme, users are prevented from making unauthorized copies of files they don't own.</P>
<HR>
<A NAME="6"><H2>Flexible and Robust Architecture</H2>
<P>TAPESYS maintains two database servers: one primary and one secondary, on two different nodes in the network.  If the node running the primary server goes down, the secondary server automatically takes over and handles all requests.  Similarly, TAPESYS maintains two copies of the media database on different disks anywhere in the network, and can continue to serve requests from across the network if either of the database disks goes down.  Recovery is transparent to the users and can even occur while system backups are underway.</P>
<HR>
<A NAME="7"><H2>Management Reports</H2>
<P>TAPESYS provides a Report Menu enabling the operator to produce reports quickly on all volumes in the library.  Free volume, allocated volume, and owner usage reports are standard.  The report writer provides scratch, allocation, and clean dates, mount counts, and protection codes as desired.  By maintaining detailed information about tape allocation and usage, TAPESYS provides information that can be used for effective allocation of costs.</P>
<HR>
<A NAME="8"><H2>Warranty & Support Information</H2>
<P>Understanding the importance of the backup function, Software Partners provides round the clock support services. Every TAPESYS user is afforded 90 days of no-charge warranty support.  In addition, customized on-site support, training and implementation services are available allowing customers to take full advantage of our wide range of experience in backup and restore strategies.  These services are available to both new and old customers.  Charges for these services as well as annual maintenance renewals apply.</P>
<HR>
<A NAME="9"><H2>Features</H2>
<UL>
<LI>Complete maintenance of the VAX/Alpha AXP tape and cartridge library, including media recycling, retention management, and versatile reporting
<LI>Automatic system backup and restore procedures</LI>
<LI>On-line directory of backed up files</LI>
<LI>Complete transaction logging with redundant Master File restore facility</LI>
<LI>Integrated Vault Storage Control System</LI>
<LI>Totally automated scheduling of all backups for lights-out processing</LI>
<LI>Full support of single CPU, Alpha/VAX clusters, and DECnet networks</LI>
<LI>Complete ANSI label monitoring</LI>
<LI>Media support for optical disks, TA90 cartridges and stackers, and many robotic devices</LI>
<LI>Round-robin device allocation</LI>
<LI>Security features to protect against unauthorized use</LI>
<LI>Ability to make concurrent multiple copies of backup tapes for off-site storage
<LI>Full and automatic archiving facilities</LI>

</UL>
<HR><CENTER>
<I>
