<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Phil Jamieson's Welcome</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<IMG SRC="/gifs/logo_and_tagline.gif">
<IMG SRC="/gifs/Line.gif" WIDTH=100%>
<CENTER>
<H1>Phil Jamieson's Welcome</H1>
</CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER>
<P>
<TABLE BORDER=7>
<TR>
<TD ALIGN=CENTER>
<IMG SRC="/photos/paj_pres.gif">
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE> 
</CENTER>

<P>
I'm Phil Jamieson, President and Co-founder of Software Partners/32, Inc.
Welcome to our web page.  I hope your time here is useful and interesting.
All of us at SP/32 are working constantly to improve our service and products 
for you, our very important customers.  Please drop me a line sometime to 
tell me how <A HREF="people.html">we</A> are doing.  Whether your comments 
are in the 'growth areas' category, or in the 'so-n-so is doing great' 
category, I would really like to hear from you.

<P>
Please write to me at
<A HREF="mailto:phil@softwarepartners.com">phil@softwarepartners.com</A>
or from AOL send to PJAMIESON, or on Compuserve at 76100,1505. 

<P>
<IMG SRC="/gifs/new2.gif"> to our web site, but not new to our operations and 
policies, is our <A HREF="ethics.html">Code of Ethics</A>.  Please check it 
out and drop me a comment on it.  How does it strike you?  How do you see it 
in action in our Company?  How do you think it can be improved?  I need to 
know about these things, and I need to hear from you.

<P>
Oh, and while you're here, please take a look at my newest slide show for 
<A HREF="http://www.sp32.com/SafetyPosit/SP_home.html">SafetyPosit
<SUP>&#40;sm&#41;</SUP></A>, a very important, extremely exciting project we 
are hard at work at now! SafetyPosit is a service product which, in the 
fullness of time, will have its own website and online services separate from 
Software Partners.  Soon this SafetyPosit will enable you to create all 
your regular backups offsite, immediately, for less than the cost of your 
present, onsite, labor- and capital-intensive backups!  Managing the project 
is <A HREF="/about_johnw.html">John Wallace</A>.

<P>
Meanwhile, <A HREF="StorageCenter.html">StorageCenter</A> is a major emphasis 
these days.  With V2.3 which expands platform support to Windows NT, we're 
now on to future versions that will be coming out with a steady stream of 
improvements. Our engineers recently completed our new Sybase interface 
(going into beta testing now),
and we're moving onto Oracle and Informix.  Watch for other great
new features as well, as we fill out the product line for UNIX and NT.
 Even now, though, our product, with our thirteen years of 
experience from major computing environments built in, is far ahead of the 
nearest competitors, and we're thrilled.  With StorageCenter working for you, 
you can get your backups done quickly and accurately, across networks small 
and large.  It is our 'next generation' software, and we're extremely proud 
of it.

<P>
If you go away with nothing more, I hope you at least understand from our
website that we are the company combining industrial-strength conventional
backup software solutions with contemporary Internet-based backup technology.
Using the same GUI, a customer of ours will be able to manage onsite backups,
with all the accompanying chores of tape retention, cycling, verifying, etc.
and at the same time, with the same structure, direct strategic files to be
backed up safely offsite, over the public Internet.  That's what the
StorageCenter/SafetyPosit combination is all about.
<P>
Another addition to our web-based StorageCenter presentation is the
<IMG SRC="/gifs/new2.gif">online demo, which takes you through the entire 
GUI.  <A HREF="/demo/sc.html">Try it</A> and 
<A HREF="mailto:philj@softwarepartners.com">let us know</A> how you like it!

<P>
<A HREF="tapesys.html">TAPESYS</A>, 
<A HREF="hierarchy.html">HIERARCHY</A> and 
<A HREF="thruway.html">THRUway</A> are still strong workers for us in
VMS Storage Management, and
we invite you to check them out as well.  We'll always be in the media 
management business, and therefore the backup and restore business, in VMS 
as well as UNIX, and eventually NT and Novell.
<P>
Thanks again for stopping here.  Enjoy your visit, and check it all
out!  We're glad you're here!

<P>
Sincerely yours,
<P>
<P>
<IMG SRC="/gifs/pajsig.gif">
<P>

Philip A. Jamieson
 
