<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Why The 32?</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<IMG SRC="/gifs/logo_and_tagline.gif">
<IMG SRC="/gifs/Line.gif" WIDTH=100%>
<CENTER>
<H1>Why The '32'?</H1></CENTER>
Are there 32 of you?  No, there are more.<P>
Are there 32 partners?  No.<P>
Are there 32 products? No.<P> <P> 
When Phil Jamieson, Mike Rieker and John Kernaghan founded the Company, back in 1983,
there were still a few major product lines coming from the booming
company in Maynard known as Digital Equipment Corp.  Those two platforms
were the VAX and the PDP-11.  [OK, there was also the DEC-20,
but they were fairly obscure.]  Now Digital laid down a marketing scheme
to distinguish software products from the two lines, in order to be able 
to tell them apart.  If, for example, you wanted to buy a Fortran
compiler for your PDP-11 running RSTS/E (pronounced 'ristis eee'),
you'd buy Fortran/11.  If you wanted to buy a Fortran compiler for your
new VAX, running VMS (pronounced 'V M S') you'd order Fortran/32.  Same
with Cobol, same with Datatrieve, same with just about everything that
ran in both environments.
<P><P>
We wanted people to know that we were strictly a VAX company (though our
roots were in RT-11, RSTS/E and RSX-11 (all PDP operating systems)).  SO
we took on the suffix of /32.  Hey, it made sense at the time, and we did
hit it big in VMS.<P>
<P>
Now, of course, VMS is just ONE of the many operating systems we support,
and the /32 is not as meaningful as it once was for us.  What do you think
we should do?  Drop it? Change it to /64?  How about /2000 for the upcoming
change in millenia?  <A HREF="mailto:philj@sp32.com">Write me a note</A>
, with your name and your suggestion.
I'll take the best one I get and act on it!<P>
<BR>
Thanks!
<BR>
p.s.  But why '32' and not '34' or '30'?  Well, the VAX is based on a
32-bit architecture (very advanced for the day in which it was introduced,
1977).  An addressable word in VAX memory contained 32 bits, instead of the
limited 16 bits in a PDP-11 word.  Digital prominently displayed the number
32 in lots of VAX and VMS literature.  We liked that.
<HR SIZE=4><CENTER>

<I>
<A HREF="sp32_home_page.html">Back to Home Page</A><BR><BR>
Please send comments to
<A HREF="mailto:webmaster@SoftwarePartners.com">webmaster@SoftwarePartners.com
</A><BR>or call us at (508) 887-6409
</I>

<br><BR>
<A HREF="/copyright.html"><font size=3>&copy; 1996</A>,
Software Partners/32, Inc.
