<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Software Partner's HIERARCHY&#174</TITLE>
</HEAD>
</BODY>
<IMG SRC="/gifs/logo_and_tagline.gif">
<IMG SRC="/gifs/Line.gif" WIDTH=100%>
<CENTER><H1>HIERARCHY&#174</H1></CENTER>
<HR>
<H2>DESCRIPTION</H2>
<P>HIERARCHY introduces true hierarchical storage management to OpenVMS. HIERARCHY manages disk space by leaving active files readily accessible on primary storage. Less active, "cold" files can be automatically and seamlessly archived or "shelved" to secondary or background storage. Archived files are routinely retrieved when opened by any OpenVMS application. Since no prior planning is required for an application to open an archived file, changes need not be made to existing run procedures.</P>
<P>HIERARCHY coexists with all standard OpenVMS applications and utilities. No changes are required to existing code, nor are special considerations necessary in new code.</P>
<HR>
<H2>FEATURES</H2>
<H3>Automatic Archiving</H3>
<P>HIERARCHY determines when files are unused and can select these files for shelving to nearline or offline storage. Shelving can be done either on demand or automatically at the determination of the system manager.</P>
<H3>RAM Disk Processing</H3>
<P>In addition to moving unused files to off-line storage, HIERARCHY has the ability to automatically and transparently transfer the most-used files to a RAM disk. This processing reduces the elapsed execution time of jobs as their I/O is redirected to use the RAM disk copy of the file. As with other HIERARCHY processing, there are no required changes to existing jobs for them to take advantage of the high speed RAM disk. </P>
<H3>Automatic Retrieval</H3>
<P>An archived file is not retrieved until the time it is truly needed. Executing DIRECTORY, SET FILE, RENAME, DELETE, or  PURGE commands will not cause the file to be retrieved. The file will be retrieved only when a record from that file is demanded.</P>
<H3>Intelligent Retrieval</H3>
<P>HIERARCHY can be implemented to redirect read-only file access to the offline location of the file, saving online magnetic disk space for updating only. Site-defined HIERARCHY parameters can be managed to optimize file location 
among various storage platforms, enabling the most efficient product performance.</P>
<H3>Dynamic Job Protection</H3>
<P>Output jobs will not abort due to insufficient disk space or disk quota. Instead, the output job will be suspended while alternatives for freeing up disk space are automatically performed by HIERARCHY. This can include automatic archiving of other stale files. 
The output job, whether batch or interactive, will continue afterwards without error.</P>
<H3>Seamless Directory</H3>
<P>Archived files continue to appear in standard DIRECTORY listings, even though the files themselves are located offline or nearline. The actual file locations can optionally be included in the output display.</P>
<H3>Flexible Interfaces</H3>
<P>To provide flexibility in storage management procedures, HIERARCHY supports four different interfaces:
<UL>
<LI>The HIST interface makes use of VMS BACKUP and an online history database to determine which files to archive,</LI>
<LI>The OPTICAL interface supports connections to an optical jukebox, as well as to all other standard output devices,</LI>
<LI>The <A HREF="tapesys.html">TAPESYS&#174</A> interface uses the media management and history database features of <A HREF="tapesys.html">TAPESYS</A>, The OpenVMS Tape Management System, and </LI>
<LI>The SIMPLE interface uses RMS to copy files from the monitored disk to the archive media.</LI>
</UL></P>
<H3>DECwindows Processing</H3>
<P>HIERARCHY supports DECwindows terminals by allowing HIERARCHY 
messages and prompts to be displayed as DECwindows pop-up dialog boxes.</P>
<H3>Jukebox Support</H3>
<P>HIERARCHY currently supports most optical and tape jukeboxes. Please contact Software Partners for more information.</P>
<H3>StorageTek 4400 ACS Support</H3>
<P>HIERARCHY brings your StorageTek&#174 4400 ACS to the VAX and enables the silo to perform as a robotic storage facility for archived OpenVMS files. The silo becomes an extended storage platform for your high speed VAX disks. Archived files appear as though they are on the VAX disk, but are actually resident on the silo, and are automatically retrieved when the file is accessed.</P>
<HR>
<H2>BENEFITS</H2>
<H3>True Hierarchical Storage</H3>
<P>HIERARCHY provides true hierarchical storage of files by matching the need for data to the appropriate device to handle that need. 
Expensive disk space is saved for frequently accessed "hot" files. Inexpensive optical disk or magnetic tape space is managed to store older, "cold" files. Storage location of those files is not the responsibility of the calling application, which remains untouched.  Instead, storage location is determined by cost-conscious, intelligent software routines in HIERARCHY that make the best use of disk space.</P>
<H3>Seamless Access</H3>
<P>Archived files are always available to standard applications. Standard 
DCL commands, e.g., DIRECTORY, SET FILE, RENAME, DELETE, 
or PURGE can be performed on archived files with conventional results. A standard OPEN command will cause the archived file to be retrieved.</P>
<H3>Production Savings</H3>
<P>Large production jobs that would run out of disk or quota space and normally abort are saved by HIERARCHY. Furthermore, operators and system managers no longer have to spend time moving large, old files around to find disk space for critical jobs to run.</P>
<H3>Efficient Disk Usage</H3>
<P>Disk space is taken up only by active files. Demand for additional disk space is curtailed, and only comes after the need for additional disk space is clearly proven.</P>
<HR>
<H2>HARDWARE SUPPORT</H2>
<P>HIERARCHY works on all standard DEC VAX and Alpha systems and supports all leading optical and tape storage systems.</P>
<P>Contact Software Partners for a complete list of supported vendor systems.</P>
<HR>
<H2>SOFTWARE COMPATIBILITY</H2>
<P>HIERARCHY V3 works with OpenVMS V5.4+ and Alpha VMS V6.1.</P>
<H3><A HREF="tapesys.html">TAPESYS</A> Interface</H3>
<P>HIERARCHY can be combined with <A HREF="tapesys.html"> TAPESYS</A>, The OpenVMS Tape Management System, to take advantage of the automatic backup and retrieval, and media management features of TAPESYS.</P>
<H3><A HREF="thruway.html">THRUway</A> Interface</H3>
<P>HIERARCHY can also be combined with <A HREF="thruway.html">THRUway&#174</A>, The OpenVMS Remote Device Access System, to use remote devices for 
archiving purposes.</P>
<HR>
<H2>SOFTWARE WARRANTY</H2>
<P>HIERARCHY customers are provided with complete warranty, support, and product enhancements for 90 days. Maintenance is then renewable on an annual basis. Product training is available.</P>
<HR><CENTER>
