<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> Media Management </TITLE>
<H1><CENTER>
<A><IMG SRC="mediamanagement.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE HSPACE=4 HEIGHT=75 WIDTH=75></A>
StorageCenter Media Management
</CENTER></H1>
<A><CENTER><IMG SRC="Line.Gif"></CENTER></A>
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<BR>
The Media Management environment allows users to track and control the allocation, usage, location, expiration, and cycling of all media volumes and savesets.  It assists users by increasing productivity and professionalism in an era of downsizing and tight budgets.

<P>
An important feature of Media Management is the saveset information.  In StorageCenter, a saveset is a backup of files written to a volume.  The Media Management saveset information tracks the expiration date of each saveset on a volume.  You can view a list of all the savesets in the database on the Saveset window.  This information is valuable for modifying saveset expiration dates, deleting savesets, performing saveset cleanups, and scratching volumes.  

<BR>
<BR>
<H2><CENTER>Saveset</CENTER></H2>

<A><CENTER>
<IMG SRC="savesetmm.gif" HSPACE=4>
</CENTER></A>

<BR>
<BR>
<H3>Other key features of the Media Management environment:</H3>


<H4>
<A><IMG SRC="ballred.gif"</A>
 generates reports on media status
</H4>

<H4>
<A><IMG SRC="ballred.gif"</A>
 defines access control list for each saveset
</H4>

<H4>
<A><IMG SRC="ballred.gif"</A>
 tracks volume cycling to multiple locations, and
</H4>

<H4>
<A><IMG SRC="ballred.gif"</A>
 performs cleanups of database information.
</H4>

<BR>
<P>
<CENTER>
<A HREF="backup.html">Continue the StorageCenter demo<IMG SRC="arrow.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE HSPACE=4></A>
</CENTER>

<br>
