<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> Backup </TITLE>
<H1><CENTER>
<A><IMG SRC="backup.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE HSPACE=4 HEIGHT=75 WIDTH=75></A>
StorageCenter Backup</CENTER></H1>
<A><CENTER><IMG SRC="Line.Gif"></CENTER></A>
</HEAD>

<BODY>
<BR>

The Backup environment allows you to perform full, incremental, or selective backups of your company's data. The StorageCenter Browsers help you easily locate and specify the files or directories you want to include in your backup. 

<P>
Another powerful feature of the StorageCenter Backup environment is History. Histories make it easier for you to search for backup records when you want to restore files. The history database ensures that StorageCenter will keep detailed logs of all files backed up in a particular saveset.

<P>
Also, with Backup you can make copies of your backups (savesets) for off-site storage by using the Saveset Copy feature.  


<H2><CENTER>Backup</CENTER></H2>

<A><CENTER><IMG SRC="backupjobwin.gif" HSPACE=4></CENTER></A>

<H3>Other important features of the Backup environment:</H3>


<H4>
<A><IMG SRC=" ballpurple.gif"</A>
appends multiple backup jobs to a single volume, or 
</H4>

<H4>
<A><IMG SRC=" ballpurple.gif"</A>
spans large backups across multiple volumes
</H4>


<H4>
<A><IMG SRC="ballpurple.gif"</A>
maintains a detailed audit trail
</H4>


<H4>
<A><IMG SRC=" ballpurple.gif"</A>
reports job errors via e-mail or pager
</H4>


<H4>
<A><IMG SRC=" ballpurple.gif"</A>
stores data in standard tar or cpio format, and
</H4>


<H4>
<A><IMG SRC=" ballpurple.gif"</A>
encrypts data for security using RSA algorithms.
</H4>

<P>
To set up a backup you must define a work order detailing the parameters of the backup. Next, you will view some of the information you can define in a backup work order.

<BR>
<P>
<CENTER>
<A HREF="backupwo.html">Continue the StorageCenter demo<IMG SRC="arrow.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE HSPACE=4></A>
</CENTER>

<br>
<BR>
