<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> Archiving </TITLE>
<H1><CENTER>
<A><IMG SRC="archive.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE HSPACE=4 HEIGHT=75 WIDTH=75></A>
StorageCenter Archiving
</CENTER></H1>
<A><CENTER><IMG SRC="Line.Gif"></CENTER></A>
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<BR>
The Archiving environment provides rational and controlled methods for migrating files from limited disk space to virtually limitless off-line media.  There are two methods you can use to archive your files:  Groom and Make-Space.

<P>
The Groom feature allows the administrator to remove files using criteria such as "not accessed in 90 days" or "having a 'tmp' extension."  The Make-Space feature is also driven by user specified criteria, but removes just enough files to meet your goal of free space.  

<P>
StorageCenter removes files from disk by using delete or shelve strategies.  "Delete" permanently removes unneeded files from disk, while "Shelve" moves files to tape and leaves a marker on the disk pointing to the archive location.  Shelving provides the means to systematically remove inactive data from valuable disk storage while still keeping it accessible for quick and convenient retrieval.  

<BR>
<BR>
<H2><CENTER>Archiving</CENTER></H2>

<A><CENTER>
<IMG SRC="archivewin.gif" HSPACE=4>
</CENTER></A>

<H3>Other key features of the Archiving environment:</H3>

<P>

<H4>
<A><IMG SRC="ballaqua.gif"</A> supports wildcards and other selection criteria
</H4>

<H4>
<A><IMG SRC="ballaqua.gif"</A>
uses file markers for automatic retrieval of shelved files
</H4>

<H4>
<A><IMG SRC="ballaqua.gif"</A>
analyzes archive outcome prior to performing the archive, and
</H4>

<H4>
<A><IMG SRC="ballaqua.gif"</A>
alerts file owners of pending migration via e-mail.
</H4>

<BR>
To set up an archive work order, you must first define the strategy you want to use for selecting archive files.  Next, you will view an example of a strategy.

<BR>
<P>
<CENTER>
<A HREF="archstrategy.html">Continue the StorageCenter demo<IMG SRC="arrow.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE HSPACE=4></A>
</CENTER>

<br>
<BR>
