<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Automatic Backups Run Off-Hours with SafetyPosit(sm)</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#E6E8FA" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#FF0000">
<IMG SRC="/gifs/logo_and_tagline.gif">
<IMG SRC="/gifs/Line.gif" WIDTH=100%>
<BR>
<CENTER>
<H2>Automatic Backups Run Off-Hours</H3>
</CENTER>
<BR>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=5>S</FONT>afetyPosit allows you to schedule your backup jobs 
to run on any schedule you set.  Perhaps the most common schedule would be to 
run <A HREF="primer.html #3">incremental backups</A> each weekday at the same 
time.  This would normally be after the close of business when there is 
minimal computer and network usage.  You can also schedule a periodic <A HREF=
"primer.html #1">full backup</A> or partial <A HREF="primer.html #5">
consolidation backup</A>.  These are typically done over the weekend on a 
weekly or monthly basis.</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=5>W</FONT>ith some backup systems, there is a need to be present 
when the backup is running.  This might be to change tapes or make sure the 
job completes.  With SafetyPosit electronic vaulting, you are backing up to 
a virtual tape that can't jam or run out of space.  SafetyPosit insures that 
your backups are completed and automatically restarts a job if it is 
interrupted before completion.  Because SafetyPosit is reliable and 
automatic, you can schedule it to run when you're not there.  This keeps 
backup jobs from conflicting with normal usage during business hours.</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=5>S</FONT>afetyPosit does not require that you run it on a regular 
schedule.  If your system usage is irregular, you may want to perform backups 
on demand, rather than on schedule.  SafetyPosit supports on demand backups.
</P>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=5>O</FONT>ne of the most important automation features of 
SafetyPosit is that it creates your off-site vault tapes as part of the 
backup process.  This is a tremendous labor savings over traditional off-site 
vault methods that require very careful labeling, sorting, and handling of 
tapes.  Off-site vaulting can go on automatically even when the systems 
administrator is out sick or on vacation. Since SafetyPosit uses RSA 
encryption and digital signatures, your off-site data is completely private 
and can't be accessed by an impostor, which makes it safer than most tape 
based vaulting methods.</P>
<BR><BR>
<HR>
<BR><BR>
