<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>No More Piles of Tapes or Diskettes with SafetyPosit(sm)</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#E6E8FA" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#FF0000">
<IMG SRC="/gifs/logo_and_tagline.gif">
<IMG SRC="/gifs/Line.gif" WIDTH=100%>
<BR>
<CENTER>
<H2>No More Piles of Tapes or Diskettes</H3>
</CENTER>
<BR>
<P><FONT SIZE=5>T</FONT>raditional backup methods involve the use of tape or 
some other removable media.  After a few rounds of backup, a pile of tapes 
can begin to grow and grow.  The toughest part of backup becomes keeping the 
tapes properly labeled and cataloged and figuring out when to reuse them.  
Some backup software packages (including our own <A HREF="/StorageCenter.html">
StorageCenter</A> suite) include Media Management modules to assist data 
center managers in professionally organizing their library of tapes.  
Nonetheless, many users don't want to be tape librarians and would 
welcome a tool that automates the media management function for them.  
SafetyPosit does just that.
</P>

<P><FONT SIZE=5>W</FONT>ith SafetyPosit you never even see a tape and do not 
need to worry about having enough tapes or cleaning and reusing them.  Our 
SafetyPosit vault is professionally managed and we take care of all media 
management issues for our users.  Every backup you send us will have your 
assigned expiration date, typically around 40 days.  This allows you to keep 
all backups available until a new <A HREF="primer.html #1">full backup</A> or 
<A HREF="primer.html #5">consolidation backup</A> has been made.  SafetyPosit 
offers all the protection and benefits of professional media management 
without any of the headaches.</P>

<BR><BR>
<HR>
<BR><BR>
