<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Secure off-site storage with SafetyPosit(sm)</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#E6E8FA" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#FF0000">
<IMG SRC="/gifs/logo_and_tagline.gif">
<IMG SRC="/gifs/Line.gif" WIDTH=100%>
<BR>
<CENTER>
<H2>Secure Off-site Storage</H3>
</CENTER>
<BR>
<P><FONT SIZE=5>O</FONT>ne of the major oversights of many backup plans is 
failure to provide for adequate off-site backups.  Sometimes the backup tapes 
are kept in the same room as the system they are backing up.  This can be a 
disaster in the case of fire, theft, etc.  One home PC user entered her home 
only to find that her PC had been stolen.  She breathed a temporary sigh of 
relief when she realized that she had recently made backup diskettes.  The 
relief was short lived when she noticed that the burglar had taken her box of 
diskettes too! 
</P>
<P><FONT SIZE=5>T</FONT>his problem is not limited to home PC users.  When a 
bomb explosion forced the evacuation the World Trade Center, many IS 
professionals had to carry their backup tapes down 80 flights of stairs.  
Many others didn't even have a recent backup to carry out.  Ideally, your 
current data should already be off-site when a disaster strikes.  Automatic 
off-site backup is a built in advantage of SafetyPosit.</P>

<P><FONT SIZE=5>M</FONT>ost other off-site tape storage services involve many 
manual steps.  First the tapes are made, then assembled in a shipping carton, 
then left on the front stoop or in the lobby, then picked up by a courier in 
a truck with lots of other customers' tapes, then checked into a warehouse 
storage location.  Finally this process reverses when the tapes expire or you 
need one for restore.  The obvious problem is that data is at risk with each 
of the manual handling steps.</P>

<P><FONT SIZE=5>B</FONT>y contrast, with SafetyPosit your data is never 
manually handled and never at risk of accidental disclosure.  SafetyPosit 
incorporates powerful security technology from RSA Data Security, Inc. a 
leader in commercial data security. SafetyPosit <A HREF="primer.html #6">
encrypts</A> your data using RSA's 128 bit encryption key before it ever 
leaves your host system.  This insures that your data cannot be read by 
anyone else.  To further protect your data, SafetyPosit uses RSA 
<A HREF="primer.html #6.1">node authentication</A> to prevent an impostor 
from accessing our backup system.  Node authentication incorporates a 1024 
digit public/private key system as a digital signature to verify that every 
user who attempts to access SafetyPosit really is who he claims to be.</P>

<P><FONT SIZE=5>T</FONT>he SafetyPosit off-site <A HREF=
"/SafetyPosit/SP_secure.html">secure storage vault</A> is a concrete storage 
bunker with no windows, controlled access, and advanced security alarm and 
fire suppression system.  It is protected from electrical power interruptions 
by an Uninterruptible Power Supply (UPS) and a natural gas powered backup 
generator.</P>

<BR><BR>
