<HEAD>
<TITLE>SafetyPosit(sm) Advantages</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<IMG SRC="/gifs/logo_and_tagline.gif">
<IMG SRC="/gifs/Line.gif" WIDTH=100%>
<BR>
<CENTER>
<H2>What are the advantages over conventional tape backup?</H2>
</CENTER>
<BR>
<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER=1>
<TR>
<TH WIDTH=200>Tape Backup</TH>
<TH WIDTH=200>SafetyPosit</TH></TR>

<TR>
<TD>Requires expensive, single purpose hardware, namely a tape drive.</TD>
<TD>We provide all necessary hardware at our storage center.  You don't waste a
single minute shopping for a tape drive.</TD></TR>

<TR>
<TD>Requires installing and configuring complex hardware and software.</TD>
<TD>We provide the software as well as expert advice and assistance as you 
get ready to perform your first backups.</TD></TR>

<TR>
<TD>Requires purchasing, labeling, storing, and cataloging a library full of 
tapes.  You become a tape librarian and must load tapes as needed.</TD>
<TD>We perform all media management functions.  With on-line direct access, you
never even need to see or handle a tape.</TD></TR>

<TR>
<TD>Requires many manual steps to create and send tapes to off-site storage.  
High potential for confusion and mix ups.</TD>
<TD>Through the magic of electronic vaulting, off-site backups occur 
automatically, even if you're on a two week vacation!!</TD></TR>

<TR>
<TD>Competes with higher visibility projects for limited resources.</TD>
<TD>Uses the Internet connection you already have during hours when no one else
would be using it anyhow.</TD></TR> 

<TR>
<TD>May require a trip to the data center to load a tape for restoral.</TD>
<TD>With the proper password and decryption key, you can request a restoral 
from anywhere on your network</TD></TR> 

<TR>
<TD>Restores start after the tape has been loaded.</TD>
<TD>Restores start immediately upon request.</TD></TR> 

<TR>
<TD>Unencrypted tapes are an invitation to data security and privacy problems.
</TD><TD>
SafetyPosit encrypts all data before transmission.  Only you can read your 
data.</TD>
</TD></TR> 
</TABLE>
<CENTER>
