<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> Backup Work Order</TITLE>

<H1><CENTER>
<A><IMG SRC="backup.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE HSPACE=4 HEIGHT=75 WIDTH=75></A>
StorageCenter Backup</CENTER></H1>
<A><CENTER><IMG SRC="Line.Gif"></CENTER></A><BR>

</HEAD>
<BODY>
StorageCenter uses a Backup Work Order to collect all of the information (parameters) it will need to perform your backup successfully.  The backup work order gives you the opportunity to be specific and creative when defining backup information.   

<P>
In the dialog boxes below you can see that Backup offers a variety of options including type of backup, history database, volume pool and device information, and backup saveset format.  Each of these options allow flexibility and adaptability in your backups.

<H2><CENTER>Backup Work Order</CENTER></H2>

<A><IMG SRC="backwo2.gif" HSPACE=4></A>
<BR>

<P>
Next, you will view information about the Restore environment.

<BR>
<P>
<CENTER>
<A HREF="restore.html">Continue the StorageCenter demo<IMG SRC="arrow.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE HSPACE=4></A>
</CENTER>

<br>
