<DOCOLDNO>IA027-000288-B001-2</DOCOLDNO>
<DOCHDR>
http://bh1.storagecenter.com:80/demo/archstrategy.html 206.214.152.4 19970114013204 text/html 2447
HTTP/1.0 200 OK
Server: Netscape-Commerce/1.1
Date: Tuesday, 14-Jan-97 01:27:49 GMT
Last-modified: Thursday, 20-Jun-96 20:04:07 GMT
Content-length: 2262
Content-type: text/html
</DOCHDR>
<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE> Archiving Strategy</TITLE>
<H1><CENTER>
<A><IMG SRC="archive.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE HSPACE=4 HEIGHT=75 WIDTH=75></A>
StorageCenter Archiving
</CENTER></H1>
<A><CENTER><IMG SRC="Line.Gif"></CENTER></A>
</HEAD>

<BODY>

<BR>
StorageCenter uses a Strategy to help search for files you want to archive.  In your strategy, you can choose to delete or shelve files using the standard UNIX find, ls or cat utilities, and a complete list of pre-defined criteria selection buttons.  When you run the Archive Work Order, StorageCenter will reference the strategy to locate the file(s) you want to archive.

<P>
Also, when defining your archive, you can select the Analyze Only mode which will run the archive work order and report the results without actually archiving any files.  This feature is great if you want to first analyze the files that will be affected when you run the archive in Normal mode.  If the results are not what you want, just change the strategy and try again.

<BR>
<BR>
<CENTER>
<H2>
Archiving Strategy and Work Order
</H2>
</CENTER>

<A><CENTER>
<IMG SRC="archstratgr.gif" HSPACE=4>
</CENTER></A>

<P>
The list below describes each of the strategy lines in the dialog box.

<UL>
<LI>
"Delete ls *.tmp"  - deletes files with a .tmp extension
</LI>

<LI>
"Delete find name eq weekly_report" - deletes a file named weekly_report
</LI>

<LI>
"Shelve find atime gt 6M" - shelves files that have not been accessed in over six months
</LI>

<LI>
"Shelve find group eq students" - shelves all files belonging to the group named "students"
</LI>
</UL>

<BR>
<P>
<CENTER>
<A HREF="jobcalendar.html">Continue the StorageCenter demo<IMG SRC="arrow.gif" ALIGN=MIDDLE HSPACE=4></A>
</CENTER>

<br>
