<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>SafetyPosit(sm) for Professional Offices</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#E6E8FA" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#FF0000">
<IMG SRC="/gifs/logo_and_tagline.gif">
<IMG SRC="/gifs/Line.gif" WIDTH=100%>
<BR>
<CENTER>
<H2>SafetyPosit(sm) for Professional Offices</H2>
</CENTER>
<BR><BR>
<P>
<B>Problem</B>:  professionals such as accountants, architects, consultants, dentists, doctors, graphic artists, insurance agents, lawyers, programmers, etc. have become increasingly dependent upon computers for managing information and
finances.  Along with this dependence comes an increasing responsibility to
assure that irreplaceable data is never lost.  Most small office computers do
not have tape drives for backups.  Even if they did, on-site backups are not
adequate protection for catastrophes like burglaries, fires, or earthquakes.  
Professionals should maintain off-site data backups.</P>
<P>
<B>Solution</B>:  is a service business, time is money, and SafetyPosit aims 
to save both.  SafetyPosit allows you to schedule unattended backups to run 
outside normal business hours, without a tape drive, and with a minimal time 
commitment from your staff.  SafetyPosit sends your irreplaceable files to 
our storage vault for safe keeping.  If you ever need to restore a lost file, 
SafetyPosit can download it in a few minutes.  Because SafetyPosit <A HREF=
"primer.html #6">encrypts</A> your files before they leave your PC, you 
maintain complete privacy.  You will have the only valid <A HREF=
"primer.html #6">encryption key</A> and no one else can read your data.  With 
SafetyPosit, you will be able to do an initial <A HREF="primer.html #1">
full backup</A> and then refresh this with periodic <A HREF="primer.html #3">
incremental backups</A> and <A HREF="primer.html #5">consolidation backups
</A>.</P>
<P>
<B>System Requirements</B>:<BR><BR><UL><UL>
<LI><A HREF="SP_windows_NT.html">Windows NT</A></LI><BR><BR>
<LI><A NAME>Windows 95 (available mid-1997)</A></LI><BR><BR>
<LI><A HREF="SP_unix.html">UNIX</A></LI><BR><BR>
</UL></UL></P><BR><BR>
<P>
<B>Communications Options</B>:  via the <A HREF="primer.html #9">Internet</A>
and<BR><BR><UL><UL>
<LI><A HREF="primer.html #10">Dial modem</A></LI><BR><BR>
<LI><A HREF="primer.html #11">ISDN</A></LI><BR><BR>
<LI><A HREF="primer.html #12">Dedicated access</A></LI><BR><BR>
<LI><A HREF="primer.html #13">Cable modem</A></LI><BR><BR>
<LI><A HREF="primer.html #14">ADSL</A></LI><BR><BR>
</UL></UL></P><BR><BR>
<P>
<B>Pricing</B>:  <A HREF="SP_pricing.html">Usage fees</A>.</P> 
<P>
<B>Register</B>:  SafetyPosit is currently available for Windows NT and UNIX.  
Windows 95 will be supported in mid-1997.  SafetyPosit is not available for 
Windows 3.1, MAC OS, or Novell at this time.  If would like to 
be notified when SafetyPosit is available for any of these operating systems 
or if you would like to be considered for Beta Testing (user validation 
testing), please <A HREF="/SafetyPosit/sp_register.html">register</A>.
</P>

