<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>SafetyPosit(sm) for Small Business Users</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#E6E8FA" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#FF0000">
<IMG SRC="/gifs/logo_and_tagline.gif">
<IMG SRC="/gifs/Line.gif" WIDTH=100%>
<BR>
<CENTER>
<H2>SafetyPosit(sm) for Small Business Users</H2>
</CENTER>
<BR>
<P>

<B>Problem</B>:  most small business depend on their computers for order entry,
inventory management, invoicing, and general ledger.  In addition, functions
such as sales, marketing, product development, and production increasingly rely
on PCs.  Along with this dependence on computers comes an increased need to
insure that irreplaceable data is never lost.  Computer management is 
frequently an "extra duty" for an employee that wears many other hats.  It 
may be unrealistic to expect part time computer managers to become proficient 
at tape backups.  Even if they did, on-site backups are not adequate 
protection for catastrophes like burglaries, vandalism, fires, or 
earthquakes.  Small businesses should perform frequent data backups and 
maintain up to date copies at an off-site location.</P>
<P>
<B>Solution</B>:  SafetyPosit is both a data protection and productivity tool.
  It allows you to schedule unattended backups to run outside of normal 
business hours without a tape drive and with a minimal time commitment from 
your staff.  Using the Internet, SafetyPosit sends your irreplaceable files to 
our storage vault for safe keeping.  If you ever need to restore a lost file, 
SafetyPosit can download it in a few minutes.  Because SafetyPosit
<A HREF="primer.html #6">encrypts</A> your files before they leave your 
building, you maintain complete privacy.  You will have the only valid
<A HREF="primer.html #6">encryption key</A> and no one else can read your 
data.  With SafetyPosit, you will be able to do an initial <A HREF=
"primer.html #1">full backup</A> and then refresh this with periodic <A HREF=
"primer.html #3">incremental backups</A> and <A HREF="primer.html #5">
consolidation backups</A>.</P>

<P>
<B>System Requirements</B>:<BR><BR><UL><UL>
<LI><A HREF="SP_windows_NT.html">Windows NT</A></LI><BR><BR>
<LI><A NAME>Windows 95 (available mid-1997)</A></LI><BR><BR>
<LI><A HREF="SP_unix.html">UNIX</A></LI><BR><BR>
</UL></UL></P><BR><BR>
<P>
<B>Communications Options</B>:  via the <A HREF="primer.html #9">Internet</A>
and<BR><BR><UL><UL>
<LI><A HREF="primer.html #10">Dial modem</A></LI><BR><BR>
<LI><A HREF="primer.html #11">ISDN</A></LI><BR><BR>
<LI><A HREF="primer.html #12">Dedicated access</A></LI><BR><BR>
<LI><A HREF="primer.html #13">Cable modem</A></LI><BR><BR>
<LI><A HREF="primer.html #14">ADSL</A></LI><BR><BR>
</UL></UL></P><BR><BR>
<P>
<B>Pricing</B>:  <A HREF="SP_pricing.html">Usage fees</A>.</P>
<P>
<B>Register</B>:  SafetyPosit is currently available for Windows NT and UNIX.
Windows 95</A> will be supported in mid-1997.  SafetyPosit is not available 
for Windows 3.1, MAC OS, or Novell at this time.  If would like to 
be notified when SafetyPosit is available for any of these operating systems 
or if you would like to be considered for Beta Testing (user validation 
testing), please <A HREF="/SafetyPosit/sp_register.html">register</A>.
</P>
<BR><BR>
