<HEAD>
<TITLE>SafetyPosit(sm) for Departments or Regional Offices</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#E6E8FA" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#FF0000">
<IMG SRC="/gifs/logo_and_tagline.gif">
<IMG SRC="/gifs/Line.gif" WIDTH=100%>
<BR>
<CENTER>
<H2>SafetyPosit(sm) for Departments or Regional Offices</H2>
</CENTER>
<BR>
<P>
<B>Problem</B>:  in today's distributed computing environment, many 
departments and
regional offices within large organizations are on their own when it comes to
backing up their data.  Your data is just as essential to the mission as data
generated elsewhere, but your resources for backing up your data files may be
very limited.  After all, you want your sales reps to sell and engineers to
design.  Any time spent on computer administration is overhead that detracts
from your mission.  Nonetheless, you're performance and reputation will be in
jeopardy if you loose valuable data.  What's a department or office manager to
do?</P>

<B>Solution</B>:  SafetyPosit is data protection and productivity tool.  
SafetyPosit allows you to schedule unattended backups to run outside normal 
business hours without a tape drive and with a minimal time commitment from 
your staff.  SafetyPosit sends your irreplaceable files to our storage vault 
for safe keeping.  If you ever need to restore a lost file, SafetyPosit can 
download it in a few minutes.  Because SafetyPosit <A HREF="primer.html #6">
encrypts</A> your files before they leave your PC, you maintain complete 
privacy.  You will have the only valid <A HREF="primer.html #6">encryption 
key</A> and no one else can read your data.  With SafetyPosit, you will be 
able to do an initial <A HREF="primer.html #1">full backup</A> and then 
refresh this with periodic <A HREF="primer.html #3">incremental backups</A>
and <A HREF="primer.html #5">consolidation backups</A>.</P>
<P>
<B>System Requirements</B>:<BR><BR><UL><UL>
<LI><A HREF="SP_windows_NT.html">Windows NT</A></LI><BR><BR>
<LI><A NAME>Windows 95 (available mid-1997)</A></LI><BR><BR>
<LI><A HREF="SP_unix.html">UNIX</A></LI><BR><BR>
</UL></UL></P><BR><BR>
<P>

<B>Communications Options</B>:  via the <A HREF="primer.html #9">Internet</A>
and<BR><BR><UL><UL>
<LI><A HREF="primer.html #10">Dial modem</A></LI><BR><BR>
<LI><A HREF="primer.html #11">ISDN</A></LI><BR><BR>
<LI><A HREF="primer.html #12">Dedicated access</A></LI><BR><BR>
<LI><A HREF="primer.html #19">Other</A></LI><BR><BR>
</UL></UL></P><BR><BR>
<P>
<B>Pricing</B>:  <A HREF="SP_pricing.html">Usage fees</A>.</P>
<P>
<B>Register</B>:  SafetyPosit is currently available for
Windows NT and UNIX.  Windows 95 will be supported in mid-1997.
SafetyPosit is not available for Windows 3.1, MAC OS, or Novell 
at this time.  If you would like to be notified when SafetyPosit is 
available for any of these operating systems or if you would like to be 
