<HEAD>
<TITLE>SafetyPosit(sm) for Corporate Data Centers</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#E6E8FA" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#FF0000">
<IMG SRC="/gifs/logo_and_tagline.gif">
<IMG SRC="/gifs/Line.gif" WIDTH=100%>
<BR>
<CENTER>
<H2>SafetyPosit(sm) for Corporate Data Centers</H2>
</CENTER>
<BR>
<P>

<B>Problem</B>:  most corporate data centers have the hardware, software, and 
staff necessary to perform regular tape backups for gigabytes of data per data.
Nonetheless, other challenges remain. For any large data center, maintaining 
emergency off-site backups is both a practical necessity and a fiduciary 
responsibility.  However, the most common methods of performing off-site 
backups are themselves risky.</P>
<P>
A common off-site storage arrangement involves sending unencrypted tapes to a
third party storage location.  As part of the pickup process, the tapes
frequently change hands and are sometimes left unattended.  A risk of mixing
your confidential tapes with your competitor's or other third party tapes 
always exists.</P>
<P>
<B>Solution</B>:  SafetyPosit is data protection and productivity tool.  
SafetyPosit allows you to schedule unattended backups to run outside normal
business hours without a tape drive and with a minimal time commitment from 
your staff.  SafetyPosit sends your irreplaceable files to our storage vault 
for safe keeping.  If you ever need to restore a lost file, SafetyPosit can 
download it in a few minutes.  Because SafetyPosit <A HREF="primer.html #6">
encrypts</A> your files before they leave your PC, you maintain complete 
privacy.  You will have the only valid <A HREF="primer.html #6">encryption key
</A> and no one else can read your data.  With SafetyPosit, you will be able to
do an initial <A HREF="primer.html #1">full backup</A> and then refresh this 
with periodic <A HREF="primer.html #3">incremental backups</A> and <A HREF=
"primer.html #5">consolidation backups</A>.</P>
<P>
<B>System Requirements</B>:<BR><BR><UL><UL>
<LI><A HREF="SP_windows_NT.html">Windows NT</A></LI><BR><BR>
<LI><A NAME>Windows 95 (available mid-1997)</A></LI><BR><BR>
<LI><A HREF="SP_unix.html">UNIX</A></LI><BR><BR>
</UL><BR><BR>
<P>
<B>Communications Options</B>:  via the <A HREF="primer.html #9">Internet</A> 
and<BR><BR><UL><UL>
<LI><A HREF="primer.html #11">ISDN</A></LI><BR><BR>
<LI><A HREF="primer.html #12">Dedicated access</A></LI><BR><BR>
<LI><A HREF="primer.html #19">Other</A></LI><BR><BR>
</UL></UL></P><BR><BR>
<P>
<B>Pricing</B>:  <A HREF="SP_pricing.html">Usage fees</A>.</P>
<P>
<B>Register</B>:  SafetyPosit is currently available for
Windows NT and UNIX.  Windows 95 will be supported in mid-1997.
SafetyPosit is not available for Windows 3.1, MAC OS, or Novell
at this time.  If would like to be notified when SafetyPosit is available
for any of these operating systems or if you would like to be considered for
Beta Testing (user validation testing), please 
<A HREF="/SafetyPosit/sp_register.html">
register</A>. 
</P>
<BR><BR>
