<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>SafetyPosit Licensee Program</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#E6E8FA" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#FF0000">

<IMG SRC="/gifs/logo_and_tagline.gif">
<IMG SRC="/gifs/Line.gif" WIDTH=100%>
<CENTER><H1>SafetyPosit Licensee Program</H1></CENTER>

<P>
<B>Program Description -</B>  this program provides everything necessary for an
ISP/OSP to set up and operate an electronic storage vault.  Software Partners
provides backup software as well as hardware and facilities recommendations,
operating policies and procedures, consulting services and training so an
ISP/OSP can set up and operate a storage vault.  Software Partners has over 13
years of experience in providing software and consulting to major data centers
and has incorporated many valuable "lessons learned" into the Licensee Program.
For an ISP/OSP looking to minimize the up front cost of offering an electronic
vaulting service, Software Partners also offers the SafetyPosit Reseller
Program.  The Reseller Program authorizes an ISP/OSP to offer SafetyPosit 
backup to a storage Vault operated by Software Partners.  The reseller has 
an option to convert to licensee status in the future.
<P>
<B>Software Partners' Responsibilities -</B>  under this program Software
Partners would:
<UL>
<LI>provide an initial trial period during which the ISP/OSP or end user could
send backups to Software Partners' storage vault as a validation test</LI>
<LI>provide all software necessary for performing backup, restore, archiving,
and media management</LI>
<LI>provide recommendations on the hardware and facilities required</LI>
<LI>provide an operations manual with policy and procedures 
recommendations</LI>
<LI>provide up to two weeks consulting and training to help ISP/OSP staff set 
up and operate a storage vault</LI>
<LI>assist ISP/OSP in preparing marketing materials and programs</LI>
<LI>help train the ISP/OSP sales staff</LI>
<LI>provide second tier technical support</LI>
<LI>provide end user referrals on a non-exclusive regional basis
</UL>
<P>
<B>ISP/OSP Responsibilities -</B>  Under this program the ISP/OSP would:
<UL>
<LI>operate a SafetyPosit storage vault in accordance with standards specified
in the license agreement</LI>
<LI>offer SafetyPosit to their entire user base</LI>
<LI>consider offering a SafetyPosit stand alone option</LI>
<LI>incorporate SafetyPosit into their marketing materials and advertising</LI>
<LI>ensure sales staff is capable of selling the SafetyPosit service</LI>
<LI>provide first tier technical support to their end users</LI>
</UL>
<P>
<B>Commissions and fees -</B>  the following describes the financial 
arrangement between Software Partners and ISP/OSP:
<UL>
<LI>the initial one time enrollment fee for an ISP/OSP is $25,000 which 
includes all software and consulting services</LI>
<LI>end users will be billed by the ISP/OSP at the recommended end user pricing
or other mutually agreed pricing structure</LI>
<LI>ISP/OSP will pay Software Partners a royalty of 10% of revenues billed</LI>
<LI>ISP/OSP pays royalties within 40 days of billing end users</LI>
<LI>the minimum monthly royalty payment from ISP/OSP to SoftwarePartners 
negotiable based on size of ISP/OSP customer base.</LI>
</UL>

<P>
<B>Contact - </B>for more information on this program, or if you have
additional questions, please write to
<A HREF="mailto:bobn@softwarepartners.com">
bobn@softwarepartners.com</A>
<BR><BR>

