<HEAD>
<TITLE>SafetyPosit(sm) System Requirements for Windows NT</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#E6E8FA" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#FF0000">
<IMG SRC="/gifs/logo_and_tagline.gif">
<IMG SRC="/gifs/Line.gif" WIDTH=100%>
<BR>
<CENTER>
<H2>SafetyPosit System Requirements for Windows NT</H3>
</CENTER>
<BR>
<P><FONT SIZE=5>T</FONT>his page discusses Windows NT system requirements for 
this version of SafetyPosit</P>
<HR>
<P><FONT SIZE=5>S</FONT>afetyPosit requires the follwing amount of free 
<B>disk space</B> to install the current version on Windows NT.<BR><BR>  
<UL><UL>
<LI>9MB for SafetyPosit, and</LI>
<LI>7.5MB for NuTCRACKER</LI>
</UL></UL></P><BR><BR>

<HR>
<P><FONT SIZE=5>T</FONT>he following table lists the requirements for running 
the SafetyPosit Graphical User Interface (GUI) and Command Line Interface 
(CLI).
<BR><BR>
<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER=1>

<TR>
<TH>User Interface</TH><TH>Requirements</TH>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>Graphical User Interface  (GUI)</TD>
<TD>Uses NuTCRACKER<FONT SIZE=-2>(TM)</FONT> running on
Windows NT to run the GUI.  
<BR><BR>
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>Command Line Interface (CLI)</TD>
<TD>To use the CLI, you must have an MS-DOS or NuTCRACKER<FONT SIZE=-2>(TM)
</FONT> window running on Windows NT.</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</CENTER>
</P>

<BR><BR>
<HR>
