<HEAD>
<TITLE>SafetyPosit(sm) System Requirements for UNIX</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#E6E8FA" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#FF0000">
<IMG SRC="/gifs/logo_and_tagline.gif">
<IMG SRC="/gifs/Line.gif" WIDTH=100%>
<BR>
<CENTER>
<H2>SafetyPosit System Requirements for UNIX</H3>
</CENTER>
<BR>
<P><FONT SIZE=5>T</FONT>his page discusses UNIX system requirements for this 
version of SafetyPosit</P>
<HR>
<P><FONT SIZE=5>T</FONT>he <B>disk space</B> required by SafetyPosit is 
dependent upon several factors.  The following list will help you determine 
the amount of free space you will need to install SafetyPosit on your system.
<BR><BR><CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER=0>

<TR>
<TD>Hewlett-Packard HP-UX</TD><TD>10MB</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>Digital UNIX</TD><TD>13MB</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>SunOS</TD><TD>13MB</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>Sun Solaris</TD><TD>16MB</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>IBM AIX</TD><TD>12.5</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
<BR><BR>
</P>
<P>Also, 512 bytes per file backed backed up in the history database</P>
</CENTER>
<BR><BR>
<HR>
<P><FONT SIZE=5>T</FONT>he <B>interface</B> requirements are as follows:
<BR><BR>
<CENTER>
<TABLE BORDER=1>

<TR>
<TH>User Interface</TH><TH>Requirements</TH>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>Graphical User Interface  (GUI)</TD>
<TD>Bit-mapped terminals or workstations supporting
<UL><BR><BR>
<LI>OSF/Motif&174;, and</LI><BR><BR>
<LI>X Windows System(TM)  (X11R5)</LI>
</UL><BR><BR>
SunOS systems might not have Motif installed.<BR>
You can use Xwindow manager linked in SafetyPosit.</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>Command Line Interface (CLI)</TD>
<TD>Any supported terminal or workstation running<BR>
the UNIX operating system.</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</CENTER>


<BR><BR>
