<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>SafetyPosit Reseller Program</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#E6E8FA" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000FF" VLINK="#FF0000">

<IMG SRC="/gifs/logo_and_tagline.gif">
<IMG SRC="/gifs/Line.gif" WIDTH=100%>
<CENTER><H1>SafetyPosit Reseller Program</H1></CENTER>

<P>
<B>Program Description -</B>  this program allows an ISP/OSP to offer 
electronic vaulting to its client base very rapidly while minimizing the 
staffing, investment, and management attention required.  
Under this program, the reseller
markets the service to their end user accounts and also performs monthly
billing.  Software Partners operates the storage vault to receive and store
backups.  By eliminating the need for an ISP/OSP to set up their own storage
vault, this program offers the fastest time to market and the fastest path to
profitability.  Furthermore, Software Partners also offers a SafetyPosit
Licensee Program.  The reseller has an option to convert to licensee status in
the future when the ISP/OSP could profitably operate a storage vault with
an established subscriber base on day one.
<P>
<B>Software Partners' Responsibilities -</B>  under this program Software
Partners would:
<UL>
<LI>provide an initial trial period during which the ISP/OSP or end user could
send backups to Software Partners' as a validation test</LI>
<LI>make arrangement to receive backups from ISP/OSP's end users</LI>
<LI>assist ISP/OSP in preparing marketing materials and programs</LI>
<LI>help train the ISP/OSP sales staff</LI>
<LI>provide first or second tier technical support as selected by the
ISP/OSP</LI>
<LI>establish service and support policies and procedures</LI>
</UL>
<P>
<B>ISP/OSP Responsibilities -</B>  Under this program the ISP/OSP would:
<UL>
<LI>offer SafetyPosit to their entire user base</LI>
<LI>consider offering a SafetyPosit stand alone option</LI>
<LI>incorporate SafetyPosit into their marketing materials and advertising</LI>
<LI>ensure their sales staff is capable of selling the SafetyPosit service</LI>
<LI>establish service and support policies and procedures</LI>
</UL>
<P>
<B>Commissions and fees -</B>  the following describes the financial 
arrangement between Software Partners and ISP/OSP:
<UL>
<LI>the initial one time enrollment fee for an ISP/OSP is $5,000</LI>
<LI>users will be billed by ISP/OSP at the recommended end user pricing or 
other mutually agreed pricing structure</LI>
<LI>Software Partners will provide monthly usage statement, itemized by end
users, to support ISP/OSP billing activities</LI>
<LI>ISP/OSP will earn a commission equal to 25% of amounts billed to end users
plus a monthly administration fee of $2.50 per end user account</LI>
<LI>ISP/OSP pay amounts billed less commissions and fees within 40 days of
billing end users</LI>
<LI>the minimum monthly payment from ISP/OSP to SoftwarePartners negotiable 
based on size of ISP/OSP customer base.</LI>
</UL>

<P>
<B>Contact - </B>for more information on this program, or if you have 
additional questions, please write to 
<A HREF="mailto:bobn@softwarepartners.com">
bobn@softwarepartners.com</A>
<BR><BR> 

