<title>Nemzet 1996.06.01</title><BODY bgcolor="#ffffff" text="#000000"><h1>Nemzet 1996.06.01</h1><!-- body="start" --><pre>N     N  EEEEEEE  M     M  ZZZZZZZ  EEEEEEE  TTTTTTTNN    N  E        MM   MM       Z   E           TN N   N  E        M M M M      Z    E           TN  N  N  EEEE     M  M  M     Z     EEEE        TN   N N  E        M     M    Z      E           TN    NN  E        M     M   Z       E           TN     N  EEEEEEE  M     M  ZZZZZZZ  EEEEEEE     T--->> M A G Y A R   I N T E R N E T   V I L A G L A P <<---=="MI, MAGYAROK A NEMZETI ONTUDAT TULHANGULYOZASAVAL SOK KART OKOZTUNK AZ EMBERISEGNEK"  (Magyar Balint)[Szerkesztosegunk velemenye szerint aki ilyet mond, de ugyanakkor nem szegyelli nemzetunk nevet hasznalni, annak azonnali hatallyal vissza kellene valtoztatnia a nevet eredeti csaladnevukre. A becsuletes "Magyar" szo egy becstelen ember neveben a "Magyar" szo olyan tulhangsulyozasa, amellyel ez a mocskos alak kart okoz a magyarsagnak]CLUB OF BUDAPEST[Magyar Forum, majus 23][Talan inkabb "Budapest Banda"-nak kellene nevezni, a szerk.]Ismeretes, hogy a Romai Klub 1960 ota a vilag legkivalobb tudosainak nemzetkozi szintere, mely evenkent ajanlasokat dolgoz ki a kormanyoknak a vilag alapveto gondjainak megoldasara (pl. ehinseg felszamolasa). Ennek mintajara (vagy talan ellensulyozasara?) jott letre a Budapest Klub is, amely a napokban Anglia, Belgium, Hollandia, Kanada, Nemetorszag, az USA es Magyarorszag reszvetelevel tartotta meg elso vilagtalalkozojat, het kulfoldi es hazai nagyvallalat jotekony tamogatasatol kiserve. Az eloadasoknak es filmvetiteseknek a Varban a Magyar Kultura Alapitvany szekhaza adott otthont, de ezeknek a szekhaz nevetol eltekintve semmi koze sem volt a magyar kulturahoz. A valosaghoz kozelallobb, stilusosabb lett volta, ha ezt a talalkozot pl. Jeruzsalemben rendezik meg. Nemcsak azert, mert egyetlen eloadas sem hangzott el magyarul, hanem mert a targykor es az eloadokszellemisege is idegen volt tolunk. E tenyen meg az sem enyhitett, hogy a megnyiton a Magyar Filharmonia Kamarazenekara, Yehudi Menuhin vezenyletevel feledhetetlen elmenykent adta elo Haydn 87. szimfoniajat."AZ ONZESTOL ES ELSZIGETELTSEGTOL AZ EGYUTTERZESEN AT A BELEELESIG: A MUVESZET ES SZELLEM SZEREPE ES FELELOSSEGE" cimmel tartott rendezveny eloadoi negy napon at meglehetosen kodos, olykor pedig megdobbento velemenyeknek adtak hangot. Szerintuk a mai civiklizacio az osszeomlas fele kozeleg. A tortenelemvegen jarunk. Spiritualis ugrasra van szukseg, hogy a tortenelem utani idobe jussunk. Ebben a klubban olyan szervezetek es emberek legyenek, akik ki akarnak lepni a jelen valosagabol. Tizenegyezer, enciklopediaba foglalt alapkerdes var megoldasra. A politika es a vallasok utan eljott a szellemiseg kora. A szellemisegrol vilagkonferenciat kell rendezni a dalai lama enokletevel, mivel emberi ertelemben folfoghatatlan, magasabb rendu -- transzcendens -- vilag fele tartunk. Krisztus es a profetak utjan az emberiseg nem jutott el a vegso igazsaghoz, az Igazsag Egyetemes Hazahoz. A vilagmindensegben a ter es az ido hataran majd globalis onmegvalositas lesz. A jelszo: gondolkodj es cselekedj globalisan! A festok torekedjenek a szinek segitsegevel minket ujszeruen kifejezni. A zenesz az igazsag vednoke: veszelyeztetett allatfaj... A ko is sugarzik, mintha elne. Egy kis kavicsban tudatossag van. Egy angol tanarno fenykepeket keszitett arrol, hogy az ideges gyereket a tenyereben szorongatott KO LELKISEGE megnyugtatta. Ahhoz, hogy aFold mennyorszagga valtozzek, nekunk vilagi polgarokka kell lennunk. A hadsereget le kell szerelnunk, a nemzeti erdekeket az egybekovacsolodott vilag kovetelmenyei ala kell rendelnunk -- mondtak --, mikozben korulottunk orak alatt kovacsolodik ujja a kisantant. Az ENSZ Egyesult Vilag Allamokka fejlesztesenek hirdetese jol egybecsengett a jelenlegi kormanyzopart kozelmultban is hallatott erolkodesevel: "...NEMZETKOZIVE-E-E-E LESZ HOLNAPRA A VILAG". A kereszteny vallasrol pozitiv ertelemben szo sem esett. Helyette a megfoghatatlan hit erejerol beszeltek.Ilyen es hasonlo bolcsessegek hangzottak el az eloadok szajharmonikazasatol, tapsatol, eneketol vagy futyulesetol kiserve. Hankiss Elemer a legelkepesztobb badarsagokat is nagyon erdekesnek, figyelemre meltonak nevezte, viszont negyszer belefojtotta a szot abba a hazai eloadoba, akinek szajan kicsuszott az "alliberalis" kifejezes. De mit is vartunk volna attol a vilagkonferenciatol, amelynek alaphangjat kulturank legfobb ore, Magyar Balint miniszter a sajat nevenek es beosztasanak meghazudtolasaval otperces megnyitojaban nemzetunk elkepeszto becsmerlesevel adta meg: "SAJNALATTAL KELL BEVALLANUNK, HOGY MI, MAGYAROK A NEMZETI ONTUDAT TULHANGULYOZASAVAL SOK KART OKOZTUNK AZ EMBERISEGNEK. KORMANYUNK IGYEKSZIK EZT JOVATENNI."A Club of Budapest rendezveny azt bizonyitotta, hogy nemcsak a toke, de "az egyetemes muveszet" szamara is erdektelen Magyarorszag mint nemzetallam, de foldrajzi kozpontkent egyre erosebb gyokeret ereszt a magyar talajba. Es meg ezek utan is van, aki nemzetunk jovojeert foloslegesen aggodalmaskodonak nevezi Csurka Istvant?S.J.==Csermely Peter      EGY PERC   [Demokrata 22]Neha a szotar veget is erdemes olvasgatni. X, xeno-: "gor., szoosszetetelek  elotagjakent az utotag idegen voltat jeloli, idegen-". A xenofobia, "beteges felelem az idegenektol", azokat a muzeumba illo emberpeldanyokat definialja, akik szamara az idegen nem okvetlenul szep. A xenologia, azaz idegentudomany meg nem szerepel a szotarban, pedig nyilvan orommel vezetik majd be azok, akik honapokig rohogtek a hungarologia, magyarsagtudomany kifejezesen. Ertelmezi viszont a konyv a xenomaniat, ami "korlatlan rajongas minden irant, ami kulfoldi, nem hazai". Sot, itt van a xenokracia, az "idegenuralom" is, amelynek jellegzetessegeit a kezikonyv nem reszletezi, igy ezen a teren talalgatasokra vagyunk utalva. A xenokracia kifejezes meglete mindenesetre bizonyitja, hogy a tortenelemben a jelenseg itt-ott mar elofordult. Ha ez Magyarorszagon bekovetkezik, ugy a tuleles termeszetes vagyatol vezerelve lapunk nevet surgosen Xenokratava valtoztatjuk. Ha lesz   eleg idonk.==Egyaltalan nem nagy ugyekCsucs alelnok penzugyekben zseni voltSESZTAK AGNES[Demokrata 22]Az alabbi tortenetekhez kommentar illene. Meg nemi moralizalas. Minek? Nem tortenhet itt mar akkora esemeny, ami felhaborodast vagy erkolcsi rosszallast valtana ki akarmelyikonkbol is.  Ahely egy jobbfajta lakotelep, ahova jobb emberek koltoztek vagy koltoznek. Az egyik uj lako osszes ablaka a haz elotti kertnek csufolt dzsuvara nezett. Vastag kutyaurulek, szemet, korhadt fadarabok,  rozsdas drotok, rothado tavalyi avar. Az uj lako aprohirdetes utjan szerzett egy idos kerteszt. A kertet  felastak, begyepeztek, ultettek bele nehany facskat, muskatlit, orokzoldeket. Vegul korbekeritettek a kutyak elol, es kifizettek a kerteszt. Jottek a tobbi kutyak...akarom mondani lakok: Mondja, ez a kozos koltsegbol lett? A mi penzunkbol? Minek kellett hozzanyulni a kerthez, most megbontottak az egyseget.     Miert kell maguknak streberkedni? Most hova vigyuk setalni Rexiket?....  Megfigyeltek, milyen harcos es szivos volt az elozo negy ev szabadelvu sajtoja? Talpig ellenzeki  vertben, mert ugymond, csak az ellenzeki sajtonak van letjogosultsaga. Tudtunk is mindenrol, a  kormanyulesek intimitasairol eppen ugy, mint Antall Jozsef fianak egyiptomi fotoalbumarol. A kormanynak - hirdettek - egy demokraciaban nem lehetnek titkai. A valasztok adojabol nem kolthetnek   semmit ellenorzes nelkul. Ami nagyon jol mukodott l994-ig. Meg azt is tudtuk, hogy a Radio alelnokenek mekkora a telefonszamlaja, vagy hogy a miniszterelnok korhazi koltsege mekkorara rug.  Mara nema csend. A kormanyulesekrol nem szivarog ki semmi, az ott tortentekhez semmi kozunk. A  szokimondo sajto hallgat. Horn Gyula miniszterelnokot sem kerdezi meg az igen targyilagos sajto, hogy  ki fizette azokat a gyogyszereket, amelyeket a NASA intezeteiben fejlesztettek ki, es amelyekkel ot is kezelik mostanaban kulfoldi orvos baratai.Azt mondja a munkaugyi miniszter: A papirokat a helyi tanacsokon lehet megkapni.Azt mondja az olvaso: Es akkor bementem a tizenharmadik keruleti partbizottsagra.Azt mondja a miniszterelnok: Minket felesleges ijesztegetni!.. (v.o. a szemeket kinyitani, az ajtot meg becsukani)    Azt mondja erre egy teves kollegam: Mi meg ezektol fogunk meghulyulni.A Radioban nem szabad hangosan beszelni, mert mar az is letiltassal jarhat. Csendben azert megsugjak,  hogy Csucs alelnok, ha nem is volt ideologusnak kituno, penzugyekben zseni volt. Haromszaznyolcvanmilliot hagyott a kasszaban MSZP-s utodjanak, Sziranyi Janosnak. Amit egy szuk csoport harom het alatt szetosztogatott egymas kozott. A Radioban - ma meg kozszolgalatinak is csak cinizmussal nevezheto intezmenyeben - ujabban nincs a hirekben magyar blokk. Van Kozel-Kelet,  Oroszorszag, Bosznia vagy Japan, de nem szerepel Magyarorszag, egyetlen esemenyevel sem. Ugy  tudjuk, a Magyar Radio arculattervezese cimen mar felvett valaki tobb mint egymillio forintot. Nyilvan a fenti ujitast is beleszamitottak.  Vegul ket kerdes. Ha letrehoztak volna a Horn Gyula fele Kozponti Nyomozohivatalt, nyomozati vagy ugyeszi szakaszaban tartananak a VICO-birodalom ugyeinek?   Ha Kormos Valeria egymaga kinyomozta szivos munkaval a VICO osszes lathato es lathatatlan  kapcsolatat, akkor minek ehhez szazmillios apparatus?==Mondjon le a tevealelnok?[Demokrata 22]A kozelmultban a parlamenti ellenzeki partok felszolitottak Horn Gyula  miniszterelnokot, hogy kezdemenyezze a koztarsasagi elnoknel Szekely Ferenc  ugyvezeto alelnok felmenteset, es az uj teveelnok megvalasztasaig vezesse  orszaggyulesi biztos az intezmenyt. Az ellenzeki partok tobbek kozott kifogasoljak,  hogy a teveben pazarlo gazdalkodas folyik, s a kozszolgalatisag sem ervenyesul. Ket  orszaggyulesi kepviselo, Lendvai Ildiko (MSZP) es Lanyi Zsolt (FKGP) mondja el velemenyet az ugyben.      Tisztazatlan ugyek      Lanyi Zsolt (FKGP)   LEXIKONLanyi Zsolt (1929) Szekelyudvarhelyen szuletett. 1964-ben a Szamviteli Foiskolan szerzett diplomat. Az 50-es evekben segedmunkaskent dolgozott. 1962-67: az Eromu Beruhazasi Vall. anyaggazdalkodasi csop.vez., 1967-86: a Pestvideki Gepgyar anyagellatasi oszt.vez., 1986-88: az Enta Kisszovetkezet eln., 1988-89: a Termoker Kft. uzletag-ig., 1989-tol nyugdijas. 1945-tol az FKGP tagja. Jelenleg a kisgazdak kepviselocsoportjanak sajtoszovivoje.    Szekely Ferenc tevealelnok felmentesenek kezdemenyezeset azert tartjuk indokoltnak, mert  neheziti a kuratorium munkajat, csak reszben hajlando atadni a teve altal kotott  szerzodesekrol szolo dokumentumokat. Most is kulsosokkel es kulfoldi ugyfelekkel kot elonytelen  szerzodeseket, s ezzel a mediatorveny vegrehajtasat is akadalyozza. Mindez tovabb sulyosbitja a teve  katasztrofalis anyagi helyzetet. Elkepzelheto, hogy Szekely Ferencnek vannak gyanus gazdasagi ugyei.  Ezekrol a kulonbozo folyosoi suttogasokbol ertesult az ellenzek, ezert tiszta vizet kell onteni a poharba, s  az altalunk kovetelt parlamenti biztos megvizsgalhatja, mennyi igaz a vadakbol. Az is kulonos, hogy  Szekely zsarolja a kormanypartokat, azt allitja: sokat tud, s ebbol szinten arra lehet kovetkeztetni, hogy  van valami osszefonodas kozte es a kormany kozott, ezert bannak vele kesztyus kezzel. A Magyar  Nemzetben a Vico-birodalomrol kozolt haromreszes sorozat anyagabol mindenesetre kierezheto bizonyos  osszefonodas Fenyo Janos es Szekely Ferenc, illetve Fenyo es a politikai elit kozott, ezert is lenne  szukseg a parlamenti biztosra, hogy tisztazza ezt a kerdest. Mindenesetre meglepoen gyorsan jelentek  meg a szinen olyan sajtocezarok, akikrol nem lehet tudni, csak sejteni, milyen tamogatok reven tudnak  olyan anyagi feltetelekhez jutni, amellyel ratelepedhetnek az egesz kozszolgalatisagra. Eleg gyakran  emlegetik Fenyo urat mediacsaszarkent, es bizony megvan ra a lehetosege, hogy maga ala gyuri a  mediat. Egyertelmu, hogy ma a mediaban es a sajtoban hatalmas gazdasagi erdekek mukodnek, s  bizonyos csoportok elonyhoz juttatasaert folyik a lobbyzas. A mediatorveny elfogadasa utan a kokemeny  erdekcsoportok kozott folyik a harc. A kozszolgalati mediaban tulsulyban van a liberalis SZDSZ, most  pedig az MSZP szeretne megszerezni a maga reszet. Az ellenzek viszont a kozszolgalati teve  megvalosulasaert kuzd, mert hatranyban van, foleg az FKGP, esetunkben a legkevesbe sem ervenyesul  az objektivitas. A sajtoszabadsag Magyarorszagon jelenleg egyaltalan nem teljes, a kulonbozo hatalmi es  gazdasagi korok nem hagyjak elni az ellenzeki sajtot. Nemcsak gazdasagilag, hanem erkolcsileg is  tamadjak. Tamas Gaspar Miklos hirhedt javaslata arrol, hogy a neki nem tetszo ujsagokat matricaval kell  leragasztani, es az ilyen organumokat arusito bodekat fel kell borogatni, a fasizmus kezdeti lepeseire  utalnak. Ennek ellenere a teveben meg kell teremteni a koz-szolgalatisagot, hiszen a lakossag adojabol  tartjak fenn. Kulonbozo gondolkodasu emberek laknak Magyarorszagon, s mindegyik nezetnek meg kell  kapnia a megfelelo musort. A nezoket kell kielegiteni, nem szabad egyoldalu kampanyokat folytatni,  ahogyan azt Szekely Ferenc uralma alatt latjuk a kormanypartiakkal kedelyesen beszelgeto riporterno  musoraiban.     Nincs mit kipakolni     Lendvai Ildiko (MSZP)     LEXIKON Lendvai Ildiko (1946) Debrecenben szuletett. Az ELTE   BTK magy.-tort. szakan 1969-ben, filozofiaszakan pedig   1974-ben szerzett diplomat. 1969-72: a Mora Ferenc   Gimn.tanara, 1972-74: a KATE filozofiaszakos   tanarsegede, 1974-81: a KISZ KB kult.oszt. munkatarsa,   majd vezetoje, kozben az Egeszsegugyi Foisk., SOTE   oktatoja, 1981-84. az MTA aspiransa. 1984-88: az   MSZMP KB tud., kozokt. es kult.oszt. munkatarsa, majd   oszt.vez.h. 1989-95 nyaraig a Gondolat Kiado igazgatoja.Azt hiszem, az ellenzeki partok direkt politikai megszolalasa, a mediumok vezetoinek es    musorszerkezetenek partoldalrol torteno kritikaja ellentmond a mediatorveny szellemenek.  Ezt a torvenyt kozos akarattal es az ellenzek tobbsegenek konstruktiv kozremukodesevel alkotta meg a  parlament, eppen azert, hogy a politikusok ne avatkozhassanak kozvetlenul bele a media szemelyi es  musorszerkesztesi ugyeibe. Megertenem, hogyha a tevekuratorium elnoksege - amelybe valamennyi part  delegalhatott tagot - szova tenne, ha ugy erezne, hogy Szekely Ferenc akadalyozza a munkajat, de azt  nem, hogy ismet csak a politikusok avatkoznak bele a media ugyeibe. Ellenzek e teren minden atmeneti  megoldast, atmeneti idore szolo uj vezetok megbizasat, egyetertek viszont a mediatorveny  meggyorsitasara vonatkozo javaslatokkal. Kozos erdekunk, hogy most mar palyazat utjan  megvalasztando elnokok keruljenek a media elere. Az biztos, hogy komoly gazdasagi erdekcsoportok  fognak harcba szallni a frekvenciapalyazatokon. Ez azonban a kozszolgalati mediat nem erinti. Ezert  ertelmezhetetlen szamomra az az ellenzeki vad, hogy a mediahaboru ma mar a kormanypartokkal  osszefonodott gazdasagi maffia es az ujsagiro szakma erdekcsoportjai kozott zajlik. Azt azonban en is  vallom: rendkivul fontos, hogy a kozszolgalati media, kulonosen a szemelyi kerdeseket illetoen tiszta  maradjon a kulonbozo gazdasagi erdekektol, politikai haboruktol. Epp ezert fogadtam aggodalommal az  ellenzeki sajtotajekoztaton elhangzottakat, hiszen a teveelnoki posztert palyazok egyiket tamadtak meg,  kozvetlenul a kuratoriumi dontesek elott. A kozszolgalati media fuggetlensege a kormanyparti es  ellenzeki politikusok kozos celja. A leghalvanyabb jelet sem ismerem annak, hogy az MSZP vagy az  SZDSZ a Vico-fele erdekeltseget tamogatta volna, peldaul a Nap-Tv-re, illetve a Radio-Teve ujsagra  vonatkozo uzleti torekveseiben. Ugyanigy arrol sem tudok, hogy Szekely Ferenc es Fenyo Janos kozott  valamilyen gazdasagi erdekeltseget feltetelezo kapcsolat lenne. Ha a kormanyhoz egyesek szerint allitolag  kotodo Fenyo Janos jogtalan lepesekhez folyamodna, akkor termeszetesen torvenyes uton kellene ezt  megakadalyozni, de nekem errol nincs tudomasom. Nem ertem, mire gondol az ellenzek, amikor azt  allitja, hogy Szekely Ferenc azzal zsarolja a kormanyt, hogy kipakol, ha levaltjak ot. Egyreszt semmifele  zsarolo nyilatkozatat nem olvastam, masreszt kerdezem: ugyan mar, mit pakolhatna ki? Politikai  ertelemben a sajto Magyarorszagon feltetlenul szabad, azokat a gazdasagi nehezsegeket azonban nem  sikerult megoldani, amelyek egy pluralis es tobbszinu sajto kiviragzasat akadalyozzak.Hatter  "Horn Gyula miniszterelnok kezdemenyezze a koztarsasagi elnoknel a Magyar Televizio ugyvezeto  alelnokenek, Szekely Ferencnek az azonnali hatallyal torteno felmenteset - koveteli az ot parlamenti  ellenzeki part. Egyuttal surgeti, hogy nevezzenek ki orszaggyulesi biztost, aki felugyelne a mediatorveny  megtartasat, s kezdemenyezik, hogy szamoljon be Kiss Elemer allamtitkar, illetve az APEH vezetoje,  Pitti Zoltan az Orszaggyules kulturalis bizottsaga ellenorzesi albizottsaganak. Az APEH-vezeto az  ellenzeki partok mediapolitikusainak egybehangzo velemenye szerint tudatosan elszabotalja az MTV-vel  szerzodeses viszonyban allo cegek ado-ellenorizteteset. Szekely Ferenc ugyvezeto tevealelnok  egyszersmind a mediatorveny vegrehajtasat akadalyozza es nyilvanosan zsarolja a kormanyparti koroket  azzal, hogy kitalal, ha elmozditjak. Az utobbiakat persze nem nehez zsarolni, mivel egyertelmu a  gazdasagi maffia es a kormanypartok osszefonodasa. A mediahaboru ma mar nem politikai erok kozott,  hanem a kormanypartokkal osszefonodo maffia es az ujsagirok szakmai erdekcsoportjai kozt zajlik a  hirkozles felosztasaert"   (Uj Magyarorszag, majus 16. 1.,5.)  ***  "Semmi ketsegem, hogy ez idozitett politikai kampany, amelynek vilagos a celja. Nincs ebben semmi  meglepo, hiszen az ellenzek csupan kihasznalja azt a seregnyi lehetoseget, amit a karacsonyra kapott,  szamara rendkivul kedvezo mediatorveny kinal. A torveny az ellenzeknek kedvez annyiban, amennyiben  parlamenti sulyanal joval nagyobb befolyast kinal neki."   (Szekely Ferenc, az MTV ugyvezeto alelnoke, Nepszabadsag, majus 17. 1.,14.o.)  ***  "A kormanyzatot, a koalicios partokat is terheli mulasztas a mediatorveny meg-alkotasaban,  vegrehajtasaban tapasztalhato csuszasok es kesesek miatt" - mondta veszpremi sajtotajekoztatojan Janosi  Gyorgy, a parlament mediabizottsaganak tagja, az MSZP alelnoke. Nem tisztazodott kello melysegben az  intezmenyek, igy a televizio jogi statusa, amelyet husz even at a kincstar kozvetlenul finanszirozott mint  koltsegvetesi intezmenyt... Ezt az ellentmondast fel lehet es meg lehet oldani... Az ellenzeki partok kozos  "kezdemenyezeset" a Magyar Televizio alelnokenek azonnali felmenteset, helyere egy orszaggyulesi  biztos kinevezeset viszont teljesseggel elfogadhatatlannak tartja. A media-torveny tobbek kozott azt a celt  szolgalja, hogy megszunjek a media politikai, kormanyzati, parlamenti befolyasoltsaga. Az ellenzeki  partok egy resze ismet kozvetlenul kivan beavatkozni a media eletebe... Az ellenzeki fellepes neheziti a  media atalakulasat, keresztbe tesz annak, hogy a kuratoriumok altal megvalasztott elnokok mihamarabb  atvehessek megbizatasukat, es rendezett vi-szonyok kozott dolgozhassanak"   (Nepszava majus 17. 2.o.)   Az oldalt irta es osszeallitotta:  Bodnar Daniel==AZ AZSIAI SIKERMODELLT KELLENE KOVETNIKet delkelet-azsiai csodaLovas Istvan[Demokrata 22]Az egyik delkelet-azsai csoda az, hogy Gal Zoltan eszrevette, Torgyan Jozsef utan  immar o a masodik magyar politikus, akit megteritett a ketsegbevonhatatlan, valoban  letezo siker. Gal megtereserol a Magyar Nemzet szamolt be majus 14-en  Delkelet-Azsia: uj prioritas cimen.   A parlament elnoke egy delegacio elen aprilis 30-a es majus 11-e kozott Indoneziaban, Szingapurban es  Malajziaban jart. Mindharom orszagban a kommunistakat es a liberalizmust szinte szo szerint  tuzzel-vassal pusztito rendszer ert el rovid evtizedek alatt paratlan sikereket.Gal Zoltan nagyon oszinten nyilatkozott a Magyar Nemzetnek. Elmondta, hogy "a magyar kulpolitika  szamara csalodast okozott, hogy az Europai Unio es az azsiai terseg orszagai kozott letrejott bangkoki  csucstalalkozon europai barataink elutasitasa miatt az unio tarsult orszagai - koztuk hazank - nem  vehettek reszt"."Az evi 8-10 szazalekos gazdasagi novekedes, a szembetuno fejlodes lenyugozo ezekben az  orszagokban - fogalmazott Gal Zoltan. A haladas mutatoi kozul kiemelte, hogy Malajziaban evi  negymilliard dollart kolt az allam malaj diakok kulfoldi oktatasara." Es most jonnek azok a mondatok,  amelyek jelentosege szinte tulbecsulhetetlen - nem utolsosorban azert, mert Gal Zoltantol valok:"A nemzeti erdekeket a gazdasagban erosen vedik. A malajziai allam peldaul - tarsadalmi  kozmegegyezessel - kozponti szabalyozast vezetett be annak elkerulesere, hogy az orszagban is nagy  szamban elo kinaiak tulzott merteku szerephez jussanak. Az eros kozponti iranyitas miatt a parlament  sulya csekely ezen orszagok politikai eleteben, de - hangsulyozta Gal Zoltan - az allamok gazdagodnak,  fejlodnek, s nekunk tudomasul kell vennunk a sajatos, nem europai normak szerint mukodesuket. Ez a  gazdasagi kapcsolatok szorosabbra fonasanal alapveto kovetelmeny - tette hozza az Orszaggyules  elnoke."Ezek a mondatok szabad demokrata politikus szajabol elkepzelhetetlenek. Az elott pedig, hogy  mindezert Galt a szabad demokratak eddig nem tamadtak meg nyilvanosan, ertetlenul allunk. Gal  ertekelese - amelyben a malaj politika iranti egyertelmu csodalata fejezodik ki - ugyanis homlok-egyenest  ellenkezik a szabad demokratak filozofiajaval. Egy szabad demokrata egyreszt azt mondana, a nemzeti  erdekeket itt is erosen vedik, es Gal kijelentese lenyegeben ertelmezhetetlen, hiszen minden kormany a  nemzeti erdekeket vedi. Masreszt felhaboritonak tartana, ha valaki dicseri azt, hogy a malaj allam egy  nagy szamban az orszagban elo, de szamuknal lenyegesen befolyasosabb kisebbseget negativan  diszkriminal, es a pozitiv diszkriminacio a tobbsegnek nyujt kedvezmenyt. Gal Zoltan raadasul meg  olyan, a szabad demokratak valodi filozofiaja ertelmeben helytelen iranyu toleranciat is mutat, mely  szerint "sajatos, nem europai normak szerinti mukodesuket" tudomasul kell venni.Igazan orvendetes, hogy a malaj csoda ilyen elemi erovel hatott Gal Zoltanra. Ha arra gondolunk,  hogy Goncz Arpad is jart a tersegben, es ugyanugy jott vissza, ahogyan elment - vagyis reflexiok nelkul  -, a kulonbseg meg inkabb Gal mellett szol.A masik delkelet-azsiai csoda Szingapur. Egy honappal azelott, hogy Galek ellatogattak a 3 millios  varosallamba, az Asiaweek cimu hetilap statisztikai adataibol kitunt, hogy Szingapur az egy fore juto  GNP-ben merve megelozte az Europai Unio valamennyi tagallamat, beleertve Nemetorszagot is. A  '60-as evekben meg szegeny Szingapur elott tehat mar csak harom orszag all: Svajc, Japan es az  Egyesult Allamok.Szingapurt egy hajszal valasztja el attol, hogy behozza az Egyesult Allamokat az egy fore juto  GNP-ben. Mivel Szingapurban az eves fejlodes a tobbszorose az amerikainak, megtortenhet, hogy mire  ezeket a sorokat leirjuk, Szingapurban mar el is ertek az amerikai eletszinvonalat. Szingapur erejere  jellemzo, hogy az osszehasonlitaskent feltuntetett 150 millios orosz nepesseg egyutt mintegy a felet  exportalja annak, amit a 3 millios Szingapur. Ugyanakkor Szingapur a negyedreszet exportalja annak,  amit a 82 millios Nemetorszag vagy a 125 millios Japan, es alig kevesebb mint otodreszet annak, amit a  260 millios Egyesult Allamok.Szingapurnak nincs adossaga - szemben a csaknem 700 milliardos amerikai adossaggal.  Valutatartalekai ketszer akkorak, mint Svajce, amely, mondjak megbizhato korokben, nemileg hosszabb  ideje gyujti a penzt.Elkepeszto, bamulatba ejto szamok. Szinte kezenfekvo a kerdes: ha a szingapuri siker masolhato  (Malajziaban egy nem kinai etnikum masolta le sikerrel a szingapuri csodat), akkor miert ne masoljuk mi  is? Miert a szingapurinal lenyegesen gyengebb es joval nagyobb lyukakkal mukodo chilei  nyugdijrendszert akarjuk masolni, es miert nem a szingapuri tarsadalombiztositast, beleertve az ottani  nyugdijrendszert? Ha ennek az oka az, hogy nem ismerjuk, rajtunk ne muljek. A jovo hettol kezdve  ebben a rovatban tobb heten at lesz olvashato, hogy mikent mukodik ma a szingapuri csodagepezet.   Lovas Istvan ==A NAGY HAZUGSAG: "HA FELMONDJUK AZ ADOSSAGOT, A VILAGBANK NEM AD UJABB KOLCSONT"[Ismeretes, hogy Bulgaria felmondta adossagnak legnagyobb reszet. Most pedig itt az ujabb Vilagbank kolcson, $150 millio!]Bulgaria Fin Min Says World Bank To Lend Bulgarian $150 MlnAP-Dow Jones News ServiceSOFIA -- Bulgarian Finance Minister Dimiter Kostov said Friday that the World Bank will provide Bulgaria with a loan of $150 million to support structural reform, the state news agency BTA reported.The money will be granted after the signing of a standby agreement with the International Monetary Fund, Kostov said, according to BTA.The agreement in principle with the World Bank was reached Friday. Bulgaria and the IMF reached a preliminary agreement on a standby loan last Sunday.That's expected to be signed in July and is expected to bring in some $465 million in loans. ==[OROSZ VALASZTAS:  mindket fel tudja hogy a masik csalo]In Russian Vote, Both Parties Believe the Other Will CheatBy NEELA BANERJEE Staff Reporter of THE WALL STREET JOURNALMOSCOW -- With presidential elections in Russia still two weeks off, advisers to President Boris Yeltsin and his rival, Communist Gennady Zyuganov, are exchanging increasingly nasty accusations that the other side plans to cheat.The accusations suggest that the election could ignite new political conflicts in Russia. In a country where people's experience with voting comes from the showcase one-candidate "elections" of the Soviet era, charges of vote fraud point to the difficulties of holding polls that most voters will trust.The Communists have insisted over the last two weeks that the only way Mr. Yeltsin can win the election is by rigging the vote. "I think the president won't be elected, he will be named," said Viktor Ilyukhin, the Communist head of the parliament's security committee. "Boris Yeltsin will be declared president although Gennady Zyuganov will win."Neck and NeckThe Yeltsin camp struck back Thursday, with key advisers claiming the Communists are preparing to protest and engage in civil strife if they lose. Russian voter surveys have shown a surge in Mr. Yeltsin's popularity recently, putting him neck and neck with Mr. Zyuganov.In a mad-dash campaign tour of the country, Mr. Yeltsin is pledging money to just about every interest group, and he's expected to issue his campaign platform Friday."They [the Communists] believed a while ago that they could win. Now this opportunity is floating out of their hands," claimed Georgy Satarov, a close adviser to Mr. Yeltsin. If Mr. Yeltsin wins, the Communists "would start a campaign saying the returns were falsified and release their own count," he says.Chance of Fraud?Just how possible is it to carry out vote fraud on a large scale in Russia? The Russian Central Electoral Commission, which oversees the election and tabulates results, contends there are too many safeguards for falsification to occur. The local electoral commissions in each town and region are comprised of people of various parties, international observers will be on hand and the candidates have a right to send observers to polling stations.The Communists have said they will marshal 200,000 supporters to place in all 90,000 local polling stations. The Yeltsin camp said Thursday it has already assigned observers to polling stations in 55 of the country's 89 provinces.Foreign observers will only number about 500, and "can only touch the fringes of 90,000 polling stations," said Michael Meadowcroft, head of the observer mission with the Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe, a multilateral association of 54 countries involved in human rights and democracy-building in Europe.The candidates may be hard-pressed to monitor remote, rural polling stations. That's where most of the fraud in the 1993 and 1995 parliamentary elections allegedly occurred, says Alexander Sabyanin, head of the Expert Group on the Study of Elections and Referenda, an independent Russian political think tank.Mr. Sabyanin contends that voting records at the Central Electoral Commission, and reports from foreign observers in the last two elections, suggest vote fraud occurred in rural areas, fraud that benefited above all the Communist Party and its supporters, and Vladimir Zhirinovsky's nationalist Liberal Democratic Party.Weakness in CountrysideThe safeguards to falsification are weak at best in the countryside. Electoral commissions in villages don't have members reflecting the political spectrum. Instead, old Communist Party activists from the Brezhnev era run the show, "and they've changed very little from the old days," said Mr. Sabyanin.Mr. Sabyanin estimates that upward of 20% of the vote was falsified in the last two elections. Andrei Beryozkin, head of the electoral demography group EsparAnalitik and adviser to the Yeltsin campaign, claims vote fraud in the countryside and in small towns could have affected upward of two million votes in the last election.The methods are easy. For example, members of the electoral commission will go to voters" homes with a ballot box if the voters are physically unable to go to the polling station. Only about 4.5% of Russia's 102 million voters fall into that category, according to Mr. Beryozkin. In the 1995 elections, 2.5% of city dwellers cast their votes in these "mobile" ballot boxes. But in agricultural regions that voted heavily for the Communists and their allies, as much as 40% of the vote was collected this way."The ballots are supposed to be sealed in an envelope," Mr. Beryozkin said, "But it's hard to know what happens in the drive between a voter's home and the polling station."==AZ OMRI OROSZ VALASZTASI ANALIZISECENTRAL ELECTORAL COMMISSIONCONFERENCE ANALYSES TECHNICAL ASPECTS OF ELECTIONS. Central Electoral Commission (TsIK) Deputy Chairman Aleksandr Ivanchenko again criticized the bill on public monitoring of elections, recently passed by the State Duma but rejected by the Federation Council, saying it would allow too many observers to interfere with the vote-counting process. He was speaking at a 23 May roundtable on the presidential election sponsored by the TsIK and the International Foundation for Electoral Systems (IFES). IFES legal adviser Robert Dahl, who did not take a stand on the bill, pointed out that Russian parties are not taking advantage of the monitoring opportunities that exist under current legislation. TsIK member Olga Volkova argued that the Vybory electronic vote counting system's current legal status has been determined by two presidential decrees and a detailed government program. The TsIK hopes legislation will be passed on the use of computers in the vote counting process, but officials admit that the process will take many years. Ivanchenko pointed out that the TsIK has little power to control the activities of the privately owned media and can only refer violations to the State Press Committee and the Procurator-General's Office. The TsIK, for example, did not have the legal authority to take action against the anti-Communist Ne dai bog! (God Forbid), but its protests helped bring the paper in line with the law; the paper had not been providing the required ownership and editorial board information in its masthead, but recent issues of the paper have rectified that problem. Participants in the conference expressed concern that the turnout for the presidential election would be very low in St. Petersburg,  since voters there will have already voted twice in the city's gubernatorial election just weeks before the presidential election. -- Robert Orttung in MoscowTULEEV WINS COURT APPEAL. The Supreme Court upheld presidential candidate Aman Tuleev's appeal to change the manner in which he will be identified on the ballot, Radio Rossii reported on 24 May. The proposed ballot would have named Tuleev's occupation as chairman of the Kemerovo Oblast legislature; he wanted it to indicate as well that he is a member of the Federation Council, the upper house of parliament. Tuleev, who was the number three candidate for the Communist Party of the Russian Federation (KPRF) in the December parliamentary election, continues to loyally play the role of communist "reserve" candidate (see below). -- Laura BelinCANDIDATES AND PARTIESVOTE WITH YOUR HEART, YELTSIN AD ASKS. A Yeltsin paid advertisement broadcast on NTV 26 May shows an old man who is being bombarded by the sounds of street crowds and party slogans: "Immediately!" "With an iron fist!" "Only I!" The voiceover says, "When you are confused by endless party promises, vote with your heart." It ends with the slogan, "Russia is for Yeltsin with its heart." -- Robert Orttung in MoscowZYUGANOV AD PRESENTS PICTURE OF MODERATION. Communist candidate Gennadii Zyuganov used his free advertising time on 27 May on Russian Public TV (ORT) to emphasize the moderate aspects of his career. The advertisement shows the candidate with his family and talking to the camera in an informal setting. He takes the viewer on a tour of his home village, Mymrino. In describing his early career, he emphasizes his army service and years as a teacher. During the Andropov era, he worked on the staff of the Communist Party's Central Committee. He does not discuss his party leadership or ties with nationalist organizations. Zyuganov blames the collapse of the USSR and the Communist Party of the Soviet Union on the "monopoly on power, truth, and property" that the leaders then wielded. However, he salutes the middle-level managers who continue to work in spite of society's current problems. He pledges to support everyone willing to work, regardless of their party membership. The main criteria will be "professionalism and orderliness." He complains that one of the richest countries has sunk to such a level that it cannot pay the money it owes to its oldest and sickest citizens. He says that he is ready to cooperate with everyone, including the president and government, to guarantee political stability. He also strongly supports democratic electoral procedures. With this, however, the Communists apparently ran out of things to say, because the advertisement fell two minutes short of the allotted time. -- Robert Orttung in MoscowYELTSIN AD STRESSES CHOICE BETWEEN TWO MODELS, NOT TWO PERSONALITIES. In contrast to the other candidates whose faces appear on the screen during the majority of their free advertising time, President Yeltsin relies on celebrities and common people to make his points. Yeltsin's advertisement broadcast 27 May on Russian TV (RTR) presents actor Georgii Zhzhenov who warns that if Zyuganov comes to power, he and the people around him will carry out "another revolution, another perestroika." Another actor, Konstantin Raikin, argues that there were many good things during the communist era in Russia, but that these existed in spite of the political system. The advertisement also presents the life stories of ordinary people who say it is now possible to live a normal life and work without interference, while a return of the Communists would threaten these advances. The advertisements look very professional, and by couching the attack on the Communists in the life stories of ordinary citizens, Yeltsin gets his point across in a very sophisticated manner. -- Robert Orttung in MoscowMORE PEOPLE JOIN THE YELTSIN BANDWAGON. . . Over the weekend, many pro- reform political organizations endorsed President Yeltsin's re-election, including Sergei Shakhrai's Party of Russian Unity and Concord and Boris Fedorov's Forward, Russia!, Russian media reported. Moreover, the Democratic Russia movement, which helped secure Yeltsin's victory in the 1991 presidential election, also decided to back him, although leaders declared that they would prefer that the incumbent and Grigorii Yavlinskii form a coalition. The Congress of Russian Nobility supports Yeltsin since "each of their votes must be against Communists," according to ITAR-TASS on 24 May. Many prominent Russians outside the political field have also endorsed the incumbent. Famous folk dance director Igor Moiseev is planning a concert of his dance group in support of Yeltsin. Yurii Nikulin, a popular circus director and author of several books of jokes, spoke on Yeltsin's first free airtime slot on 16-17 May, according to Reuters. Two chess world champions--Anatolii Karpov, who ran unsuccessfully on Nikolai Ryzhkov's Power to the People party list in the parliamentary election, and Gary Kasparov--have been officially registered as Yeltsin campaign aides. On his visit to Krasnoyarsk Krai earlier this month, Yeltsin met with the well-known writer Viktor Astafev. Unlike many of his fellow "village prose" writers who have backed Zyuganov, Astafev warned of the dangers of a communist comeback. -- Anna Paretskaya-BUT YELTSIN CAMPAIGN GOING NOWHERE IN THE REGIONS. Many of the delegates at the fourth Russia's Choice congress held on 25 May were concerned about the president's disorganized campaign outside of Moscow. Yeltsin's main campaign organization, the All-Russian Movement of Social Support for B. N. Yeltsin (ODOP), has only a small staff and relies largely on existing parties, such as Russia's Choice, to mobilize voters. An activist from Saratov complained that the central organization promised to send flyers to the city, but so far has provided nothing, leaving locals to read handbills supporting Zhirinovsky. A delegate from Voronezh noted that the local authorities were backing Zyuganov. He argued that many provincial residents view what they see on TV as propaganda and that it is necessary to get activists to go door to door to convince them that Yeltsin was doing a good job. The Communists have been able to mobilize this kind of effort, but Yeltsin has not. Another delegate pointed out that polls showing Yeltsin pulling into the lead were not believable based on her experience in Siberia. She claimed that these false representations of the real state of affairs are "disorienting the president and the people working for him." Russia's Choice is the movement that spawned Yegor Gaidar's party Russia's Democratic Choice but stayed separate from Gaidar's party. -- Robert Orttung in MoscowSECOND CONGRESS OF REFORMIST FORCES FAILS TO BRING CANDIDATES TOGETHER. The Second Congress of Russia's Reformist Forces on 28 May, sponsored by Vladimir Shumeiko's pro-Yeltsin Reforms-New Course, failed to convince any of Yeltsin's competitors to withdraw their candidacies. Only former USSR President Mikhail Gorbachev responded to the invitation to attend, writing that he saw no grounds for cooperation. During the two-hour congress, which brought together 151 small parties, Free Democratic Party of Russia leader Marina Sale called for the president to improve the coordination of his campaign. She questioned why Sergei Filatov, leader of the All Russian Movement of Social Support for Yeltsin, and Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin, leader of Our Home Is Russia, did not attend the meeting even though they are playing major roles in Yeltsin's campaign. The 950 delegates approved an agreement backing Yeltsin as the candidate of the united reform forces and supported the creation of an undefined "coalition government" after the election to continue the reforms. The first congress was held in Yaroslavl on 22 April. -- Robert Orttung in MoscowLEBED PROPOSES TAX CUTS TO HALT CORRUPTION. In an interview published in Nezavisimaya gazeta on 23 May, Aleksandr Lebed suggested that tax cuts and tough anti-corruption measures were needed to fix Russia's "colonial economy." He remarked, "Under Brezhnev, oil and gas were sold and missiles were made with the oil dollars. Now we are selling oil and gas and buying Snickers with the oil dollars." Lebed said individual enterprises are at the mercy of corrupt government bureaucrats, who may deny them credits, tax privileges, or export benefits. He charged that these bureaucrats have more power now than they did in Soviet times. Cutting taxes collected by bureaucrats would "pull the money hoses out of the thieves' hands," he claimed. "A director is not paying his workers their wages? A banker is not returning deposits? There will tax inspections, seizure of personal and family property, a court case on deliberate bankruptcy, and a vacation to prison." Lebed has made fighting crime and corruption a central theme of his campaign literature and speeches. -- Laura BelinTULEEV CAMPAIGN HAMMERS YELTSIN. In a 28 May Russian TV (RTR) advertisement that begins by imposing flames over shots of the Kremlin and street demonstrations, Kemerevo Oblast legislature Chairman Aman Tuleev sharply criticizes Yeltsin's policies and particularly his control of the media. Tuleev is running as a "backup" communist candidate and has already announced his support for Zyuganov. The advertisement rebukes the media for following Yeltsin's every step, while remaining silent about Tuleev's numerous meetings with thousands of citizens. Tuleev also takes on those who tell him that he will never become president of Russia with a non-Russian name. His father is Kazakh, his mother Tatar, and he has a Russian wife. He claims that there are 40 million people of mixed nationality in Russia and that any president must make "an alliance of Russians by nationality, and non- Russians by blood, but all-Russian (Rossiiskie) patriots." Tuleev does not explicitly back Zyuganov in the advertisement but says that he is ready to support someone who supports his views. He calls for imposing price controls on basic foodstuffs and medicine along with greater state regulation of the economy, although "preserving all types of property." According to his plan, the government will have to submit to the supervision of the Duma and the people. If elected, his first decree would defend domestic producers from foreign competition. Using stirring music, crowd shots, and speaking in a variety of locations, Tuleev gets his message across much more effectively than many of his opponents who simply sit at their desk and talk to the camera. -- Robert Orttung in MoscowINTERVIEWIn an interview with OMRI's Robert Orttung on 28 May, ophthalmologist and presidential candidate Svyatoslav Fedorov explained his political views and coalition plans. Fedorov's efforts to form a "third force" alliance with Grigorii Yavlinskii and Aleksandr Lebed have yet to produce any results. His Party of Workers' Self-Government won about 4% of the vote (2.8 million votes) in the December Duma election. Fedorov continues to operate on patients once a week and constantly exercises his fingers when he is away from the hospital.OMRI: Do you consider yourself closer to the communists or the democrats? Fedorov: I am a realistic socialist, a democratic socialist, in favor of something like people's capitalism. I want all people to become small capitalists in their country, so they have their own home, capital, garden plot. If a person makes something, it should belong either to him completely or partly, if he is working for someone else. I want to create conditions so that each person will work for his own benefit, by his own labor. If you catch a fish you should be able to keep it. If you are using a net, then the fish should be distributed among all the fishermen. Each should give 30% to the government, that is to old people, children, and for the development of culture and education. This is a very simple system. It is already being put into place in America. American capitalists understood that they must build capitalistic socialism. They give social guarantees to people and gradually turn salaried workers into their friends who begin to think about the results of their labor just like the capitalists. I met Ross Perot and had a long conversation with him. He gave 40% of his stocks to his employees so that they would work for a good result like he does. They both have one goal. Today we have two goals: workers do nothing and try to get the maximum amount of money while managers try to get workers to work the maximum and pay them the minimum. It is an endless civil war, which nobody needs. We live in a thinly disguised slave-holders' society, veiled only by salaries. In reality it is economic slavery.OMRI: Why did the third force not work? Fedorov: My partners did not understand these ideas. They did not understand that individual leaders cannot raise the country up but only a specific policy. You can lift up millions of people when it becomes profitable for them to work, invent, and distribute what they create. People have to do this, not politicians. Politicians should resolve the problem of roads, energy supply, the preservation of nature, peaceful relations between peoples, a limited number of tasks.OMRI: Who will you support in the second round, Yeltsin or Zyuganov? Fedorov: I consider that one is a tiger, the other a leopard. It doesn't matter who eats me, one will eat me or the other will eat me. One ruins the country and the other ruins the country. There is no difference between them. One has stripes, the other spots.OMRI: Will you be able to work freely under the communists? Fedorov: No, if they limit our freedom, I will not be able to work. But today I cannot work because they do not pay me since there is no money in the budget. Nobody is working and everybody is stealing. It doesn't matter. It is bad under one system and bad under the other. On one side, the Communists do not allow me to work well and they pay me only a little and, on the other, the government doesn't pay me and people don't have any money. Why should I vote for them?CAMPAIGN DOCUMENTSYELTSIN ANSWERS VOTER QUESTIONS. The Yeltsin campaign has issued two booklets in which the candidate answers voters' questions. One contains 100 questions and answers, while the other has only 57; the former is written in the third person, while the latter is in the first person. The questions address some of the most important issues in the campaign: Yeltsin's personal traits, relations with the former Soviet republics, Chechnya, the events of 1993, and the economic reforms. Translations of some of the most interesting answers follow:Q: Is it true that I abuse alcohol? A: "To say 'yes' would be untrue. To say 'no' would not be convincing. Here people will not believe it unless they check it themselves. They would even say: 'What kind of Russian man are you if you can't drink?' So I will only say that I can drink, but that I don't abuse alcohol!"Q: Is it true that my health is not good? A: "... Last year because of huge emotional and physical burdens, I ended up in the hospital, but the doctors quickly put me back on my feet. Today, I don't think about those 'weaknesses'--everyday I work from five in the morning until late at night. I am used to such a schedule."Q: What were the Belavezha accords--the beginning of the disintegration of the empire or the birth of a new union? A: "The Belavezha accords marked the end of the uncontrollable collapse of a united state and the beginning of a new union of peoples, joined by a general fate. The idea of a new state did not occur to me, Shushkevich, or Kravchuk in one minute. Remember 1917-1918: just as the democratic February revolution took place, the republics immediately began the process of separation, moving toward independence, and the Russian empire disintegrated. On its territory several new national governments were founded, including in the Caucasus and in Central Asia. Ukraine was at the head of this process. The Bolsheviks managed to put down all national revolts by force: they suppressed the workers and peasants under arms, with an iron fist stamped out all the battles for independence, shot the national intelligentsia, and disbanded the parties. In place of the old Russian empire, they built a new empire--the Soviet Union. But it is impossible to build a genuine state by force or by the policy of "divide and conquer"--it is possible to suppress national differences, shunt them inside, but, whatever you do, they will smolder in time. ... The Belavezha accords were necessary mainly to turn the former republics of the collapsing union back to the center, toward the idea of a new union, to stimulate the negotiation process, and most importantly, to avoid the bloody "Yugoslav scenario" of uncontrollable collapse not only of the Soviet Union, but also of Russia itself--since already in 1991 the USSR law of 26 April 1990 [which gave the ethnic republics inside the Russian Federation more autonomy--a move by the Soviet government to weaken the power of Yeltsin's Russian government] was already showing results in terms of the events in Tatarstan and Chechnya. Therefore it is strange to hear today that our actions were directed at the consensual collapse of the union and its immediate destruction. I know that it will not be easy to overcome this myth, but I emphasize once again: the CIS was the only possible way of preserving a united geopolitical space at that time.Q: Yeltsin three times asked the Federation Council to confirm General Procurator Aleksei Ilyushenko, and now he is being investigated. Is it possible that the president is not very good at choosing his staff? A: Of course it is impossible to look deeply into everyone's soul. Yeltsin has rarely been let down by people, but there have been mistakes: [former Vice President Aleksandr] Rutskoi, [former Supreme Soviet Chairman Ruslan] Khasbulatov... In regard to Ilyushenko, the investigation is not complete, and if he is guilty, he will be prosecuted to the full extent of the law. Yeltsin believes that today the fight with corruption should be as tough as possible. Otherwise the reforms will not work. The reforms must be carried out with clean hands.Q: They say that the Kremlin is preparing some kind of "armed measures" in case Yeltsin is not re-elected. A: Yeltsin has no such plans. He is preparing his future work as the president. ...All talk about a coup that Yeltsin is preparing in the event of his failure is a provocation. Yeltsin is the legal president; he was elected by the people. He will never become a coup maker. Yes, in 1991 he climbed up on a tank. Yes, in 1993 he ordered the storming of the White House. But all this was in defense of democracy and the authorities legally elected by the people.Q: Yeltsin was in the Communist Party of the Soviet Union for about 30 years and was a candidate member of the Politburo. Why does he so sharply criticize the Communists? A: Regardless of what Zyuganov says today, the Communist Party of the Russian Federation (KPRF) is his only support. He is in no way an independent, non-partisan candidate. That means that he will have to submit to party discipline and follow the course of the Central Committee of the KPRF. These are people who do not like and frequently do not understand the very basis and principles of a market economy, honestly believing that the economy can live by command. Zyuganov will have to carry out a populist policy, give out money right and left, leading to a complete loss of government oversight over the financial sphere, the printing of worthless money, a new spiral of inflation, shortages of goods, and a collapse in the standard of living. We must not forget that those financial and business circles who lost out in the process of privatization are counting on the Communists to redistribute property. Such a redistribution threatens Russia with the abyss of civil war--something that even Zyuganov recognizes. -- Robert Orttung in MoscowThis material was reprinted with permission of the Open Media      Research Institute, a nonprofit organization with research offices in      Prague, Czech Republic. For more information on OMRI publications,      please write to:  info@omri.cz
